title: glazed carrots
directions: Peel carrots and cut into serving size pieces.
Cook carrots in boiling, salted water until just tender.
Drain.
While carrots are cooking, whip butter and honey together until light and fluffy.
Add orange rind, nutmeg and vanilla. Spoon glaze over carrots and toss well.

title: swiss chicken casserole
directions: Arrange chicken in a greased 14 x 10 x 2-inch baking dish or 2 (8 x 10-inch) dishes.
Combine soups, milk, salt, pepper and onion; mix well.
Spoon over chicken and cheese.
Sprinkle stuffing mix over all.
Drizzle with melted oleo.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Serves 12.

title: hot rolls
directions: Combine yeast with 1 cup water.
Combine sugar with 1 cup warm water.
Mix the two together and add eggs and butter.
Mix flour and salt into the mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Pinch off small ball size and work in hand, then place in pan.
Let rise.
Bake at 350° until brown.
These will keep in refrigerator for a week.

title: searion chicken casserole
directions: Combine and mix well all ingredients, except dressing and butter.
Put in casserole.
Top with the dressing and 1/2 cup melted butter.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Can be frozen without dressing.
Thaw completely, then put on dressing mixture and bake.

title: carla's zucchini cake
directions: Beat egg whites, sugar, Sweet 'N Low and vanilla together. Add dry ingredients, zucchini and raisins.
Bake in Bundt pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Contains 164 calories per 1/6 of cake. No fat!

title: chocolate-oatmeal no-bake cookies
directions: Melt first four ingredients in pan on stove and boil for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add 3 cups raw oats (may add more if liquidy).
Add 1/2 cup peanut butter.
Mix well.
Drop by spoon on waxed paper.
Cool.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix juice from pineapple, tropical fruit and fruit cocktail with pudding and Tang.
Reserve bananas until just before serving time.
Pour mixture over other ingredients and chill.

title: vodka pasta
directions: Cook pasta according to directions on package.
Drain.
While pasta is cooking, heat oleo in large skillet over medium, low heat.
Stir in vodka and red pepper.
Heat gently 3 to 4 minutes. Add tomatoes and salt.
Increase heat; cook until thick, about 10 minutes.
Stir in cream and cheese.
Serve over cooked pasta.

title: shrimp-macaroni salad
directions: Toss macaroni, cheese, celery, green pepper, onion, and shrimp. Blend mayo, sour cream and salt. Toss with macaroni mixture. Chill. Top with green pepper rings if desired.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl, then put into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole.
Refrigerate overnight.
Take from refrigerator 1 1/2 hours before baking.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours, uncovered.

title: chili sauce
directions: Cut up tomatoes, peppers and onions. Simmer all together on low for 1 hour.
Add brown sugar and spices. Simmer for 1/2 hour until it gets thick. This burns very easily.
Put in jars and seal. Very good.
This is very good on a beef roast or a venison roast, too.

title: vegetable quiche
directions: Partially bake pie shells at 400° for 6 minutes on preheated cookie sheet.
Remove.
Reduce oven to 350°.
Meanwhile, prepare filling.
In 10-inch skillet over medium heat in hot butter, cook onion and pepper with garlic until tender.
In medium bowl with electric mixer at high speed, beat milk, soup, eggs and flour until well mixed.
Stir in onion mixture and pimentos.
Distribute broccoli and cheese evenly into the two baked pie crusts. Carefully pour filling over broccoli and cheese.
Bake pies on cookie sheet 50 minutes at 350° or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 10 to 15 minutes on wire rack.
Makes 2 pies or 24 servings when cut into small cubes.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of mushroom soup

title: homemade noodles
directions: Spread flour onto countertop.
Take rolling pin and roll out noodles.
Cut in desired size and shape.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Rinse mushrooms and pat dry; remove stems.
Place caps on a greased baking sheet.
Combine remaining ingredients except olives; mix until well blended.
Spoon mixture into mushroom caps; top each with an olive slice.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: beefy jalapeno corn bread
directions: Combine corn meal, milk, egg whites, baking soda, oil and corn in a bowl.
Brown ground beef in skillet; put in colander and run hot water over meat to remove excess fat.
In a 10 1/2-inch nonstick skillet or 9 x 13-inch baking dish, sprinkle 1 tablespoon of corn meal over bottom.
Pour 1/2 of corn meal mixture into pan. Sprinkle evenly with browned beef.
Top with chopped onion, then shredded Cheddar cheese.
Pour other 1/2 of corn meal mixture over cheese.
Top with jalapenos.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: baked cauliflower and broccoli au gratin
directions: Cut broccoli and cauliflower into bite size pieces.
Steam until tender, drain.
Place vegetables in an 8 1/2 x 11-inch baking dish.
Scald 1 1/2 cups milk in saucepan.
Add pepper and 2 tablespoons butter.
Pour remaining 1/2 cup milk into a jar; add flour.
Cover and shake until smooth.
Pour flour mixture into hot milk, stirring constantly.
Cook over low heat until mixture thickens.
Add cheese; mix well.
Pour sauce over vegetables; top with bread crumbs and wheat germ.
Dot with remaining butter and paprika.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: taco salad
directions: Layer chips, lettuce, onion, tomatoes, chili beans and cheese. Pour dressing over and serve.

title: mocha pound cake
directions: Cream shortening.
Sift in sifted flour, sugar, instant coffee, salt, cream of tartar and soda.
Add water and vanilla. Mix until flour is dampened.
Beat one minute more. Pour into loaf pan lined and floured.
Bake at 325° for 65 to 70 minutes, even 1 1/2 hours won't hurt.
Sprinkle with confectionary sugar.
Cool for 10 minutes, then refrigerate.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix together, cook until thick.
Add butter and vanilla when thick.
Pour into precooked pie shell.

title: chili beans
directions: Cook onion with hamburger.
Melt chili brick with meat mixture.
Add in beans and tomatoes.
Salt and pepper if you want. Simmer about 1 hour; stir occasionally.

title: creamed oven chicken
directions: Mix flour, salt, pepper and paprika. Coat chicken.
Melt butter in shallow pan and lay chicken in pan, skin side down. Bake at 400° for 1 hour. Remove chicken from pan and make gravy by adding mushroom soup and chicken soup.

title: aunt verdie's fruit cake cookies
directions: Mix together.
Cook at 275° for 30 minutes.

title: foolproof pie crust
directions: Mix first four ingredients in separate bowl. Mix water with eggs.
Combine gradually.
Makes two (9-inch) double crusts and one (9-inch) shell.

title: carol's poppy seed bread
directions: Mix ingredients in large bowl.
Bake 1 hour in 2 greased loaf pans at 325°.
Cool in pan 1 hour, then add glaze.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until set.

title: grandma tanny's famous pork chops(crock pot recipe)
directions: Place dry ingredients in a plastic bag or mix in pie plate. Coat pork chops with dry ingredients.
Brown coated pork chops in 2 Tbsp. of oil in a skillet.	Place one chop at a time in the crockpot and put a small scoop of soup on each chop.
(Roasted garlic cream of soup works well also.)
Put some water (1 can) and any remaining soup in pan with drippings.
Mix and then pour over the chops in the crock pot.
Cook on low for 6-8 hours/or on high 3-4 hours.	Serve over rice.

title: easy stroganoff
directions: Stew meat until tender with onion and seasoned to taste. Leave 1/4 cup broth in pan.
Add to meat all of the mushroom soups.
Heat until boiling.
Turn off heat and fold in sour cream. Serve immediately over cooked noodles.

title: pound cake(easy)
directions: Put all ingredients in a mixing bowl and beat for 10 minutes with electric beater on high speed.
Pour batter into an ungreased tube pan.
Do not preheat oven.
Put in cold oven.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Combine ingredients in large skillet.
Cover; cook over medium heat for about 10 minutes.
Yields 6 portions.

title: caramel brownies
directions: Melt caramels and 1/3 cup milk; keep warm.
Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix with 1/3 cup evaporated milk and margarine.
Mix well.

title: red clam sauce
directions: In a heavy skillet, heat oil over low-medium heat.
Add garlic and anchovies.
Cook a few minutes; add tomato paste.
Cook a few more minutes.
Add parsley and red pepper, stirring with a fork to blend.
Add clam juice from bottles and juice reserved from canned clams.
Stir again to blend.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat to simmer.
Cook slow for 15 minutes.
Add clams.
Heat and serve over pasta.

title: christmas bonbons
directions: Grind dates and nuts through food grinder.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add sugar.
Add vanilla and red cake coloring.
Roll into balls.
Roll balls in meringue; bake at 250° for 30 minutes.

title: sherry's original deer and vegetable bake
directions: Brown meat in 1/4 cup water.
Add onion, bell pepper and celery.
Simmer until onions are clear.
Set aside.

title: corn cake
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients; add egg, milk and melted fat. Bake in shallow greased pan in moderate oven, 350°, for 20 minutes.
If buttermilk is used, use only 2 teaspoon baking powder and 1 teaspoon soda.
Drizzle caramel icing over cake.

title: strawberry congealed salad
directions: Heat pineapple enough to dissolve Jell-O.
Allow to cool. Add rest.
Put in 8 x 10-inch pan.

title: one gallon sweet tea
directions: Place 3 bags of Lipton family-size tea bags in top of coffee maker.
Pour 12 cups water in back of coffee maker and turn on to brew into bottom decanter.
When ready (about 5 minutes), measure 2 cups sugar (if desired) to it and stir in a 1-gallon container. Add the additional amount of water and serve.

title: southern ribs
directions: You will need 1 Reynolds oven bag (large size).

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until frothy; add sugar, Karo and milk.
Cook slowly over low heat and stir constantly until it boils up once.
Cool completely.
Add condensed milk (whipped) or whipping cream (whipped) and vanilla.

title: barbecue weenies
directions: Mix and heat equal amounts of jelly and mustard.
Add hot dogs, cut into 2-inch pieces.
Heat thoroughly.
The longer they stay in the sauce, the better.
These do well in a crock-pot. Serve with toothpicks.

title: quantity hot dog sauce
directions: Brown the beef; drain.
In a large skillet, combine all ingredients; salt to taste.
If too tangy, add sugar to your taste.
Add finely crumbled bread crumbs, enough to thicken as desired.
Simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours on low heat, but stir often.

title: crab imperial
directions: Heat milk or cream in a small saucepan.
Thoroughly mix the mustard and flour into melted fat and stir heated milk or cream into mixture.
Cook until thickened; remove from heat and add remaining ingredients except bread crumbs.
Mix well and spoon mixture into clam shells.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until heated through or place 4 to 5 inches below broiler unit until lightly browned.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream margarine.
Add sugar gradually.
Add eggs.
Beat in one at a time.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Sift together and add to the mixture flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix in small bowl pecans, granulated sugar and cinnamon.
Grease and flour Bundt pan. Sprinkle 1/2 of nut mixture in bottom of pan.
Spoon 1/2 batter over nuts.
Sprinkle rest of nuts over batter.
Cover with remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 or 10 minutes until done.
This cake is delicious!

title: hay stacks
directions: Melt morsels over low heat, stirring gently.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper. Good for Christmas parties.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cream shortening, sugar, eggs, pumpkin and water.
Blend all dry ingredients.
Add nuts and raisins.
Bake in 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) greased pans for 65 to 70 minutes.

title: homemade bread
directions: Mix water and sorghum, sprinkle yeast on water and let stand 5 minutes, Add salt, lard and wheat flour. Stir well, add white flour, stirring constantly. Knead well until dough is smooth, firm and elastic. Put in a grease bowl and cover with a cloth. Allow to rise in a warm place for 1 hour. Punch down and let rise 15 minutes. Grease four, 2 pound bread pans. Let rise 1 hour. Bake at 375 degrees for 45 minutes. Brush with butter.

title: brownies
directions: Mix together butter and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients in order.
Bake on a large cookie sheet at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes (ovens may vary).
Watch closely until you can touch the top and finger will not stick.
Do not overbake!
Makes 36 (2-inch) squares.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, carrots and onions to tender; drain.
Add soup and sour cream.
Mix with vegetables.
Mix stuffing mix and butter.
Put 1/2 of stuffing on bottom of pan; add the vegetables and then top with other half of stuffing.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: peach delight cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 2 round 8 or 9 x 1 1/2-inch pans.
Drain peaches, reserving syrup. Add enough water to reserved syrup to measure 1 1/2 cups.
Prepare cake mix as directed on package, except substitute syrup mixture for the water.
Pour batter into pans. Bake and cool as directed on cake mix.
Cut peaches into bite size.
Mix yogurt and whipped topping. Fold in peaches. Fill layers.

title: easy chicken and dumplings
directions: Make Bisquick dumplings following directions on box.

title: stuffed mushrooms parmesan
directions: Remove stems of mushrooms and chop.
Combine stems, cheese, butter and onion.
Fill mushroom caps.
Place on rack of broiler pan.
Broil 2 to 3 minutes or until top of filling is slightly crusty.
Serve hot.

title: rice casserole
directions: Saute hamburger, celery, onions and carrots; add soups, water, soy sauce and rice.
Bake in covered casserole at 350°
for 1 hour.
Uncover and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake until cheese melts.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Separate eggs; beat egg whites, set aside.

title: easy doughnuts
directions: Heat deep fryer or oil.
Punch a hole in the center of each biscuit, then you are ready to drop 2 or 3 at a time into the grease.
Let cook until golden brown, then turn and cook other side until golden brown.
When all are cooked, you can top with icing or cream cheese.
Makes 40 small doughnuts.

title: goulash
directions: Fry beef and onions in pan.
Drain off fat.
Chop tomatoes. Add tomatoes, kidney beans, chili powder, macaroni and liquids to beef mixture.
Simmer, covered, about 20 minutes, until macaroni is tender, stirring occasionally to keep from sticking.
Thin with a little water during cooking, if necessary.
Makes 4 servings.

title: twice-baked potatoes
directions: Bake number of potatoes needed.
For each potato, cut off top and scoop out potato, leaving a shell.
Mash and add the ingredients.
Bake about 15 minutes, until cheese is melted.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Top with any vegetable, chopped fine.

title: pink strawberry salad
directions: Mix strawberry Jell-O according to directions on box.
Add pineapple, marshmallows and cottage cheese; mix well.
Blend in Cool Whip and pecan bits.
Chill overnight.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix ground chuck or ground beef, eggs, bread, garlic, oats, onions, pepper, salt and seasoned salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape into meatballs.
Place meatballs into boiling water for about 5 minutes; drain.

title: depression cake
directions: Bake in a 350° oven for 30 - 35 minutes.

title: cinnamon twists
directions: Beat eggs well, beating in sugar gradually; stir in milk. Sift flour, baking powder, salt and cinnamon together; stir into egg mixture.
Add butter and vanilla; mix well.
Turn dough onto floured board; knead lightly.
Pat dough to thin rectangle; cut into 3 x 1 1/2-inch strips.
Cut slits.
Let twists rest for about 5 minutes; fry twists (4 or 5 at a time) in a deep hot fat until golden.
Drain on paper towels; roll in mixture of cinnamon and sugar.
Yield: 3 dozen twists.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Cover
starter,
milk and 1 cup flour.	Let stand for 4 to
8 hours.
Add
rest
of
flour
and
seasonings.
Mix all together; turn out onto floured board.
Knead lightly 8 to 10 times.	Roll or pat out dough to about 1/2 to 3/4-inch thickness; cut out biscuits.
Dip each biscuit in salad oil;
place in
pan and let stand for 30 minutes.
Bake in a 375° oven for 30 minutes.

title: greek salad
directions: Wash romaine lettuce, pat dry with paper towels and tear into bite size pieces.
Place in a large bowl with cucumber, mint, cheeses, olives and tomato.
In small bowl, mix olive oil, lemon juice, garlic and pepper; whisk together until well blended.
Pour dressing over salad, toss well and serve.

title: pineapple-cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and cottage cheese.
Drain pineapple and add to mixture, then add to powdered jello.
Mix and chill.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Use large pot or skillet.
Press your hamburger lightly on bottom of pot.
Salt and pepper.

Put 1 layer of potatoes on top of hamburger, 1 layer of green beans on top of potatoes, 1 layer of potatoes on top of green beans, 1 layer of carrots on top of potatoes and then add the last layer of potatoes.
Slice 1 onion on top; salt and pepper.
Pour tomato soup on top and then 1 can of water.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Enjoy.

title: minted hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix and store in airtight container. Use 3 to 4 heaping teaspoonfuls mix per cup of hot water or milk.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Mix ingredients well, except the wheat flour.
Add whole wheat flour.
Knead by hand or dough hooks until dough handles easily. Let rise until double.
Divide into 4 parts.
Roll each section out.
Spread with margarine, sprinkle with brown sugar, raisins, cinnamon and nuts.
Roll into log shape, slice approximately 1 1/2 inches.
Place in baking pan.
Let rise until double.
Bake 25 minutes at 375°.
Frost when cooled (powdered sugar and lemon juice).

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: guacamole
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and cover and refrigerate at least 1 hour before serving.
Serve with tortilla chips or as a condiment.
Yields about 2 1/2 cups.

title: 4 pie crusts
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening; add water, egg and vinegar.
Stir until mixed.
A very pliable dough.
Makes 4 crusts.

title: pepsi chicken
directions: Melt margarine in electric skillet.
Place chicken in skillet and pour Pepsi and ketchup over chicken.
Cook at 200° for 2 hours.
Serves 4.

title: meatballs
directions: Roll into bite size balls.

title: happy day cake
directions: Measure into sifter the first 4 ingredients.
Measure into a bowl the shortening.
Measure into cup the milk and vanilla.
Have 2 unbeaten eggs ready.
Blend all together.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° to 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes a good birthday cake.

title: wild rice and vegetable salad
directions: Cook rice in water and salt until tender.
Drain and rinse. Combine next 7 ingredients in salad bowl and whisk for dressing. Add vegetables and rice.
Toss and serve.
This keeps well for several days in refrigerator.
Serves 4 (3/4 cup) servings, 130 calories per serving, 4 gm fat, 0 chol and 43 mg sodium.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Heat olive oil in small skillet.
Add garlic and remove from heat.
Combine bread crumbs, cheese, salt and pepper.
Brush chicken with oil mixture.
Dip pieces into crumb mixture.
Place on baking pan.
Bake at 350° about 1 hour.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Boil sugar, syrup, water, butter and vanilla until light brown or crack stage (300° or 290°).
Remove from fire and add soda. Stir and pour over peanuts that have been spread on cookie sheet. Let cool then break.

title: sweet and sour sausage
directions: Brown sausage; drain and cut into 1-inch chunks.
Combine cold water with cornstarch.
Mix with salt, vinegar and syrup.
Heat over medium heat until thick.
Add all other ingredients and heat for 5 minutes before serving.
Keep warm in chafing dish.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake in a tube pan at 325° until cake is done.
Test with toothpick.
If it comes out clean, cake is done.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Core cabbage and place in enough boiling water to cover. Cut off cabbage leaves as they become soft. Trim off vein of each cabbage leaf. Set aside.

title: chocolate cherry drops
directions: Melt chocolate in double boiler.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg; blend well.
Stir in vanilla and melted chocolate; beat until combined.
Add in flour, soda and salt; mix.
Stir in cherries and nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Bake 13 to 15 minutes or until set at 350°.
Makes 5 dozen cookies.

title: baked walleye
directions: Place fillets in shallow baking dish.
Pat with paper towel. Spread mayonnaise on fillets.
Sprinkle on bread crumbs and tarragon.
Drizzle with butter.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Serve with lemon and tartar sauce.

title: creole sauce
directions: Slice onion, pepper and celery julienne-style and saute in margarine 4 to 5 minutes.
Add
remaining
ingredients
and simmer 1 hour.

title: angel food cake
directions: Put egg whites in extra large mixing bowl.
Add cream of tartar, salt, vanilla and almond extract.
Whip by hand or with electric mixer until foamy.
Add 1 cup sugar, 2 tablespoons at a time, whipping between each addition.
Whip until peaks stand up very stiff.
Then sift 1 cup sugar and flour together three times. Sift small amount of flour and sugar over egg mixture and fold in with spatula until all flour mixture is added.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake in 400° oven for 45 minutes.

title: chewy cake
directions: Mix melted margarine and sugar; cream well.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour and mix well.
Then add nuts.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let cool and cut into squares.

title: cupa cupa cupa peach cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Mix together flour, sugar and margarine.
Pour into a greased 9 X 11 pan.
Pour peaches on top, including juice.
Bake until crust rises to the top and turns golden brown.
Remove from oven and top with vanilla ice cream and serve.

title: easy stew
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Boil everything except frozen vegetables 30 minutes.
Add vegetables and simmer another 30 minutes.
Season to taste.

title: chicken casserole with japanese veggies
directions: Place vegetables (uncooked) on bottom of casserole dish. Pound chicken to 1/4-inch thickness and place on top of vegetables.
Mix mayonnaise, soup and cheese.
Spread on top of chicken.
Sprinkle with Italian bread crumbs.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.

title: cranberry salad ring
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Chill until consistency of unbeaten egg whites.
Chop cranberries, unpeeled and seeded oranges and unpeeled and cored apples.
Combine with the undrained pineapple and sugar.
Mix well.
Fold fruit mixture with jello. Add chopped pecans.
Pour into a lightly oiled 10 cup ring mold. Chill overnight.

title: new potato bake
directions: In large bowl, combine soup, sour cream and hot pepper sauce. Add potatoes and onions; toss to coat well.
In 2-quart oblong baking dish or 2-quart casserole, spoon potato mixture in even layer.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes, or until potatoes are fork-tender.
Garnish with chives.

title: butterhorns
directions: Mix the flour, shortening, salt and sugar. Dissolve the yeast in 1 cup of lukewarm milk. Add 1 teaspoon sugar and 1 teaspoon flour.
Let sit until the ingredients start foaming.
Pour this into the flour mixture with 2 eggs.
Mix well. Work into a large ball.
Place in a large greased bowl.
Set in refrigerator until it is raised (or overnight).
Divide dough into 5 portions.
Roll each piece like a pie crust and cut into pie slice pieces. Roll each piece, starting with wide end.
Use soft butter to butter each butterhorn.
Let raise.
Bake at 350° until brown.
Cool horns, then spread with powdered sugar frosting.

title: apple pudding cake
directions: Combine apples and sugar.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Bake in a 9-inch pan for 30 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip or frost with powdered sugar frosting.

title: sauerbraten
directions: Put water, vinegar, sugar, pickling spices and onion in pot to warm.
Put meat in a bowl and pour marinade over meat.
Cover and refrigerate for 3 to 4 days, turning meat once a day.
Remove meat from marinade.
Pat dry with paper towel. Brown meat on all sides in a little oil or shortening.
Add marinade, simmer for 2 hours. Add gingersnaps.
Cook another hour, strain gravy.
Sometimes it is necessary to thicken gravy a little more.
Meat is ready to slice.

title: vegetable fried rice
directions: Heat oil.
Add celery and onion.
Stir-fry for 2 minutes.
Add peas and carrots.
Continue to stir-fry, stirring constantly until vegetables are tender-crisp, about 4 minutes.
Add rice.
Sprinkle with seasonings.
Stir-fry until rice is heated and flavors are blended, about 2 minutes.

title: cordon bleu casserole
directions: Rinse broccoli under water to thaw and separate; pat dry. Line bottom of 8 x 8 x 2-inch microwave-safe baking dish with bread.
Top with chicken, ham and broccoli.
Stir onion powder into soup; pour over all.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover.
Chill overnight, if desired.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Dredge slices in cornmeal.
Fry tomatoes in hot oil in a skillet until browned; turning once.
Drain well on paper towels.
Sprinkle slices with salt, pepper and sugar.
Serve hot.

title: tex mex dip
directions: Spread refried beans in bottom of casserole.
Mix sour cream, mayonnaise and taco seasoning.
Spread on top of beans.
Layer on green onions and then tomatoes, topping off with the grated cheese.
Chill.
Serve with tortilla chips.
This may be doubled for a large group.

title: big noni cascio chocolate cookies
directions: Mix flour and Crisco together like for pie crust.
Set aside. Cook dates and raisins in the water, for 20 minutes.
Cool, then add nutmeats.
Set aside.
Beat eggs very well and add whiskey. Add to crust-like mix then add all dry ingredients and cooled raisin, date nut mix.
Mix well.
Drop by tablespoon onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° till slightly brown; about 20 minutes.
Frost with glaze.

title: key lime pie
directions: When cream cheese is soft, whip in milk, vanilla and juice until soft and fluffy.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Top with Cool Whip.
Place in refrigerator or freezer.
You may add a few drops of green coloring.

title: oriental salad
directions: Cut up onions and peppers.
Add to coleslaw.
Crush noodles and add to coleslaw.
Add all other ingredients and let set for 1 to 2 hours before serving.
Do not make way ahead or it will become soggy.

title: chicken stir-fry
directions: Combine soy sauce, sherry, cornstarch, garlic and 1/4 cup water; set aside.
Cut chicken in small strips or chunks.
In wok, stir-fry chicken in hot oil for 2 minutes.
Add vegetables; stir-fry 4 minutes.
Add soy sauce mixture; cook and stir until slightly thickened.
Serve over rice.

title: salisbury steak with onion gravy
directions: In bowl, combine 1/3 cup soup with ground beef, crumbs, egg, salt and pepper.
Shape into oval patties.	In frying pan brown patties.
Drain
off fat and remove patties.
Keep warm. Gradually blend
flour
into
remaining
soup,
mixing
until smooth.
Add remaining
ingredients,
blending
well.
Add to frying pan.
Heat to
boiling, stirring to loosen brown bits. Cover;
cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add patties to gravy and simmer an additional 15 minutes.

title: hobo dinner in a can
directions: Butter inside of coffee can.
Place ingredients in can in order.
Cover can with heavy foil.
Punch a couple of holes in foil for steam to escape.
Cook on hot grill 30 minutes, or until done.
Serve in can with long handled fork and mitts or empty can onto plate.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken breasts in bottom of a large baking dish.
Mix soup, chicken broth and Veg-All together.
Pour over chicken; season with salt and black pepper to taste.

title: kung pao pork
directions: Combine pork and 2 tablespoons soy sauce; refrigerate for 30 minutes.
Combine remaining 2 tablespoons soy sauce, lemon juice, cornstarch, crushed red pepper and 1/4 cup water.
In wok or large skillet, stir-fry pork and garlic in hot oil for 3 minutes or until brown.
Add red pepper and onion.
Stir-fry for 3 minutes.
Add cornstarch mixture; cook and stir until slightly thickened.
Add peanuts.
Serves 4.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix everything together and pour in pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: jam-filled cookies
directions: In large bowl cream shortening and sugars.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; mix until smooth.
Stir together flour and next 4 ingredients; stir into creamed mixture.
Cover and chill.

title: oreo ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients together and press into a large bowl.
Keep in freezer, covered.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Mix all ingredients except chicken in large Dutch oven.
Add chicken and simmer for 1 hour. Serve over cooked white rice.
This can also be baked, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lazy man's cobbler
directions: Cook the fruit (peaches, blackberries or cherries) and sweeten with the 1 cup sugar.
If using canned, sweetened fruit, omit sugar.
Prepare batter by mixing together the dry ingredients and milk with the additional cup of sugar.
Melt the butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add fruit to pan, then drip batter over hot fruit. Bake for about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift flour; measure and resift with the next dry ingredients. Beat the egg; add milk and shortening, then add to flour mixture and beat just until smooth.
Fold in drained corn; let stand 5 to 10 minutes while heating shortening in a frying pan.
Drop small amounts like pancakes in frying pan.

title: sweet and sour wieners
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Simmer about 30 minutes on low.

title: tuna and rice casserole
directions: Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Microwave 10 to 15 minutes on High.

title: pa's fruit salad
directions: Combine ingredients in a large bowl.
Toss gently.

title: ricotta cookies
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Mix in Ricotta cheese, eggs, flavor and salt in another bowl.
Add to butter mix and blend until smooth.
Stir in baking soda and flour.
Drop onto a greased cookie sheet by tablespoon.
Sprinkle with a little nuts.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes until dry to touch.

title: bean soup
directions: Drain beans and potatoes; mix together.
Add mushroom soup. Add water to test.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground meat and onion; add enchilada mix, tomato soup, mushroom soup, Cheddar cheese soup and Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Cook for about 10 minutes, then pour in casserole dish, alternating meat with tortillas.
Top with grated cheese (1 1/2 cups).
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes; can be frozen before you cook.

title: trifle
directions: Put layer of vanilla wafers in a 1 1/2-quart bowl.
Make up Jell-O and cool. Drain fruit cocktail and put fruit in with vanilla wafers.
Pour Jell-O over and let set.
Make up Whip 'n Chill, pour over set Jell-O and chill.
Decorate with Cool Whip.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Put all ingredients except the vanilla in the top of a double boiler.
Be sure the bottom of the double boiler does not touch the water in the lower pan.
Beat over boiling water for 7 minutes.
Remove from heat and beat
in vanilla.

title: three bean and franks bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Heat oil in large saucepan over medium heat; add onion and garlic and cook 8 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add red and green peppers; cook 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in baked, butter and red beans, ketchup, brown sugar, vinegar and mustard; bring to a boil. Stir franks into bean mixture. Transfer mixture to 2 qt. casserole or 8 or 9 inch square baking dish. Bake 40 to 45 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook for 1 1/2 hour on simmer.
Stir in 1 pound cubed Velveeta cheese.
Simmer until blended.

title: german coffee cake
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Let stand a few minutes, then stir.
Stir in sugar, salt and 1 cup of the flour.
Beat the egg; add softened lard and add to flour mixture.
Beat in the remaining flour until mixture is smooth.
Drop by spoonfuls into a greased shallow baking pan.
Let rise in a warm place until dough is nearly doubled.
Dot the top of dough with the slivers of margarine or butter.
Then sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon. Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: individual cheese cakes
directions: Cream sugar and cheese together; add eggs one at a time. Add lemon juice and vanilla; beat well. Place vanilla wafers in cup cake papers in muffin pan, top with one tablespoon of batter. Bake at 325° for 20 - 25 minutes. Cool slightly. Remove paper when completely cooled topping with cherry pie filling.

title: cheesy potatoes
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Pour on thawed hash browns.
Add soup and sour cream.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: kidney bean salad
directions: Mix thoroughly with enough mayonnaise or salad dressing to moisten.
Chill.

title: cheesy ranch potatoes
directions: Microwave or boil potatoes until tender, unpeeled.
Cut potatoes into quarters.
Spray a casserole dish with a nonstick spray and line dish with potatoes.
Place dots of butter around potatoes or squeeze liquid butter over them.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix thoroughly; chill overnight.
Serve with crackers or raw vegetables.

title: robert's mom, sue, fruit salad
directions: Wash and cut red grapes in half.
Add chopped apples, bananas.
Add mandarin oranges with juice.
Mix all together with grapes and nuts.
Add whipping cream.
Can be refrigerated overnight.

title: coconut balls
directions: Mix together and refrigerate. Shape into balls and dip into melted chocolate. Lay on wax paper to cool.

title: cheese cupcakes(serves 24 to 26)
directions: Have cream cheese at room temperature.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Cream cheese and sugar.
Add vanilla and egg yolks.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and let stand 5 minutes.

title: spanish style shrimp and rice(quick and simple)
directions: Shell and devein shrimp; set aside.
Heat olive oil in saucepan and add rice, onion, green pepper and garlic.
Saute until rice is lightly browned while stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and add tomatoes and their juices.
Also add oregano, chili powder and pepper.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Cook shrimp in boiling water or steam for 4 to 5 minutes until done.
Add shrimp to mixture and let it stand for 5 minutes, then serve with fresh green tossed salad.
Makes 4 servings.

title: "loukoumades" - honey puffs
directions: Dissolve yeast with warm water; add in salt and flour and slowly mix well.
Dough should be a loose texture.
Cover and let rise in a warm place.
Heat deep oil.
Make sure it's very hot before adding dough.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Baking Temperature: 325°.
Baking Time: 45 minutes.

title: peach fried pies
directions: Cook peaches in water or until tender; drain and mash. Combine with sugar, lemon juice and spices.
Roll out pastry and cut into 5-inch rounds.
Place 3 tablespoons peach filling on half of each round.
Moisten edges with water; fold in half, pressing edges together with fork to seal.

title: round steak supper
directions: Cut steak in bite-sized pieces, removing as much fat as possible.

title: honey wheat bread
directions: Put margarine, water and honey in microwave.
Melt margarine and heat only to luke warm.
In a bowl mix with all other ingredients.
Knead, let rise, cook for 15-20 minutes at 400 degrees.

title: spinach balls
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well. Roll into walnut sized balls.
Freeze, well wrapped.
When ready to serve, unwrap and place on baking sheet still frozen.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix oleo, milk and sugar in a saucepan and bring to a full, rolling boil.
Take off stove and add vanilla, cocoa, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Mix all together and drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: quick snack
directions: Slice sausage into bite size pieces.
Brown in skillet.
Pour barbecue sauce over heated meat.
Ready to serve with toothpicks.

title: hot cheese spread
directions: Mix ingredients in mixer, cream cheese, sour cream and milk; add cut up dried beef, garlic, salt and pepper.
Put in shallow pie pan.
Brown 3/4 cup chopped pecans in 2 tablespoons butter. Sprinkle pecans on top and bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable cheese soup
directions: Cook first 7 ingredients until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and melt.
Serve inside Kaiser rolls, that have been hollowed out.

title: vichyssoise soup
directions: Peel potatoes and slice thin.
Put in a saucepan with butter and chopped shallots. Add enough water to cover.
Cook 1 hour over low heat.
When cool, blend in blender.
Add enough Coffee Rich to make soup as thick or thin as you want it. Add salt and pepper to your taste. This soup is served cold, but I prefer to heat it.

title: veggie salmon casserole(tuna optional)
directions: Drain salmon; set aside.
Cook noodles according to package directions.
Drain and rinse in hot water.
Combine noodles, salmon, celery and onions.
Blend in sour cream, mustard, mayonnaise, thyme and salt.
Spoon half the mixture into a buttered 2-quart casserole.
Top with half the zucchini; repeat layers.
Top with cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly.
Sprinkle with chopped tomatoes.

title: cookie salad
directions: Mix pudding and buttermilk. Fold in remaining ingredients. Add strawberries, bananas, fruit cocktail or peaches, if desired. Just before serving, add crushed Oreo cookies.

title: garlic chicken
directions: Skin meat, remove fat and cut breasts in half.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Brown in oil.
Stir in heads of peeled garlic cloves, thyme and stock.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.

title: candyland
directions: Melt margarine and let cool.
Mix with cookies and press in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix instant pudding and milk.
Add vanilla ice cream. Beat until smooth and then pour on cookie mixture.
Spread on Cool Whip and sprinkle with Heath bars (crushed).
Refrigerate.
Enjoy!

title: veggie chili(meatless chili)
directions: Cook beans in water until done. Add rest of ingredients and cook for 45 minutes or until veggies are done. Good with homemade bread or cornbread.

title: brownies
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, then add eggs.
Combine dry ingredients, then mix well.
Pour into greased pan and bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Chop apples and oranges.
Mix all ingredients and chill at least 2 hours.

title: sweet potato-oatmeal bread
directions: Cream oil and sugar.
Add eggs and sweet potatoes; mix well. Sift dry ingredients; add a little at a time with the water.
Add oatmeal, pecans and coconut.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until done.
Let cool 10 to 15 minutes before taking out of pan.
Makes 2 large loaves.
When bread starts to dry out, slice and use cream cheese between 2 slices.

title: party wieners
directions: Mix all ingredients. Simmer in crock pot on low heat. Serve warm.

title: buttermilk pineapple congealed salad
directions: Combine sugar and pineapple and bring to a boil.
Add gelatin and dissolve.
Let cool.
Add buttermilk, whipped topping and nuts.
Spray glass dish with cooking spray and pour in mixture. Refrigerate until firm.
Serves six.

title: 7 layered salad
directions: In 9 x 13-inch pan, put lettuce, sprinkle on celery, onion, green pepper, frozen peas, eggs and bacon.
Mix salad dressing and sugar together.
Spread on top of salad.
Sprinkle with cheese. Cover with Saran Wrap and put in refrigerator 8 hours or overnight.

title: dog, cow and pig
directions: You will also need 20 wooden toothpicks.

title: aunt karen's bow ties
directions: Open biscuits and flatten out on cutting board.
Dip into melted butter, then into sugar and cinnamon mixture.
Twist one time and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: biscotti(italian cookies)
directions: Mix sugar with butter, seed, anise and nuts.
Beat in eggs with a large mixing spoon.
Mix dry ingredients and add to egg mixture.
Mix thoroughly; chill dough, covered, for 2 to 3 hours. Shape dough directly on greased cookie sheets to form flat loaves 1/2-inch thick and 2-inches wide.
Place only 2 loaves well apart on a sheet.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Let cool in pans when cool.
Slice loaves into 3/4-inch slices and lay the slices on their cut sides.

title: pound cake
directions: Beat together shortening and sugar. Sift flour and 1 level teaspoon baking powder. Mix all ingredients and beat well. Grease and flour tube pan. Mix equal around pan. Bake at 300° until done, approximately 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: crazy mixed-up pizza sandwiches
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Mix in seasoning and tomato sauce.
Add about 3/4 of the cup of Mozzarella cheese.
Fill buns with mixture.
Top with remaining cheese.
Wrap each in aluminum foil. Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: yummy shrimp salad(servings:  4)
directions: Mix together shrimp and celery; set aside.
In separate bowl, mix the rest of the ingredients to make dressing.
Pour dressing over shrimp and toss well.
Serve chilled on bed of chopped lettuce, garnished with tomato, hard-boiled egg and lemon wedges. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: turkey noodle soup
directions: In 8-quart kettle or Dutch oven, place turkey carcass, water, celery, celery leaves, onion, bouillon cubes, salt, pepper and bay leaf.
Heat to boiling; lower heat; cover and simmer 1 hour. Remove carcass and let cool.

title: fruit pudding
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
In separate bowl, combine remaining ingredients together and pour over first mixture.
Bake 50 minutes at 350°.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Mix, chill and serve.
It is good!

title: texas brag chili
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Drain fat.
Place meat in heavy iron pot or Dutch oven.
Add onion, peppers (with seeds or seeded, if desired), garlic, salt, paprika, cumin, chili powder, pepper, tomato sauce, water and beer.
Stir until well blended.
Simmer 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
About 1/2 hour before serving, mix masa with enough water to make a heavy paste.
Add to chili while stirring chili to avoid lumping.
Serves 6.

title: pasties(pronounced pass-tees)
directions: Measure flour and salt into bowl.
Cut in Crisco thoroughly. Sprinkle in water, 1 tablespoon at a time, mixing until all flour is moistened.
Gather dough into ball, handling as little as necessary.
Set
aside.

title: vintage smokies
directions: Mix jelly, barbecue sauce, and red wine vinegar.
Add Bryan Smokies and heat in a crockpot until hot.
Serve from chafing dish or crockpot.

title: divinity candy
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water together in saucepan.
Cook on low heat until it boils. Boil until it spins a thread when dropped from spoon.

title: country club onion rings
directions: Put fresh nut meats into clean, heatproof jars.
Put on caps, screwing the bands tight.
Process in the oven, using lowest possible heat (225°), for 45 minutes for any size jars.

title: chili
directions: Rub skillet with garlic powder.
Add oil and heat.
Add peppers and onion.
Do not brown.
Add meat and brown.
Add chili pepper and mix well.
Add tomatoes, beans and water.
Season with salt. Cover and let simmer gently 30 to 40 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: Mix salt, flour and cream of tartar together.
Add water, oil and food coloring.
Cook 3 minutes on medium heat or until mixture pulls away from sides of pan.
Knead immediately and store in airtight container.

title: garlic mashed potatoes
directions: Peel and cut potatoes into about 5 chunks.
Cover potatoes and garlic that have been peeled, with water.
Bring to a boil and cook about 20 minutes until very tender.
Drain, leaving a little potato water in the pan.
Using a potato masher, blend in butter, sour cream and salt.
Add a little more hot water, if necessary. Pile into a buttered shallow casserole dish and top with cheese. Serve immediately or re-warm in a low oven at serving time.

title: steak dijonnaise
directions: Prepare 24 hours in advance.
Combine all ingredients except steak and oil and mix with wooden spoon until dissolved.
Gradually add the oil, stirring constantly.
Put marinade in shallow container and settle steak into container, stirring twice to coat thoroughly.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Turn steak occasionally.
Remove and grill.

title: vegetable-cheese casserole
directions: Mix first six ingredients and put cracker crumbs on top.
Drip some margarine over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sweetheart salad
directions: Heat pineapple with sugar.
Add gelatine, which has been softened in 1/4 cup cold water.
Stir until melted.
Add lemon and cherry juices and cool.
Mix chopped cherries with cream cheese. Add to pineapple mixture.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Whip cream and blend with pineapple mixture.
Mold and chill.
Nuts may be added to cherries and cream cheese, if desired.

title: cajun chicken
directions: Melt margarine with oil in shallow pan in oven 5 minutes.
Coat chicken with flour and salt in bag.
Bake chicken at 325° for 25-30 minutes single layer.
While cooking combine oregano, thyme, basil, salt, paprika, peppers.
Saute in large fry-pan garlic, onion, celery, green pepper, tomato until soft.
Mix seasonings, simmer about 1 minute.
Mix in broth the tomato sauce.
Bring to boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Lower heat and add chicken breasts and potatoes. Cook until potatoes are soft and chicken is done.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add chopped vegetables.
Cook over medium heat until melted.
Add tomatoes; simmer for 15 minutes. Add shrimp and dry ingredients; simmer and cook for 15 minutes. Serve over rice with French bread and butter.

title: cheesy corn spoon bread
directions: Saut butter and onion until tender.
Set aside.
In a bowl, beat eggs; add sour cream, both cans of corn, salt and pepper. Stir in corn bread mix just until blended.
Fold in sauteed onion, jalapeno and 1 1/2 cups of cheese.
Transfer to a greased shallow 3-quart baking dish.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Cool slightly.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: butterscotch slices(cookies)
directions: Place first 4 ingredients in mixing bowl; mix thoroughly.
Add nuts and mix.
Sift flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Divide into two portions.
Add first portion to shortening.
Mix well, then add the second portion.
Knead dough with hands until smooth. Pack firmly in two rolls.
Place in refrigerator.
Chill until firm.
Slice and bake for 6 to 8 minutes.
Makes 60 cookies.

title: pink fluff
directions: Combine condensed milk and pie filling with a spoon.
Fold in tidbits and Cool Whip.
Place in glass bowl to serve and chill for at least 2 hours.
This is a wonderful holiday dish.

title: dried beef log
directions: Mix with a little dried beef the remaining ingredients. Spread mixture on middle of dried beef; roll and refrigerate overnight or 24 hours.

title: chocolate hot water cake
directions: Beat the sugar, shortening, cocoa, eggs and salt.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chocolate pudding for pie
directions: Combine cornstarch, salt and sugar.
Gradually add milk; add golden syrup and chocolate.
Heat to boiling over direct heat and then boil gently for 1 1/2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add vanilla and butter.
Pour into baked pie shell or pudding dishes.

title: aunt betty's mississippi mud
directions: Mix together.
Press on bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Let cool.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: In medium saucepan, combine water and sugar; bring to a boil over medium heat.
Add cranberries, apples, vinegar, raisins and spices.
(If wish, add celery, nuts and onion salt.)
Bring to boil, then simmer gently 10 minutes, stirring often.
Pour into mixing bowl. Place plastic wrap directly on surface of sauce. Refrigerate.
Bring to room temperature before serving or put in small canning jars.

title: chocolate cake
directions: In large mixer bowl, combine butter, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Beat on high speed 3 minutes.
Very important.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately with water to creamed mixture.
Blend just until combined.
Pour into pans.
Bake at 350° in greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chocolate eclair bars
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with graham crackers.
Beat pudding with milk well.
Add Cool Whip.
Spread 1/2 of mixture on layer of crackers.
Add another layer of crackers, rest of mixture and another layer of crackers.
Top this layer with a thin layer of chocolate frosting.
Refrigerate at least 10 hours or make day before.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine spinach, cream cheese, butter, onion and pepper. Place in casserole dish in alternating layers with artichoke hearts, starting and ending with a layer of spinach. Top with cheeses. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Put chicken in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex oblong baking dish. Sprinkle with black pepper and very little salt.
Mix can of soup with can of water and add can of Ro-Tel.
Mix well, then add rice to mixture and mix.
Pour over chicken pieces; sprinkle dry onion soup mix over rice and add a few teaspoons of water to cover dry onion soup mix (about 1/2 to 3/4 cup of water).
Cover baking dish with foil or tight lid and bake in 400° oven for 1 1/2 hours. Ready to serve.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Grease pie pan.
Beat mixture until smooth.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes at 350°.

title: dog biscuits(bulldog biscuits)
directions: Combine all dry ingredients (except yeast) in a large bowl. Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup broth or water and add to remaining broth.
Add liquid to dry ingredients.
Knead 3 minutes.
(Dough will be stiff.
If too stiff, add 1 egg.)
Roll out on floured board 1/4-inch thick.
Cut in shapes and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Brush with egg and milk mixture.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.
Turn oven off and leave overnight or until bone hard.

title: broccoli casserole(microwave)
directions: Cook noodles to specifications on box.
Drain while preparing broccoli.
Cook broccoli and butter for 10 minutes on High in microwave.
Add 2/3 cup water to gravy mixture and cook on medium on stove top until it thickens.
Mix broccoli, noodles, gravy and Cheddar cheese all together.
Cook 7 more minutes in the microwave.

title: patties
directions: Shape into patties and fry.
Top with spaghetti sauce and Mozzarella cheese or mushroom soup and Cheddar cheese.
Bake in baking dish at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Cook diced potatoes and onions in chicken broth until tender. Add milk and butter.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.

title: green bean provincial
directions: Cook beans in a small amount of water until just tender. In saucepan, add ham, garlic, and butter. Cook until garlic is soft. Stir in beans, salt and pepper. Top with tomato wedges. Cover and heat through.

title: pink delight
directions: Mix condensed milk and cream cheese together.
Add strawberry Jell-O, Cool Whip and crushed pineapple.
Mix with electric mixer and chill 2 hours.

title: mushroom and rice casserole
directions: Cook onions, celery and pepper in butter until tender. Mix all ingredients and put into 9 x 13-inch dish. Will be very soupy. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sherry cake
directions: *Taylor New York state golden sherry in Giant Food.

title: dill-lemon rice mix(serve this as a side dish with fresh trout)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir until evenly distributed.
Put about 1 1/2 cups mixture each into three 1-pint airtight containers.
Label.
Store in a cool, dry place.
Use within 6 to 8 months.
Makes about 4 1/2 cups of Dill-Lemon Rice Mix.

title: coconut puffs
directions: Chill bowl and beaters.
Beat egg whites with salt and cream of tartar until foamy; gradually add sugar and almond extract (or flavoring).
Beat until stiff peaks form.
Fold in coconut, oats and pecans.
Drop by teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix together the cake mix, oil and 1 egg until crumbly.
Reserve about 3/4 cup of mixture and press the rest into the bottom of the pan. Bake for 15 minutes.

Immediately spread with the 1 egg, 1/3 cup sugar, cream cheese (all beaten together) and chocolate chips. Sprinkle reserved crumb mixture over top and bake 15 more minutes. Cover with foil while still warm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cut onion in small pieces.
Fry in margarine until soft.
Add flour, salt, milk and pepper to make a cream sauce.
Add egg yolk and cheese.
Add cooked and drained broccoli.
Put in casserole and sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: fish with green peppers and tomatoes(serves 6)
directions: Wash fish well under cold running water; dry well.
Heat oil over moderate heat in a large, heavy skillet.
Add fish; saute until golden brown on both sides.
Transfer to a plate and set aside.
Add onions to skillet and saute until soft, but not brown. Stir often.
Add green peppers and saute until soft.
Add garlic and more oil if needed and saute for about another minute. Dissolve tomato paste in water.
Add parsley and tomatoes, salt and pepper to skillet and bring to boil.
Reduce heat to low; cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add fish to skillet; baste thoroughly with sauce.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Serve cold with a crusty type bread.

title: granny's popovers
directions: Beat eggs lightly with fork; add milk, flour and salt, mixing with a fork.
Don't worry about the lumps.
Spoon into 6 well-greased muffin cups, filling them 3/4 full.
Place in cold oven and turn heat on to 450°.
(Must be placed in cold oven.) Bake 40 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: lemon lush
directions: Grease 9 x 14-inch dish or pan.
Mix flour, oleo, sugar and nuts.
Spread in pan (you may have to work with this a while) and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Mix cream cheese, confectioners sugar and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread over cool crust. Mix 2 packages pudding and milk.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Cover and refrigerate. (Chocolate or Butterscotch pudding may be substituted.
Lite oleo, Cool Whip and cream cheese may be used.)

title: orange muffins
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, sugar, cinnamon, allspice and raisins in a large mixing bowl.
Make a well in the center of mixture.
Combine egg and remaining ingredients.
Add to dry mixture, stirring just until moistened.

title: enchiladas(makes 10; microwave)
directions: Heat chili, soften tortillas so you can roll them without cracking.
Fill each tortilla with chili, onion and cheese.
Roll and place in 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Pour remaining chili over top of tortillas.
Top with cheese and some of the onion. Bake in microwave for 5 minutes.

title: turkey spaghetti
directions: Heat margarine in large skillet on medium heat. Add chopped or ground turkey breast. Cook about 5 minutes. Add garlic, onion and bell pepper. Cook 5 minutes. Add salt, pepper and tomatoes. Cook slowly on low heat about 20 minutes. Serve over spaghetti. Makes 6 servings.

title: all-american succotash chili
directions: About 45 minutes before serving, in a 12-inch skillet, over high heat, cook meat and onion, stirring frequently, until all pan juices evaporate and meat is well browned.
Stir in chili powder and salt. Cook 1 minute. Stir in tomatoes in puree, lima beans, corn, green chilies with their liquid, brown sugar, vinegar and 1/2 cup water.
Over high heat, heat to boiling. Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Skim fat from chili, if any. Serve with corn chips, if you like.
Makes 8 servings.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Bring all ingredients to boil.
Simmer 4 to 6 hours.

title: stuffed cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage a few minutes in salted water to soften; drain. Mix 2 tablespoons soup or juice with rest of ingredients.
Place mixture inside of cabbage and roll up.
Place rolls seam side down; pour on juice.
Cover; simmer 40 minutes.

title: pork chop skillet supper
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil; add chops and pan braise, turning chops so that both sides are lightly browned.
Cook until done.
Pare and slice potatoes.
When chops are done, add potatoes over the top of the chops.
Sprinkle on the green peppers.
Pour in the tomatoes.
The lemon slices go on top of all other ingredients.
If necessary, add a little water to cover potatoes. Cover skillet and simmer until vegetables are tender.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: strawberry shortcake
directions: Beat above ingredients, except egg, for 2 minutes.
Add unbeaten egg.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: marinated cabbage slaw
directions: Grate cabbage. Add green pepper and onions. Mix well with sugar. Bring to boil the salad oil, vinegar, celery seed and salt. Pour over cabbage and mix well. Put in tight container and store in refrigerator overnight before serving. Will keep for 30 days. Serves 20.

title: chocolate mocha pie
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Combine cocoa, coffee, salt, white sugar and milk.
Bring to a boil; stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin.
Cool until slightly thickened.
Beat whipping cream; add vanilla.
Fold in cooked mixture.
Pour into pie shell and top with nuts or whipped cream.
Makes one pie.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat together the 2 eggs; add the water, sugar, syrup, melted butter and vanilla.
Stir thoroughly.
Add pecans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Mix all the juices together with the sugar. Stir until sugar dissolves. Add the ginger ale and club soda just before serving. Makes 50 cups.
May add vodka or rum, if desired.

title: goulash
directions: Cook macaroni in salted water 7 minutes; drain.
In a large casserole dish, place tomatoes, salt and macaroni.
Cook onion, green pepper and ground chuck until meat is lightly browned.
Add to casserole with a large can of tomato sauce.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 8.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown the ground beef, then drain well.
Add the pepper and onion and saute with the meat.
Add the rest of the ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: brownie cheesecake bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
In a mixing bowl, beat flour, sugar, melted margarine, cocoa, 2 eggs, milk, 2 teaspoons vanilla and baking powder until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in pan.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Cover cucumbers with vinegar, allspice, salt and alum.
Soak for 6 weeks, then drain and add 5 pounds sugar.
Cover and keep in a dark place.
Use as needed.

title: italian vegetable dip
directions: Mix mayonnaise, sour cream and Zesty Italian salad dressing mix until well blended; stir in peppers.
Refrigerate.
Serve with bread sticks, vegetable dippers or chips.
Makes 2 1/4 cups.

title: butterfinger dessert
directions: Mix melted butter and cracker crumbs.
Reserve 2/3 cup. Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate.
Prepare pudding according to package instructions, except use only 2 cups of milk. Blend in softened ice cream.
Spread over crust and refrigerate until set.
Spread whipped topping over top of pudding mixture. Top with crushed candy bars and reserved cracker crumbs.
Serves 12.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Beat egg whites to make meringue and set aside.
Mix all other ingredients and cook in saucepan until thick.
Pour into baked pie shells and top with meringue.
Place in oven long enough to brown top of meringue.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Combine all ingredients except cheese and chilies; pour half of mix in greased baking pan.
Spread 1 cup of cheese on top. Spread 1 layer of chilies on cheese.
Spread remaining cheese over chilies.
Cover with remaining batter.
Bake at 450° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: pineapple chiffon pie
directions: In a saucepan, bring to boil the crushed pineapple.
Stir in lemon Jell-O until dissolved, then mix in sugar.
In another bowl, whip chilled evaporated milk with lemon juice.
Mix this into pineapple mixture.
Pile into pie shell and refrigerate at least one hour.
Garnish with shaved chocolate.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add water and cook until thick.
Add jello and food coloring.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Bake pie shell.
Place strawberries in pie shell. Pour mixture over berries.
Place pie in refrigerator to cool.
Serve with Cool Whip, if desired.
Makes 1 pie.

title: quick spicy chili
directions: Saute turkey meat and minced garlic until all the pink disappears in a nonstick frying pan sprayed with nonfat cooking spray.
Add the remaining ingredients and simmer about 30 minutes. This is quick and good.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.
Fat: 1.03 grams.
Calories per serving: 243.
Sodium: 389.

title: the ultimate pasta salad
directions: Add any of the vegetables or anything else that suits your fancy. Watch proportions as this can get out of hand!!!

title: persimmon pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Cream sugar, eggs, soda, salt and all flavorings.
Gradually add flour and milk.
Add pulp.
Add butter.
Pour into a well-greased pan.
Place in oven.
Bake for 70 minutes.

title: chicken chili
directions: Boil chicken with 2 teaspoons salt and 2 teaspoons pepper. Debone.
Make sauce of milk, tomato sauce, cheese and green chilies.
Add onion to sauce.

title: idiot rolls
directions: Mix eggs, cold water and sugar in large bowl.
In a small bowl, mix Crisco, margarine and boiling water.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Mix all together in large bowl.
Add flour and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate.
Let stand overnight.

title: date-pecan candy
directions: Beat until thick.
Roll into small balls and dip in white chocolate.

title: baked onion casserole
directions: Melt 1/2 cup butter in pan.
Add onions and saute until tender.
Transfer to baking dish.
Combine soup, milk, salt and pepper and pour over onions.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Dip bread slices in melted butter and arrange on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apple cinnamon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend together the cake mix, pie filling and eggs in a large bowl.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
(Combine the sugar and cinnamon.)
Spread half of cake batter in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle with half of cinnamon and sugar.
Repeat with remaining batter.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes.

title: southern barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all the ingredients and simmer in a heavy pan 2 hours, uncovered.	Stir
often
to prevent burning.
Watch the liquid content does not
evaporate,
you may need to add a bit of water. Makes 1 quart.

title: lemon tea cookies
directions: In medium bowl, stir together all ingredients (with spoon) until well blended.
Drop by level tablespoons onto cookie sheet. Sprinkle each cookie lightly with sugar and nutmeg.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes, until lightly brown.
These are tangy cake-type cookies.
Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix
all
ingredients together.
Makes 20 hush puppies. Cook at 375° until done.

title: cornlight bread
directions: Mix well and bake in food pan.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange apples in well-greased 8 x 10-inch baking dish. Blend remaining ingredients and spread over the apples.
Add 1/4 cup water.
Bake 45 minutes until apples are done and top is crisp.
Serve with sweetened whipped cream.

title: zucchini torte
directions: Mix together.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: buffalo chip cookies(serves one herd)
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients and add eggs and vanilla. Sift together flour, baking powder and soda and add.
Add remainder of ingredients.
Refrigerate dough at least one hour.
Place large balls on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 350°.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs and sugar gradually until creamy.
Add oil and beat.
Add flour, soda and cinnamon.
Stir in grated carrots, nuts, pineapple and vanilla.
Pour in tube pan (ungreased).
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Do not turn pan upside down until it cools or it will break apart.
Good plain or with cream cheese icing.

title: pralines
directions: Mix all ingredients except vanilla well.
Cook on low fire and simmer.
Let cook until forms soft ball in water.
Add the vanilla. Remove from fire.
Cool.
Beat until begins to lose glaze.
Drop by spoon on wax paper.

title: chili con queso soup
directions: Cook onion in butter until softened.
Add chiles and tomatoes. Cook 8 to 10 minutes until liquid evaporates.
Stir in cream cheese.
Stir in chicken broth, half and half, lemon juice, cayenne and salt.
Heat until warm.
Sprinkle with tortilla strips, onions and Jack cheese over individual servings.
Makes 8 cups.

title: cherry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water.
Add to the pie filling and pineapple.
Mix together and chill.

title: potato and onion soup
directions: Peel and dice potatoes and onions.
Cover with water and cook until soft.
Put in chicken bouillon, adding water if it gets low.
Watch so it doesn't stick.
Add parsley, salt and pepper. Add milk and butter.
Let simmer.
Can be made ahead and frozen. Reheat very slowly.

title: country style steak
directions: Salt and pepper steak. Flour

steak and fry in hot skillet, browning both sides. Remove steak from pan and add small amount of flour to hot oil. Stir. Continue to add flour and cook until golden brown. Add water and stir until comes to boil. Add small amounts of water and stir until gravy is thickness you desire. Place steak in covered dish and cover with gravy. Place in 250° oven and cook until tender (1 hour or more, depending on amount you cook).

title: refrigerator potato rolls
directions: Prepare mashed potatoes according to package directions.
In large mixing bowl, stir together 2 cups flour and yeast.
In saucepan, heat milk, butter, sugar and salt until just warm, stirring constantly to melt butter.
Stir in potatoes.
Add to dry mixture.
Add eggs.
Beat at low speed of mixer for 1/2 minute, then beat at high speed for 3 minutes.
By hand, stir in enough of remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Place in greased bowl, turning once to grease surface.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours or up to one week.

title: peach dumplings
directions: Mix brown sugar, spices, 2/3 cup water, dash of salt and lemon juice in bowl and set aside.
Mix 3/4 teaspoon salt and next 2 ingredients. Cut in shortening.
Add 1/3 cup milk and stir with fork until dry ingredients are moistened.
Roll out on lightly floured board to form a 12-inch square.
Cut in 4 smaller squares. Put a peach half or quarter in center of each square.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar and dot with butter.
Moisten edges of pastry squares and fold corners over fruit.
Brush with milk.
Put in shallow baking dish and pour remaining brown sugar syrup around dumplings.
Bake in a very hot oven (450°) for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 375° and bake about 30 minutes longer.
Serve warm with cream.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Cut out center of bread and use as bowl for dip.
Break up bread center into pieces and eat with dip.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix together and bake in a loaf pan at 400° for 1 hour. (I pour tomato juice over top before baking.)

title: aunt mamie's pork and bean casserole
directions: After browning meat, add onion and cook until onions are soft. Drain any fat.
Add all ingredients to crock-pot and cook at least 1/2 hour on medium setting.

title: ice cream cocoa roll
directions: Grease 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan; line with wax paper; grease again.
Beat eggs with vanilla until thick and lemon colored.
Beat in sugar until mixture is thick and fluffy.
Sift remaining ingredients over egg mixture and fold in carefully.
Spread batter in pan.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Invert immediately on towel which has been dusted with powdered sugar.
Remove wax paper and roll end to end, towel and all.
Cool, unroll, remove from towel and spread with softened ice cream (your choice).
Re-roll, wrap in foil or plastic wrap and freeze.

title: chicken oahu
directions: Combine stuffing cubes, undrained pineapple and 1/4 cup water.
Put in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
In bag combine flour, salt, paprika and dash of pepper.
Add chicken a few pieces at a time, shake to coat.
In skillet, brown chicken in hot oil. Place atop stuffing.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: italian salad of mozzarella, avocado & tomato
directions: Halve the avocado and remove the stone. Peel off the skin and slice the flesh thinly. Place in a bowl and sprinkle with the lemon juice.

title: under sea salad
directions: Heat juice until it comes to a boil.
Add marshmallows.
Stir until dissolved.
Mix pecans into softened cheese, then add to juice mixture and fold in whipping cream.
Pour in long Pyrex and let set overnight in refrigerator.
Pour lime jello on top and chill.

title: fudge nut squares
directions: Melt margarine and chocolate.
Beat in sugar gradually.
Add eggs, beating constantly, one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour together with salt and fold into chocolate mixture (use low speed on mixer).
Add nuts and bake in 9 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut in squares when cool.

title: layer taco dip
directions: Use a 9 x 11-inch pan.
Cook hamburger; drain.
Add taco mix made by directions on package.
Layer ingredients in the following order:
jalapeno bean dip, sour cream, taco sauce (poured over sour cream), taco meat (spread), chopped lettuce and Cheddar cheese.
Place chopped tomatoes on top.
Serve with taco chips.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift flour and sugar together; cut in shortening to resemble coarse cornmeal.
Add soda to buttermilk; add to flour mixture. Beat until smooth.
Store in refrigerator or use immediately.
Roll and cut like Parker House rolls with melted oleo on top and on fold.
Bake at 400° until brown.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: low-fat crepes
directions: Beat eggs and blend with other ingredients until batter is smooth and thick enough to coat a spoon.
Cover and let stand 30 minutes.
Heat a 5 or 6-inch crepe pan.
Oil lightly and pour in just enough batter to form a very thin layer.
Tilt pan so batter spreads evenly.
Cook on one side, turn and brown on other side. Stack with waxed paper.

title: greek sauce
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 3 hours.
Add water as needed.

title: chicken and cheese
directions: Cube chicken and cook in frypan.
Mix with shredded cheese, onion, salt and pepper.
Put a little mixture in each roll.
Roll up and cook at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes in casserole dish with milk and soup poured over top.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over top, too.

title: banana pudding
directions: Prepare pudding by directions.
Crumble vanilla wafers into fine crumbs.
Add sweetened condensed milk to pudding mix using a large bowl.
Place a thin layer of crumbs on bottom; cover crumbs with pudding mix.
Place layer of bananas on top.
Cover with Cool Whip.
Continue alternating layers until ingredients are all used. Refrigerate overnight.

title: lori's salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate. This is fast and good.

title: pound cake
directions: Mix together.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken green noodle casserole
directions: Stew hen.
Reserve stock.
Cut chicken into bite-size pieces. Saut pepper, onion and celery in margarine.
Add mushrooms and chicken.
Boil noodles in reserved stock; drain well.
Combine with chicken mixture and pour into 2-quart casserole.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until well heated.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Chop squash and onion. Boil in water until onion is clear. Drain off water. Fry sausage and beef until browned.
Drain off fat. Combine zucchini mixture with meat, seasoning, salt and tomato sauce.
Place mixture in a baking dish.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs and cheese on top.
Bake at 357° until brown (approximately 45 minutes).

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into two 9-inch greased pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Makes its own crust.

title: prehistoric pudding
directions: You will need 8 to 10 paper or plastic cups and prehistoric decorations.

title: lynda's pineapple and coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix sugar with flour and eggs.
Add melted butter, coconut and pineapple.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: melva's tarter sauce for fish
directions: Grind onion and pickle in food processor.
Stir pickle and onion into salad dressing.
Spice sauce with the spices. Refrigerate for 1 hour or more.

title: oatmeal spice cake
directions: Combine oats and raisins.
Pour boiling water over oats and raisins; set aside.
Sift flour with baking soda and spices. Cream butter with sugar, beating until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until blended.
Add flour mixture alternately with oats and raisins (not drained), beginning and ending with the dry ingredients.
Blend well.
Turn into greased 8 x 12-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: chicken and dressing
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Let cool and remove chicken from bone, reserving broth for dressing.
Saute onions and celery in margarine until tender.
In a large mixing bowl, crumble cornbread; add broth, chicken, bread and milk.
Mix well.
Add onions, celery, sage, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well.
Bake in roasting pan at 350° until lightly browned.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Dissolve cream of tartar, baking soda, salt, ginger, cinnamon and cloves in coffee.
Add all ingredients to coffee mixture.
If dough is not stiff enough add more flour.
Roll out and cut cookies out.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fudge cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar
and
vanilla; add eggs.
Mix well. Melt chocolate squares (need
not
cool before mixing) but add gradually and keep	stirring constantly.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Add
to
creamed
mixture alternately with the water.
Bake in 3 cake pans at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Place butter in a 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Add blueberries, pineapple and nuts.
Combine flour, sugar and milk in a large bowl, mix until smooth.
Pour batter over fruit.
Bake at 375° until golden brown, approximately 35 minutes.

title: cheese krinkles
directions: Combine cheese and butter.
Blend well and add flour, salt and Rice Krispies.
Stir gently.
Shape into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Flatten with fork dipped in flour. Bake at 400 degrees for 10 minutes or until slightly brown. Rewarm -- serve warm or cold -- can be frozen.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Cream together margarine, butter and cream cheese (must be at room temperature).
Add sugar, then eggs, one at a time.
Fold in flour and then vanilla.
Pour batter into a greased, floured angel food cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes to 1 hour and 45 minutes.

title: sliced baked potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes if skin is tough, otherwise scrub and rinse. Cut into thin slices, but not all the way through.
Place potatoes in baking dish and fan then slightly.
Sprinkle with salt and drizzle with butter and herbs.
Bake for 50 minutes at 425°. Remove from oven; sprinkle with cheeses.
Bake potatoes for 10 more minutes or until lightly brown.

title: homemade chocolate sauce
directions: In saucepan, mix sugar, cocoa and salt; add water.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Cover and store in refrigerator.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Combine the ingredients and let stand, refrigerated, for 24 hours.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute onion, celery, bell pepper and green onions in margarine.
Add tomatoes, water and garlic.
Season to taste.
Add hot sauce.
Simmer for about 30 minutes.

title: double corn chowder
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine milk, cream-style corn, corn kernels, peas, Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, until vegetables are crisp-tender, about 5 minutes.

title: boston-style beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 6 servings.

title: carrots with lup cheong
directions: Put everything into pot with water.
Cook for 25 minutes, until carrots are cooked.

title: caramel corn
directions: Keep
corn
warm in a 300° oven.
Melt margarine.
Stir in brown
sugar,
syrup
and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil without stirring for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat;
stir in soda and vanilla.
Pour over corn and mix well. Bake
at
for
1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool. Store in an airtight container.

title: basic meat loaf
directions: Combine ground beef, 1/2 cup tomato sauce and the next 5 ingredients; mix well.
Shape meat mixture into a loaf.
Place on rack of a lightly greased broiler pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Combine remaining tomato sauce and the last 2 ingredients; stir well.
Pour over meat loaf; bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: johnny's favorite pumpkin chocolate chip cookie
directions: Cream together the sugars, butter, eggs, vanilla and pumpkin. Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.
Mix both mixtures together gently.
Drop by teaspoon onto a greased cookie sheet and bake for 12 to 15 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: butter crunch lemon chiffon pie
directions: Heat oven
to
Mix
all
and
spread in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake
minutes,
stirring occasionally.
Take from oven and stir to make crumbs.
Save 1/2 cup for topping. Immediately press
rest of mixture against sides and bottom of 9-inch pie pan. Cool.

title: easy peroshki
directions: Grate 1/2 onion into ground meat.
Brown meat mixture until cooked.
Dice other half of onion in oil, saute and set aside.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook onion and squash 3 minutes in microwave.
Stir, cook another 2 minutes, drain.
Combine soup, sour cream and carrots. Spread 1/2 of dry stuffing mix in bottom of dish.
Add squash/onion to soup mixture.
Put in dish.
Top with rest of stuffing mix.
Drizzle melted butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hot sausage puffs
directions: Remove sausage from casings; cook meat in large skillet until browned.
Drain fat.
Spoon sausage into large bowl and let cool. Add cheese, Bisquick and water, mix well.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls; place on a large cookie sheet 2 inches apart and bake in 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes or until puffed and browned.
Makes about 75 puffs.

title: baked cheese eggplant
directions: Combine bread crumbs, flour and salt.
