Peel and slice eggplant. Dip eggplant in milk, then in the bread crumb mixture, coating each slice well.
Melt half the butter or margarine in a skillet. Fry the eggplant in butter until brown on both sides, adding more butter or margarine as necessary.
Add the cheeses to the beaten egg.
Place a layer of eggplant in a buttered baking dish. Spread the cheese egg mixture on it and cover with remaining eggplant.
Bake in a 375° oven for 20 minutes. Serves 3.

title: beet salad
directions: Mix vinegar and sugar together until dissolved.
Pour over onion and beets.
Refrigerate until chilled.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls on cookie sheet.
Flatten to cover entire sheet.
Bake according to package directions.
Cool.

title: fish with sour cream and parmesan cheese
directions: Rinse fish under cold water and pat dry.
Lay fish in greased baking dish and sprinkle with lemon juice. Mix sour cream and cheese together and spread evenly over fish.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes, then brown under broiler.

title: peanut butter ice cream sauce
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and cook for minute or until sugar dissolves.
Remove from heat and add peanut butter.
Beat until smooth.
Serve warm.

title: goulash
directions: Boil macaroni until done.
Cut or dice onions.
Fry in a little butter.
Put hamburger in with onions, then add tomatoes.
Let simmer until macaroni is done.
Then strain macaroni.
Put in large bowl.
Add onions, hamburger and tomatoes from frying pan.
Stir all together.
Salt to taste.

title: company vegetable casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine corn, green beans, soup, cheese, sour cream, celery, onion and green pepper in greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes.
Blend cracker crumbs and butter; sprinkle over casserole.
Bake an additional 10 minutes. Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: mousse au chocolat(chocolate mousse)
directions: Melt the chocolate in the top of a double boiler.
Allow to cool slightly.
Separate the egg whites from the yolks.
Whip the yolks and powdered sugar.
In another bowl, whip the egg whites to stiff peaks.
Mix the slightly cooled chocolate and the sugared egg yolks.
Gently fold the chocolate mixture into the egg whites. Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.

title: jello ice cream
directions: Boil sugar and water for 2 minutes.
Dissolve strawberry Jell-O in hot mixture.
Add lemon juice and grated orange rind. Freeze until partly frozen; beat until fluffy.
Blend well.
Place in freezer.
Freeze 1/2 hour.
Beat again and freeze.

title: buttermilk salad or "julie's pink pouf"
directions: Bring pineapple to a boil.
Add jello, then let cool.
Mix together buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Add nuts.
Mix all together and chill until congealed.

title: fruit soup
directions: Bring first 5 ingredients to a boil.
Add next 2 ingredients, and cook 2 minutes.
Add frozen concentrate and peaches.
Chill. Garnish with fresh fruit (kiwi, bananas, strawberries, blueberries, sprinkle of coconut).

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute oleo and celery in pan. Mix all ingredients in casserole dish and bake at 350°, covered, for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: kayre's tomato jam
directions: Scald tomatoes in boiling water; cover and let stand 2 minutes.
Drain.
Peel and slice tomatoes.
Put in a kettle with the sugar and finely sliced lemon.
Cook until thick and clear, about 20 minutes.
Stir to prevent sticking.
Do not cook too thick.
Put in sterilized jars and seal, if you wish.
Makes about 2 pints.
Absolutely delicious!

title: microwave peach pie
directions: While peeling and slicing peaches, put one crust in a 9 inch microwavable pie plate and the other one on wax paper to thaw. Prick holes in pie crust in pan with a fork and microwave on 70% power for 7 minutes.
Cut remaining pie crust into strips to place crisscrossed on pie.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except the shrimp, until mixture is smooth and creamy, then fold in the shrimp.
Serve with corn chips, potato chips, pretzels or crackers.

title: earthquake cake
directions: In oblong 9 x 13-inch pan spread pecans in bottom.
Top with shredded coconut.
Mix cake mix according to package directions. Put this on top of coconut.
Melt margarine.
Add cream cheese. Add powdered sugar.
Pour this on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: frosty fruit cooler
directions: In a punch bowl or large 2-quart container, combine first 3 ingredients.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Float scoops of sherbet on top.
Serve immediately.

title: orange chicken
directions: Mix together ingredients and paint on the chicken.
Bake for one hour at 350 degrees; then 15 minutes at 400 degrees.

title: mother's ham loaf(servings:  12)
directions: Mix the above.
Spray pans.
Put in two large loaf pans.
Pour sauce on top and periodically during baking; drain any liquid from meat and add additional sauce.

title: chicken cheese dip
directions: Heat cheese (cut up in chunks) until melted. Add all ingredients and mix. Serve warm with your favorite chips.

title: impossible turkey and stuffing pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate (9 x 1 1/4-inches). Arrange turkey in plate; sprinkle with seasoned salt.
Separate stuffing into small pieces and arrange on turkey.
Top with onions and peas.

title: eclair pie
directions: Place whole graham crackers in bottom of a 9 1/2 x 12 1/2-inch dish.
Pour pudding (prepared according to package directions) over crackers.
Top pudding with a layer of graham crackers.
Heat frosting in microwave until pourable.
Pour over 2nd layer of crackers.
Refrigerate overnight and serve.

title: gateway salad
directions: Stir pineapple and pudding mix together in a large bowl, then add all other ingredients.
Chill about 30 minutes to an hour.

title: buttery peanut brittle
directions: Heat and stir first 3 ingredients until sugar dissolves.
Add butter.
Stir often after 230°.
Add peanuts at 280° and stir constantly to 305°.
Remove from heat.
Quickly stir in soda, mixing well.
Pour onto 2 buttered cookie sheets.
Stretch thin by lifting and pulling edges with forks.
Loosen from pans as soon as possible.
Break up.

title: cheesecake walnut bars
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Line bottom and sides of 13 x 9-inch pie pan with foil; butter foil.
Combine cookie crumbs, 1/2 cup walnuts and butter; press firmly into bottom of pan.
Bake until golden 5 to 6 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool slightly.
Beat cream cheese, sugar and flour until smooth.
Beat in eggs, heavy cream and vanilla until well blended.
Spread evenly on baked crust. Bake until cheese is almost firm, 25 to 30 minutes.
Turn oven off. Leave cake in oven with door ajar about 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining nuts, pressing lightly with spatula.
Cool; cover and refrigerate.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Heat milk; add candy bar.
Mix well.

title: instant russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients well and store in covered jar.

title: mexican salad
directions: Mix softened cream cheese with 1/2 package taco seasoning mix. Spread mixture in a round pizza pan.
Spread jalapeno relish on cream cheese.
Sprinkle on lettuce, tomatoes, cheese and olives. Serve with tortilla chips.
Enjoy!

title: no name dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan. Refrigerate or freeze for 1 to 2 hours.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill!

title: curried almonds
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. In 8 or 9-inch cake pan, combine almonds and melted butter. Toast in oven 30 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add curry powder and salt; toss until thoroughly coated. Transfer to waxed paper to cool.
Store almonds in tightly covered container.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Combine sugar and milk in a heavy saucepan.
Cook to 238° on a candy thermometer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and Marshmallow Creme; stir until smooth.
Spread into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool and cut into squares. Makes 64.

title: supper skillet
directions: In large skillet cook turkey in margarine until lightly browned; stirring to keep crumbly.
Stir in onions, green peppers and mushrooms. Arrange uncooked noodles over mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese, salt and pepper.
Pour tomatoes over all; do not stir.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 20 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: darby's green sweet salad
directions: Mix Cool Whip and pistachio pudding together in a bowl (the Cool Whip will turn green).
Pour in the fruit cocktail.
Slice the bananas last and add to mix.
Add chopped pecans or other nuts, if desired.
Keep cold.

title: honey bun cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Pour 1/2 of batter into a greased long pan.
Mix brown sugar, cinnamon and raisins together. Pour over first half of batter.
Swirl into batter with knife. Pour in rest of batter and swirl with knife again.
Bake 45 minutes at 300°.

title: sparkling harvest cider
directions: In punch bowl, combine first 3 ingredients and stir until sugar dissolves.
Chill.
Just before serving, add ginger ale. Serve over ice.
Makes about 3 quarts.

title: hamburger pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400° or if using metal pan heat to 425°.
Cut Crisco into flour, mixing in onion salt and water and work until like pie crust.
Divide dough in half.
Roll out and put half of crust in pie can.

title: shrimp gumbo
directions: Heat butter in a saucepan; add onion, green pepper and celery. Cover 10 minutes or until soft and lightly browned.
Add okra, tomatoes, parsley, bay leaf, stock and shrimp.
If canned shrimp is used, add 5 minutes before cooking is finished.
Cover and simmer gently, about 20 minutes.
Season to taste.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.
Serve with rice.

title: strawberry punch
directions: Mix in blender until smooth. Add 2 liters of ginger ale, Sprite or 7-Up. Keep all ingredients cold if you are serving immediately upon mixing.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Melt margarine.
Add ingredients and stir well.
Pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until brown.
Use big pie pan.

title: memorable meatballs
directions: Mix thoroughly all ingredients except shortening, soup and water.
Shape firmly into 16 meatballs.
In skillet, brown meatballs in shortening; pour off fat.
Stir in soup and water. Cover; cook over low heat 20 minutes or until done.
Stir occasionally.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook in large iron skillet at 350° until done (about 30 or 40 minutes).

title: chicken or turkey casserole
directions: Combine and put in baking dish.
Cover with grated cheese. Cover cheese with crackers or potato chips.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: pecan cookies(ciastka kurche-polish)
directions: Cream butter with vanilla.
Add sugar gradually, beating until fluffy.
Add water and beat thoroughly.
Add flour in fourths, mixing until blended after each addition.
Chill the dough until easy to handle.
Shape a teaspoon of dough around each pecan half, covering each nut completely.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while still warm.

title: pineapple-jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and cream cheese.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Chill.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together; then add other ingredients. Mix all ingredients.
Pour into a 9-inch unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
This is a rich tasty pie.

title: fat-free apple spice cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking soda, baking powder, cinnamon, allspice, salt and cloves.
Add applesauce, yogurt, egg substitute; blend well.
Add raisins, if desired.
Pour into greased and floured 12-cup Bundt or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Top with Quick Yogurt Glaze, if desired.

title: pizza in a skillet
directions: Prepare pizza crust according to package directions. Generously grease bottom and sides of cold 10-inch cast-iron skillet.
Grease fingers and spread dough evenly over bottom to edges of skillet; pinch up edges to hold sauce.
Pour canned pizza sauce from package over dough; spread to edges.
Cook covered with lid slightly ajar over medium-low heat on electric range or low heat on gas range for 14 to 16 minutes or until bottom is golden brown.
Loosen sides and bottom of pizza with spatula.
(Do not use a plastic spatula.)
Slide pizza onto cutting surface.
Serve immediately.

title: lady locks
directions: Cut butter into flour and sugar.
Beat yolks and water until foamy.
Blend in flour and mix until sticky dough.
Knead until smooth.
Cover and place in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Roll out into rectangle 1/3 inch thick.
Spread Crisco on dough (about 1/4).
Do this 4 times for 1 hour each time.
Fold over and return to refrigerator.
Take out and roll out 1/8 inch thick.
Cut into strips (1/2 x 6-inch).
Roll onto clothespins, covered with aluminum foil or you can buy new ones and season as you would a frying pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes, until lightly browned.
Cool.
Fill.

title: meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch meatballs (about 28).
Arrange on pan. Bake in preheated 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes until uniformly brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine the cream cheese, Worcestershire sauce and Accent and blend.
Chop the onions finely, adding some of the green tops.
Add to the cream cheese mixture.
Chop one package of dried beef or ham and add to the mixture.
Chill for 2 hours.
Roll into ball.
Chop the second package of dried beef or ham.
Roll ball in the chopped beef or ham.
Serve with your favorite crackers.
Enjoy!!

title: egg muffins
directions: These are elegant toasted and served under a poached egg.

title: 3-bean casserole
directions: Brown bacon and onion; add to beans and mix well.
Can sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sand cookies
directions: Mix sugar and margarine on high for 20 minutes.
Add flour. Keep mixer running on slow.
Fizz together baking soda and vinegar; add to dough.
Drop onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 300° for 25 minutes or until light brown.

title: quick mix drop cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375° and grease 2 large cookie sheets.
Sift flour and sugar together in a 2-quart bowl.
Add other ingredients and mix with electric mixer 2 minutes at low speed.
Keep guiding batter into beaters with rubber spatula (or beat by hand until batter is smooth, about 150 strokes).

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Break spaghetti in 1/2-inch pieces.
Cook and drain. Meanwhile, saute mushrooms in butter.
Season Sauce with nutmeg and sherry.
Put spaghetti in shallow baking dish.
Pour over half the sauce.
Put in chicken and mushrooms.
Pour over rest of sauce.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° until browned.
Serves 4.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine
creamed
and
whole
corn and butter.	Stir in sour cream
and	eggs (whipped).
Finally add corn bread mix. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top should be brown and crusted.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cook beets until tender.
Dip
into cold water and peel off skins.
Be sure
to
leave	plenty of stalks attached when cooking, otherwise they
will
"bleed"
and
lose their color. Slice or quarter as preferred.

title: mrs. wanda's peach cobbler
directions: Heat fruit in pan; put butter on top.
Put back in oven and heat until butter is melted.
Pour batter over fruit and butter. Bake until brown at 350°, usually about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: fudge sauce
directions: Mix together cocoa, salt, sugar and water.
Add evaporated milk and boil together for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add butter and vanilla.
Stir until blended.

title: coke cake
directions: Mix and set aside the flour and sugar.
Mix butter, Crisco, cocoa and Coke in saucepan; bring to a boil rapidly.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix all together and pour in greased 8 x 12-inch pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
Check from time to time; don't overcook.

title: chocolate cookie sheet cake
directions: In a
bowl
mix flour, sugar and salt.	Later add eggs, soda, buttermilk	and vanilla.
In a saucepan mix oleo, water, liquid Crisco
and cocoa.	Bring saucepan to a boil, stirring. Pour over mixture
in
bowl;	mix well by hand.
Add 2 beaten eggs.
Add
1 teaspoon
soda to 1/2 cup buttermilk and add to mixture.
Add
1 teaspoon
vanilla.	Pour
on
a greased 16 x 12-inch cookie sheet. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: coconut pie
directions: Cream the sugar and eggs. Add flour, water, vanilla and coconut.
Mix well. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix and put in baking dish.
Mix 1 stick butter (melted) or margarine and 1 stack crushed Ritz crackers.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until brown.

title: fast fixin fruit 'n cake
directions: Cover the bottom of a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan with the oil.
Put cake mix, eggs and water into pan.
Stir with a fork or spoon until well blended.
Scrape sides and spread butter evenly into the pan.
Spoon pie filling onto batter.
Use a fork to fold into batter, just enough to create marble effect.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool.
Store cake loosely covered.

title: macaroni and cheese(student favorite)
directions: Boil water and stir in macaroni; continue for 7 to 10 minutes or until tender.
Do not forget to stir occasionally or it will all clump together and be gross.
Add butter, milk and cheese sauce mix (included in macaroni box) and mix well.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: berry chili-barbecue sauce
directions: In a saucepan, mix together all ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until cranberry sauce is melted.
Use as a baste for broiling or grilling meat or poultry.
Also hot dogs, cut up and heated in sauce makes a nice party food! Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: sugarless mudd cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place flour and pecans in a 9 x 13-inch pan; melt oleo and pour over flour and pecans.
Mix well and flatten in pan.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Make whipped topping as directed with 1/2 cup cold water.
Add cream cheese and diet sweetener.
Beat well and spread on top of cooled first layer. Make another package of whipped topping.
Spread on top.
Finish with shaved chocolate bar.

title: kerry' red chili(get a big pot!)
directions: First put all of your tomatoes, water and sauce in a big pot. Cook on low heat while you are browning your meat. Next chop your green chilies and add them to the big pot. After you have browned your meat drain it and add it to your big pot. Now add the contents of the 2-Alarm chili mix except for the masa. Mix and add the masa about one hour prior to serving. And last but not least make adjustment as needed. Cook for at least 4 hours stirring every 15 min. and shazam its chili.

title: catfish jambalaya
directions: Saute sausage and set aside.
Melt butter.
Saute catfish strips until golden brown (5 to 6 minutes).
Add white wine; add shrimp and saute, about 5 minutes.
Add tomatoes, peppers and onion.
Cook with a top on about 5 minutes.
Add tomato sauce, diced tomatoes, seasonings and hot sauce.
Add sausage and mussels.
Add a few shakes of Jerk Seasoning.
Add a little more white wine if too thick and seasonings to taste.
Turn down and simmer for about 15 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: raisin sponge pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour
and salt with raisins.
Add water and lemon juice.
Cook
over
low
heat,
stirring constantly, until thickened (about
5 minutes).
Cool and spread in 9-inch baked pie shell.

title: breadsticks
directions: Cut day old bread into cubes.
Brush lightly with oil or melted butter or oleo.
Put cubes on shallow baking pan and bake at 300° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Stir once halfway through the cooking process.
These can be seasoned with garlic salt, seasoned salt or Parmesan cheese while hot.

title: easy corn pudding
directions: Melt butter in casserole.
Mix other ingredients and add butter.
Bake at 400°
for 45 minutes.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger or sausage; drain and set aside.
Combine cheese and Ro-Tel tomatoes in a large nonstick pan.
Place on low heat and stir until cheese is melted.
Add meat and mix well. Pour into crock-pot to keep dip warm and serve with chips.

title: overnight coffeecake
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, soda, salt, and 1 tsp. cinnamon in a bowl and set aside.
In another bowl, cream granulated sugar, 1/2 c. brown sugar, and butter.
Mix in eggs, buttermilk, and flour mixture.
Fold in apples.
Pour topping combine remaining 1/2 c. brown sugar, walnuts, and 1 tsp. cinnamon and sprinkle over batter.
Cover with foil and put in refrigerator until next morning.
Uncover and let stand about 30 minutes.
Bake 45 minutes in a 350 degree oven.
It's best served warm.
Try drizzling coffeecake with a thin powdered sugar frosting before serving.

title: spinach canapes
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Form into bite size balls.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° about 20 minutes.

title: taco supreme
directions: Cook ground beef,chirizo sausage and onion until brown.
Pour off fat and add several drops of Tabasco sauce.
Spread beans in 10 x 15 pan.
Spread meat mixture over beans and sprinkle on chili and cheese.
Drizzle salsa over that.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Top with scallions.
Mount avocado in center of pan and top with sour cream.
Then garnish with olives and parsley.
Keep warm and serve tortilla chips for dipping.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt butter and cocoa together.
Remove from heat.
Mix well. Add flour, nuts and vanilla; mix well.
Spoon batter into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes. Spread marshmallow cream on top.
Cover with chocolate frosting.

title: dorothy's poppy seed dressing
directions: Blend in blender first 7 ingredients; add oil and blend again. Put in large jar and add poppy seed; shake well.
May be kept in refrigerator for several days.
Shake well before each use.
Good on lettuce or spinach salads.

title: four layer dessert
directions: 1st Layer:
Mix the flour with the margarine and the nuts. Put in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan and bake for 15 minutes in 350° oven.
Cool.

title: broccoli lima bake
directions: Cook vegetables until barely tender, as on package directions. Blend soup, sour cream and onion mix; stir until vegetables cook. Add water chestnuts.
Pour into buttered casserole.
Top with Rice Krispies that have been tossed in stick of margarine that has been heated over low heat.
Place on top of vegetable mixture. Cover with foil.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: caramel tarts
directions: Mix cheese, 2 sticks oleo and flour.
Make 72 balls.
Press into greased tart pans or use paper liners.

title: popcorn cake
directions: Melt marshmallows in butter.
Pour over popped popcorn.
Add peanuts and gumdrops to corn mixture.
Mix together and then press firmly into buttered angel food cake pan.
Let set until firm. Turn out on plate and slice with electric knife.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Brown sausage and onion.
Drain.
In bowl, mix eggs, milk, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper.
Place crumbled bread in greased casserole.
Put sausage and onion over bread.
Pour eggs over sausage.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Cover and put in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour, uncovered.

title: refrigerator rolls(4 dozen)
directions: Scald milk with sugar and shortening.
Cool to lukewarm.
Then add yeast thoroughly dissolved in lukewarm water.
With the new fast-action yeast, you can use it according to the instructions on the package; eliminate the 1/4 cup warm water and mix the dry yeast in with the flour.
Add 8 cups of flour.
Beat well.
Let rise until double in bulk, then add salt, soda and baking powder.
Add enough flour (about 1 cup) to make soft dough.
Place in bowl, grease surface of dough, cover and place in refrigerator.
Make rolls when wanted.
Will keep 1 week to 10 days.

title: sweet potatoes gratin
directions: Bake sweet potatoes until tender in preheated 350° oven 1 hour. Or, pierce sweet potatoes several times with a fork and place on microwavable plate.
Microwave at HIGH (100% power) 16 to 18 minutes, rotating and turning over after 9 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes.
While sweet potatoes are hot, cut lengthwise into halves. Scrape hot pulp from skins into large bowl.
Beat 1/4 c. butter and 2 Tbsp. sugar into sweet potatoes with electric mixer at medium speed until butter is melted.
Beat in eggs, orange juice, 1 1/2 tsp. cinnamon, salt and nutmeg, scraping down sides of bowl once. Beat until smooth.
Pour mixture into 1 1/2 qt. baking dish; smooth top.
For topping, combine flour, oats, remaining 1/4 c. sugar and 1/2 tsp. cinnamon in medium bowl.
Cut in remaining 1/4 c. butter with pastry blender or 2 knives until mixture becomes coarse crumbs.
Stir in pecans.
Sprinkle topping evenly over sweet potatoes.* Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until sweet potatoes are heated through.
For a crispier topping, broil 5 inches from heat 2 to 3 minutes or until golden brown.
Garnish as desired.

title: chocolate coca-cola cake
directions: Mix flour, soda and sugar.
Heat margarine, Coca-Cola and cocoa over medium heat to boiling point.
Pour over flour mixture and stir.
Add buttermilk, eggs, vanilla and marshmallows.
Batter will be thin.
Bake in well-greased 3-quart Pyrex pan (13 x 9-inches) for 35 minutes at 350°.
Top with favorite frosting.

title: hot cheddar dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, except corn chips, in a 1-quart casserole dish or glass bowl.
Microwave, uncovered, at Medium-high for 2 to 3 minutes.
Stir 1 or 2 times during cooking. Serve hot with chips.
Yield: 1 1/2 cups.

title: jambalaya
directions: Brown both meats separately and drain well.
Stir in all ingredients.
Cover and cook for 20 minutes or until rice is done.

title: chicken pie
directions: Mix all ingredients except Bisquick and milk together.
Mix Bisquick and milk and spread over top.
Dot with butter or margarine.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
May be divided into 2 pans; freezes well.

title: chicken in foil
directions: Cut 4 (24 x 18-inch) pieces of heavy- duty aluminum foil. Place a chicken quarter in center of each; sprinkle with garlic salt and paprika.
Top evenly with onion and next 4 ingredients. Spoon soup evenly over each portion.
Seal bundles and place on a 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tuna-spinach sandwich spread
directions: Mix together the tuna, mayonnaise, spinach, green onions, Worcestershire sauce and hot pepper sauce.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple, oranges and thawed strawberries.
Add pie filling.
Add sliced bananas.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground meat.
Drain.
Mix everything together, except Velveeta.
Cube Velveeta and mix again.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Beat eggs until light and frothy.
Add remaining ingredients and mix until well blended.
(If using cocoa, add with dry ingredients.)
Sift together and add dry ingredients to first mixture; blend well.

title: cajun paneed chicken
directions: Combine catsup, mustard and all of the seasonings in a small bowl; mix well.
Combine eggs and Parmesan cheese in a shallow pan; mix well.
In a separate pan, combine 2 tablespoons of the seasoning mix with the bread crumbs (a blender or food processor works best); set aside.
Spread a thin layer of the remaining seasoning mix on each side of the chicken tenders.
Soak the coated chicken in egg mixture for 30 minutes.

title: marinated pork chops
directions: Put the chopped onions, ginger and garlic in blender and blend to a smooth paste (about 1 minute at high speed).
Combine paste with remaining ingredients except the pork chops and mix well. Prick holes in the pork chops.
Rub well with the marinade; cover and refrigerate for at least 6 hours.
Reserve marinade.
Sear pork chops on grill for 8 minutes on each side at low temperature. Put grill on high temperature and cook for about 20 minutes on each side.
Brush with the marinade before turning pork chops over each time.

title: egg custard pie(very good)
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Add butter and mix.
Add yolks, milk and vanilla; mix again.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Beat egg whites (1/3 cup sugar to 3 egg whites) and put on baked pie.
Bake again until golden brown.
"Men love this."

title: mama mables october relish(very good!)
directions: Chop vegetables and mix with pickling salt.
Let this stand 2 hours.
Drain thoroughly.
Mix with the last 3 ingredients.
Bring this to a boil and pack in jars.

title: polynesian tang island ribs
directions: Trim fat from ribs.
Line a large shallow baking dish with foil.
Arrange ribs in dish.
Bake at 450° for 30 minutes.
Turn and bake 30 minutes more.
Pour off fat.

title: saucepan brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt oleo and chocolate in 2-quart pan over low heat, mixing occasionally.
Stir in sugar and cool to room temperature.
Stir in eggs, vanilla and then flour and walnuts.
Turn into a buttered 9-inch square pan and bake 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle chocolate chips on right away.
Allow to stand 5 minutes or until melted.
Spread to make frosting.
Cool and cut into squares.
Very good and very quick.

title: cash tuna casserole
directions: Combine tuna, soup, milk, noodles and 1 1/2 cup cheese in 2.5 quart casserole dish.
Top with remaining cheese and crushed corn flakes.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain peas, green beans, corn & pimento. Chop celery, bell pepper and onion. Mix all ingredients in a bowl. Bring vinegar, sugar and oil to a boil. Pour over vegetable mixture and refrigerate overnight.

title: coconut carrot cake
directions: Combine flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Beat oil, sugar and eggs until well blended.
Add flour mixture;
beat until smooth.
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Pour into greased 10 inch tube pan or 13 x 9 inch pan.
Bake 350 degrees for 50 to 55 minutes, or until tester inserted in center comes out clean. Remove from pan.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Mix all ingredients together.
Chill the mixture until firm.
Mold into balls.
Freeze.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes on foil sprayed with Pam.

title: roast duck with sausage stuffing
directions: Prepare herb dressing according to directions.
Add your favorite sausage.
Add celery, pecans and onions.

title: taco soup
directions: Mix in crock-pot. Cook on high for 2 hours or low for 3 hours. Can cook on stove for 1 hour. Top with grated cheese and sour cream. Serve with tortilla chips or corn bread.

title: cream cheese biscuits
directions: In a bowl soften cream cheese and butter and stir to mix.
Add flour and salt; stir to mix.
Shape into a 1 1/2-inch diameter log.
Refrigerate.
When dough is hardened, cut into 1/4-inch wafers.
Bake on an ungreased baking sheet for 20 minutes in a preheated 350° oven, for 10 minutes at 400°.
Biscuits will be light brown.
No need to butter.
Makes about 40 biscuits.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: Slice mushrooms through cap and stem.
Cook with onion in butter for 5 minutes.
Add flour and blend; add stock.
Cook and stir until slightly thickened.
Cool slightly.
Add sour cream and seasoning.
Heat through.
Serve at once.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: spaghetti squash marinara
directions: In a large nonstick skillet, heat olive oil and butter.

Saute garlic and onion until onion is translucent, about 5 minutes. Add mushrooms and saute 2 minutes longer. Stir in tomatoes, parsley and seasonings. Cover and simmer gently for 15 minutes. Stir in half of the Parmesan cheese. Reheat spaghetti squash and arrange strands on serving platter.
Spoon sauce and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cracker candy
directions: Line a 9 x 13-inch cookie sheet with foil.
Arrange saltine crackers, 1 layer thick, in rows on cookie sheet.

title: chex muddy buddies puppy chow
directions: Pour cereal in large bowl.
Melt chocolate chips, butter and peanut butter.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour mixture over Chex cereal until evenly coated.
Shake on powdered sugar.

title: tacocitas
directions: In
a
deep
dish,
place
1/2 of the lettuce (shredded fine), then
layer of Fritos.
Add 1/2 can of tomatoes chopped over the Fritos,
then
a layer of 1/2 can of chili which has been heated to	boiling
point.
Repeat
in this same way the other
half of ingredients.
Lastly, sprinkle grated cheese on top.
Serve at once.

title: flip flop salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add pineapple juice; cool.
Mix the next 5 ingredients together.
Reserve 1 tablespoon mayonnaise to grease dish.
Put the cream cheese mixture in bottom of dish. Pour Jell-O mixture on top and watch it "flip flop."
Chill in refrigerator.

title: passover macaroons
directions: Beat egg whites and sugar until stiff.
Add coconut.
Add enough cake meal to make batter loose enough to drop off spoon. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: cafe vienna mix
directions: Place sugar in a small bowl.
Sprinkle with almond and vanilla extracts.
Blend until no traces of moisture remain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Sift to blend.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 1 1/2 cups of mix.
To serve:
Add 3 teaspoons mix to 1 cup boiling water.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Allow to cool completely.
With a fork, poke numerous holes in the cake.
Pour the Kahlua over the top of the cake, cover with aluminum foil, and sit overnight.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Measure peanut butter and corn syrup into mixing bowl.
Mix until thoroughly combined.
Add Rice Krispies cereal; stir until well coated.
With back of tablespoon, press mixture evenly and firmly in bottom and around side of lightly buttered 9-inch pie pan to form crust.
Chill until firm.
Spread ice cream evenly in chilled crust.
Freeze until firm.
Cut into wedges to serve. Garnish with peach slices or other fresh fruit, if desired.

title: hamburg casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in moderate oven (about 375° to 400°) for 20 to 30 minutes.
tags: cream of chicken soup or cream of celery soup

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat; drain. Add spaghetti sauce. Grease 9 x 13 casserole dish. In casserole dish, line bottom with 3 lasagna noodles, then 1/2 hamburger mixture. On top of that, "spoon out" 1 can diced tomatoes. Layer 1/2 cottage cheese, 1/2 container Parmesan and 1/2 grated cheese. Add another layer of each. Cover with Reynolds Wrap and bake at 375° for about 25 to 30 minutes. Take off foil and brown cheese.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix all together and beat 1 1/2 minutes.
Pour into two 9-inch pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: throw-together-in-the-morning when the relatives spend the day -(note:  nothing needs to be exact.)
directions: Optional:
Chicken broth, kidney beans, tomatoes (fresh or canned), snap peas, sliced mushrooms, celery, onions, garlic, zucchini, parsley, almost any vegetable, even potatoes.

title: yogurt shakes
directions: Blend juice concentrate, yogurt and milk in blender until smooth.
Pour into 2 tall glasses and top with large scoop of orange sherbet.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix flour, milk and eggs; beat well.
Blend together, but not until smooth.
Pour hot butter into skillet.
Bake in 425° oven for 15 minutes.
Top with jelly or marmalade.

title: golfer's corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Pour into round pan.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: sugar-free zucchini bread
directions: Mix oil with Sugar Twin, zucchini and eggs.
Mix flour with salt, baking soda, baking powder and spices.
Add to zucchini mixture.
Blend in milk; stir in nuts and raisins.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Combine butter, flour, milk and salt; cook until thickened. Arrange alternate layers of potatoes and sauce in greased baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tasty fruit dip
directions: Beat all ingredients until creamy.
Serve with fruit, such as apple wedges, pear wedges, grapes, pineapple, etc.

title: cheese puff tidbits
directions: Place all ingredients in a bowl.
Blend with fingers until smooth.
Refrigerate for 1/2 hour.
Form into 1/2-inch balls and place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 15 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: kay's smith island cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar well.
Beat eggs separately and add to creamed butter and sugar.
Add vanilla.
Mix evaporated milk and water together.
Alternately mix in flour and evaporated milk.
Add baking powder and last cup of flour.
Bake in thin layers.

title: chutney spread
directions: Mix together with small amount of milk.
Layer 1/2-inch thick on serving platter.
Sprinkle top with toasted almonds.
Chill. Serve with crackers.

title: busy day fish bake
directions: Pepper fish fillets.
Dip in milk and coat with cornflake crumbs.
Arrange fillets in single layer in lightly oiled shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until flakes easily. May be baked hotter for shorter time.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.

title: popcorn puffs
directions: Bring butter, brown sugar and Karo syrup to a boil.
Add 1/4 teaspoon baking soda and simmer 5 minutes.
Put 1 bag of Snyder's Puff and Corn popcorn in large pan.
Pour syrup mixture over popcorn and stir.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool on waxed paper.
Break up in pieces.

title: dumplings
directions: Add enough cold water or chicken broth to make a stiff dough. Make into small balls and let rest about 2 hours.
Roll dough real thin. Cut about 1-inch wide.
Drop dough into hot broth that has been strained to prevent small bones.
Add cooked chicken and cook 10 minutes.
Turn off heat.
Two tablespoons of sweet milk may be added.

title: cherries jubilee
directions: In a large, heavy skillet, melt butter.
Add sugars, cinnamon, zest and cloves.
Separate cherry juice and add cherries to pan. Heat 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add orange and lime juice and stir.
Add cherry juice and dissolved cornstarch.
Heat until thick.
Insert cloves into horseneck orange at intervals.
Heat brandy in ladle (if using gas stove) or in small pan (if using electric stove).
Flame and pour into pan.
Stir and serve over vanilla ice cream.

title: quick and easy baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bacon.
Pour into baking dish and bake at 400° for about 30 minutes.
Crumble bacon on top.

title: irene's country chili
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Add onion, celery, green pepper and garlic.
Brown until onion is golden.
Add tomatoes, chili powder (mixed with the cold water), salt, sugar and Worcestershire sauce. Boil, covered, then simmer one hour.
Add beans, drained.
Cook, uncovered, until well heated and to desired thickness.
Spice with a speck of cayenne pepper.

title: quick and delicious punch
directions: Mix this and add enough water to make 2 1/2 gallons.
Can be made ahead and frozen.
Serve ice cold.

title: easy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter in a large, heavy saucepan; heat to boiling.
Stir constantly until mixture reaches soft ball stage (238°), about 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients; stir until blended.
Pour into well-greased pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Makes about 3 pounds of fudge.

title: red beet eggs
directions: Peel the eggs.
Combine the juice from the beets, vinegar and sugar.
Dissolve sugar well.
Add juice mixture and beets to eggs. Let stand 1 to 2 days in refrigerator.
Eggs will get a deep red color like the beets as they stay in the juice.
Good in salads or by themselves.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Combine
all ingredients, except pie crusts, in a large mixing bowl.
Beat
with
an
electric
mixer until smooth and creamy. Pour in pie crusts and bake at 375° for 70 minutes.

title: pear relish
directions: Process all vegetables.
Place in large pot.
After it begins to boil, cook for 30 minutes.
Makes 10 pints.

title: olive-cucumber finger sandwiches
directions: With a fork, score cucumber lengthwise; cut into thin slices. Place in a bowl; add water and vinegar.
Let stand for 30 minutes. Meanwhile, in a small mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, mayonnaise, garlic powder, onion salt and worcestershire sauce.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean and stem mushrooms.
Cook sausage like taco meat.
Mix sausage with cream cheese.
Stuff mushrooms with mixture.
Broil until stuffing lightly browns and sizzles.
Serve.

title: baked chili casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Brown hamburger with onion.
Mix macaroni, hamburger, sugar, spaghetti sauce, kidney beans and chili powder. Salt to taste.
Bake in casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Add pineapple, marshmallows and pecans to Cool Whip and pudding.
Mix well	and
refrigerate
at
least
1 hour before serving.

title: mexican meat pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Grease 12-inch pizza pan.
Prepare hot roll mix as label directs, but use 1 cup water and omit eggs.
Do not let dough rise.
Press 1/8-inch thick onto bottom and sides of pan.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: powderhorn potatoes
directions: Grate potatoes and cheese and onion. Mix all ingredients together in small baking dish. Cook at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: dried beef casserole
directions: Fry beef in butter until lightly browned.
Add mushroom soup and
milk.	Combine
noodles,
beef
mixture and put in a casserole.	Cover
with
buttered
bread crumbs.
Can also use beef chunks instead of dried beef.

title: ruth vancies
directions: Butter a 10 x 13-inch pan.
In pan, bring brown sugar and Karo syrup to boil.
Turn off heat.
Mix in peanut butter then Special K.
Put in buttered pan.
Melt chocolate chip bits and butterscotch bits together.
In microwave, heat 3 minutes on High. Pour over pan mixture.
Set aside to harden.
Cut into small pieces and refrigerate.

title: copper pennies
directions: Cut carrots in 1/4-inch rounds.
Slice onions thin and separate into rings; cut green pepper in strips.
Cook carrots in salted water for 8 to 10 minutes or until tender; drain.
In large bowl, combine carrots with onion and green pepper.
Stir remaining ingredients together and pour over vegetables.
Cover and marinate in refrigerator several hours or overnight.
Drain to serve.
Save liquid to pour over leftover vegetables and refrigerate.

title: neiman-marcus cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs and vanilla. Mix together with flour, oatmeal and spices. Add chips, candy and nuts. Make into balls and place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chili sauce
directions: Brown onion and hamburger meat in small amount of oil.
Add tomatoes, tomato paste, tomato sauce, Worcestershire sauce and chili powder.
Cook on low heat for 1 hour, covered.
Stir occasionally.
Bring to a boil, then cook down to thicken.
Good on hot dogs and hamburgers, too!

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly. Roll into large marble size balls and bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: light cheese cake
directions: Cream the cream cheese until smooth.
Add sugar and mix well. Fold in yogurt and	Cool Whip.
Pour into pie crust and chill for several hours.
Garnish with cherries.

title: cheese mushroom puffs
directions: Cut rounds from bread (2 per slice) and brush with butter on one side.
Toast on buttered side.
Place a mushroom on untoasted side.
Mix remaining ingredients and put a teaspoon of mixture on each mushroom.
Place under broiler until it puffs.
Serve at once.
Yields 32 puffs.

title: butter bundt cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add one egg at a time.
Stir in well. Stir in flour all at once.
Add vanilla.
Pour into prepared Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: chocolate pleasers
directions: In a large bowl, combine Crispix and peanuts. Set aside. Put both kinds of morsels in small bowl in microwave. Heat on High 2 minutes, stirring after 1 minute. Stir until smooth. Pour melted morsels over dry ingredients, stirring until well mixed. Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper. Chill until firm, about 15 minutes. Store in the refrigerator in an airtight container. Makes 4 dozen candies.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Combine all ingredients and refrigerate 24 hours.

title: spoonburgers
directions: Brown meat and onion in fat slowly in a skillet, stirring with fork to break up meat.
Spoon off any fat left in skillet.
Stir into meat mixture the milk, salt and pepper.
Cook and stir over low heat until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat and stir in catsup.
Spoon meat mixture into buns.
Serve hot, 2 to a serving. Makes 4 servings.

title: quick chili rice
directions: In a large skillet, brown beef and onion; drain.
Add all ingredients except rice and cheese.
Cover and bring to a full boil.
Add rice; reduce heat, cover and simmer 5 minutes. Sprinkle cheese to cover and melt.

title: frozen cherry dessert
directions: Mix all together and freeze; cut into squares.

title: eggnog rice pudding
directions: Heat eggnog over low heat and combine milk and cornstarch. Pour into eggnog, stirring constantly.
Continue to cook over low heat until it thickens.
Remove from heat; add raisins, salt and flavoring.
Fold rice into mixture and pour into an ungreased serving dish.
Garnish with nutmeg and chill.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: hot cheddar dip
directions: In small bowl, blend all ingredients.
Cook, uncovered, 2 minutes or until hot, stirring occasionally.
Makes 1 1/2 cups dip.

title: miss hulling's carrot salad
directions: Peel carrots.
Shred coarsely into a mixing bowl.
Add marshmallows, pineapple, raisins and coconut.
Toss lightly to mix.
Combine mayonnaise with carrot mixture.
Carefully fold in whipped cream.
Garnish with additional coconut.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Drain shrimp well.
Rinse and drain very well again.
Combine all ingredients and refrigerate for at least 4 hours.
Serve with small pretzels.

title: banana bread
directions: Grease bread pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: easy to make coffee cake
directions: Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Set aside.
Combine cake mix, eggs, water, softened margarine and vanilla.
Beat until well combined (2 minutes).
Pour 1/2 of mixture into well-greased Bundt pan.
Sprinkle sugar and cinnamon mixture over batter.
Pour remaining batter over it.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Cool in pan 5 to 7 minutes before removing.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Then add eggs and beat well.
Mix flour, soda and salt together.
Then add alternately with buttermilk to sugar mixture.
Add nuts last.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
This makes a large cake.

title: ice pickles
directions: Put cucumbers in large pan and cover with ice.
Just cover top.
Put in 1/2 cup salt per gallon of cucumbers.
Let set for 3 hours.
Drain off water and rinse off salt water.
Mix remaining ingredients together.
Mix well.
Let come almost to boil.
Keep stirring with wooden spoon.
Pack cucumbers loosely in jars. Cover cucumbers with hot liquid up close to the top.
If you want to keep pickles longer than 1 year, put in pressure canner.
Let steam 10 minutes with peacock up.

title: no peek stew
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Place in crock-pot.
Cook on low for 8 hours.
Serve over hot noodles or bake in casserole for 2 to 3 hours at 350° to 375°.
Do not lift lid.

title: bow ties with sausage and sweet peppers
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
Return pasta to saucepan.

title: sausage cheese rounds
directions: Drain cooked, crumbled sausage on paper towel.
Melt cheese in top of double boiler.
Add sausage and Worcestershire sauce and mix well.
Spread on party rye bread and place
under broiler. May be frozen before broiling.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Lightly salt and pepper chicken.
Put chicken in bottom of baking dish.
Saute celery in oleo.
Add to baking dish.
Add rice.
Combine soups and water.
Pour in.
Sprinkle dried onion soup mix over chicken and other ingredients.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°, uncovered.

title: french dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together in covered glass jar.
Shake well. Refrigerate.

title: baked chicken livers and rice
directions: Coat chicken livers with flour; brown in butter.
Remove from skillet; place in casserole dish.
Add a little more butter and saute celery, onion and rice for 2 minutes, add chicken broth.
Mix well with chicken livers.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 325°.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Heat water to boiling and add to jello until dissolved.
Add pineapple juice and chill until syrupy.
Whip the Philly cream cheese and milk.
Add to Jell-O and whip.
Spread sliced bananas and chunk pineapple in bottom of a 9-inch square dish.
Pour Jell-O mixture over top and chill.

title: yummy spinach
directions: Cook and drain spinach.
Marinate spinach two hours in the sour cream and Lipton onion soup mix.
Top with Pepperidge Farm cornbread stuffing and melted margarine.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Melt butter and mix with graham cracker crumbs and 1/2 cup sugar.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix whipping cream, milk, 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla until stiff, then mix in softened cream cheese.
Spread over graham cracker crust.
Top with blueberries. Chill overnight.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Boil broccoli, onion, salt and pepper in water 15 minutes. Add cheese until melted. Add milk; use flour if you need to make soup thicker. Mix flour with water until creamy. Gradually add to soup until desired thickness.

title: cucumber-cheese ring
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water. Add cream cheese, mayonnaise, horseradish, salt and lemon juice.
Beat smooth. Chill until partially set. Stir in cucumber and green onion.
Chill in 3 1/2 cup mold until firm.

title: lena's cheese and potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes about 1/4-inch thick.
Cook until tender. Drain off water.
Then layer potatoes in a baking pan.
Sprinkle with other ingredients.
Keep doing this until you use all your potatoes and other ingredients.
Put cheese on top.
Put in oven (on broil) for about 10 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: magic marshmallow crescent puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine sugar and cinnamon.
Separate crescent dough into 16 triangles.
Dip a marshmallow in melted margarine; roll in sugar-cinnamon mixture.
Place marshmallow on shortest side of triangles.
Fold in the corners over the marshmallow, pinching in the edges.
Dip in melted margarine and place margarine side down in deep muffin cup.
Repeat with remaining marshmallow.
Place pan on a cookie sheet to stop spillage.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes until golden brown.

title: blackberry cake with cream cheese icing
directions: Mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Bundt pan preferred.
Let cake cool completely.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Soften butter or margarine.
Add sugars; beat together until well mixed.
Add egg and beat.
Sift flour, salt, soda and oatmeal.
Blend in butter mixture until well mixed.
Add chocolate chips, pecans and raisins by hand.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheets.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and powdered sugar well.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla and food coloring.
Add flour, stirring in a little at a time.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: crock-pot stew
directions: Cut steak into 1-inch strips.
Slice potatoes.
Chop onions. Layer in order in crock-pot.
Pour 1 can tomato soup on top (undiluted).
Cook on low heat for 4 to 6 hours.

title: zucchini brownies
directions: Cream the sugar, margarine and oil.
Add eggs and mix well. Add vanilla and sour milk and blend.
Add sifted dry ingredients. Stir in zucchini.
Spread baking sheet or jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inches) with cooking spray.
Pour batter into pan and sprinkle the chips and nuts evenly over the top.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: peanut butter chewies
directions: Put ingredients into a saucepan.
Stir constantly until it comes to a boil.
After it comes to a boil, stir in 5 cups of cornflakes.
Pour ingredients into an 8 1/2 x 12-inch greased pan. Let harden.
Cut into squares.

title: autumn soup
directions: Cook until vegetables are tender (except tomatoes).
Add the tomatoes the last 20 minutes.

title: pastry shell
directions: Finely crush the cereal to make 1 1/4 cups of crumbs.
Combine cereal crumbs and the brown or granulated sugar.
Mix in softened butter.
Press firmly on bottom and sides of 9-inch pie pan. Chill 1 hour before filling or bake at 375° for 5 to 8 minutes. Cool before filling.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Stir together margarine, sugar and milk in heavy 2 1/2 to 3-quart saucepan.
Bring to full boil, stirring constantly.
Boil 5 minutes over medium heat, or until candy thermometer reaches 234°, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat. Gradually stir in chocolate until melted.
Add remaining ingredients; mix until well blended.
Pour into greased 9 x 9-inch or 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature; cut into squares. Makes 3 pounds.

title: half ways
directions: Cream together shortening, brown sugar and white sugar.
Add egg yolks, beaten with water and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add to creamed mixture.
This is a stiff dough. Pat out onto 14 x 10-inch greased pan.
Sprinkle with chocolate pieces.
Beat whites stiff; add brown sugar and continue beating (will be thin).
Spread over top of chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool before cutting.

title: butternut squash soup
directions: In saucepan cook onions over medium-low heat with 1 tablespoon butter until softened.
Add salt, squash and cloves and cook, covered, over low heat for 10 to 15 minutes or until tender.
Add stock and simmer for 15 minutes.
Add cream and bring to a boil. In small saucepan, cook remaining 3 tablespoons butter over medium heat until nut-brown and add to stock mixture.
In blender, puree the mixture in batches and strain through fine sieve into a bowl. Add salt and pepper to taste and garnish with Blue cheese, sage and parsley (or some toasted walnuts).
Serves 6.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
except
cheese and potato chips. Turn into
shallow
buttered
casserole.
Combine
cheese and potato chips and spread over top. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 minutes.
(Do not overcook.) Makes 6 servings.

title: gala cherry salad
directions: Pour cherries in saucepan.
Add water and sugar; boil.
Add jello; mix well.
Stir in other ingredients.
Pour into pan or well oiled mold.
Refrigerate to set.
Serves 12 to 15.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly with sugar, dash of salt, corn syrup and melted butter.
Add pecans.
Pour into the unbaked pie shell. Bake in oven at 350° for fifty minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix apples, sugar, water and cinnamon together in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Mix brown sugar, oats and flour together, then add melted butter.
Put this mixture over apples.
Bake about 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together; bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: crawfish etouffee
directions: Melt butter in a heavy saucepan.
Add chopped vegetables and saute until well wilted.
Add flour and stir constantly until well mixed.
Do not brown!
Add seasonings and tomato sauce.
Simmer for about 25 minutes.
Pre-fry crawfish tails until water is driven off.
Add crawfish tails to mixture and simmer for an additional 20 minutes.
Just before serving, add finely chopped green onions and parsley.
Serve with hot rice.
(Do not use black cast-iron pot to cook this in.)

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Chop onion and saute in oleo.
Add Velveeta and heat until cheese melts.
Add sour cream, soup and potatoes.
Mix well and pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 325° for approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Check for doneness at the end of 1 hour.
Cooking time may vary with type and size of container.

title: fruit cookies
directions: Mix all together.
Bake on greased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes in 350° oven.
Makes 85 cookies.

title: celia's strawberry bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in a large bowl.
Make a well in the center of mixture.
Mix all ingredients together; stir enough to dampen all ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: betty ann's pumpkin dessert
directions: Set aside one cup dry cake mix.
Cut 1/2 cup softened margarine into remaining dry cake mix.
Press mixture into bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cold asparagus in mustard sauce
directions: Cook asparagus to desired tenderness.
Drain on paper towel, cover and refrigerate.
Mash cooked egg yolk with raw egg yolk and mustard in a small bowl until smooth.
Slowly whisk in oil until smooth.
Add vinegar, salt and pepper to oil mixture, blending well.
Spoon mustard sauce over asparagus and garnish with egg white.

title: peach crisp
directions: Spread pie filling in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Sprinkle cake mix over pie filling. Melt margarine and pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
You can also use apple or cherry pie filling.

title: aunt ruth's brisket
directions: Wrap brisket tightly
in foil.	Place in baking pan and cook in oven for 2 1/2
hours
at
Remove from oven and refrigerate overnight.
In morning,
unwrap
and skim off fat. Slice meat thin.
Place on clean foil.
Mix remaining ingredients. Pour over sliced
brisket.
Fold
and
seal foil.	Cook for 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook chopped cabbage in salt water until tender.
Saute onion in butter.
Add cheese.
Drain cabbage and add soup and cheese mixture.
Put 1/2 in casserole; add 1/2 of crumbs.
Add rest of cabbage and then sprinkle remaining crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: quiche
directions: Blend in blender the eggs and onion.
Add milk, Bisquick and salt.
Pour into 10-inch pie pan that has been greased and filled with cream cheese, shredded cheese and meat or vegetable.

title: rice and ham griddle cakes
directions: In medium bowl, beat eggs.
Add cooked rice, milk and butter; mix well.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add to egg mixture.
Beat until well blended.
Stir in diced ham.

title: banana split pie
directions: Combine crushed vanilla wafers with melted butter and mix well.
Press onto sides and bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: barbecue roll-ups(appetizers)
directions: Cut turkey in 1-inch squares.
Wrap 1 water chestnut slice and 3 squares turkey up with bacon.
Secure with toothpick.
Place on a rack in baking pan.
Bake at 350° until bacon is cooked.
Cover with barbecue sauce and heat until sauce is warm.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown pork slowly in oil, add water, cover and simmer until tender.
Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add pineapple juice, vinegar, soy sauce and salt.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Pour over pork, simmer 10 minutes; add pineapple, green pepper and cherries.
Cook 5 minutes longer, stir often.
Serve over rice.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant until tender.
Beat up with mixer.
Add bell pepper and onions that have been sauteed in margarine.
Add egg, Parmesan cheese and half of the bread crumbs.
Put in buttered casserole dish and add the bread crumbs to top.
Bake 25 minutes at 400°.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Put broth, poultry seasoning and soup into a large pot.
Bring to a boil.
Cut biscuits in fourths.
Add pieces one piece at a time to broth mixture.
Cook just until biscuits are done, stirring carefully.
Add diced chicken and stir.
Heat until chicken is warm.

title: aunt molly's jewish coffee cake
directions: Cream butter or margarine well.
Add sugar; cream until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift together and mix into mixture sifted flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt. Stir into mixture sour cream and vanilla.

title: marg's cranberry salad
directions: Combine
Jell-O, boiling water, cinnamon and salt.
Let set until
syrupy.
Mince
the cranberries; add the sugar and let stand.
When
Jell-O
is syrupy, add cranberries, apples, pineapple and nuts.
Let set until firm.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Place hash browns in a 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Mix butter or margarine, sour cream and soup.
Add salt and pepper according to taste.
Pour this over hash browns.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Uncover.
Put cheese and crushed corn flakes on top and bake until cheese melts and flakes brown.

title: joan's poached salmon
directions: In a poacher or roasting pan with wire rack, add enough clam juice and white wine, plus the bay leaves, to bring just about even with wire rack. Place fish on wire rack, cover with lid and place over medium heat to bring liquid to boil, then lower to simmer for approximately 25 to 30 minutes.
Can be served hot or cold.

title: south carolina spoon bread
directions: Heat milk in double boiler.
Stir in cornmeal and cook slowly until thick and smooth.
Remove from heat and add butter and salt. Let cool while beating egg whites stiff.
Beat egg yolks and add to cornmeal mixture, then fold in egg whites and bake 30 minutes in a buttered pan at 325° to 375°.

title: creamed tomatoes
directions: Combine tomatoes, butter, sugar and salt in medium saucepan. Heat over medium heat.
Stir in soda.
Combine flour and milk; blend well and add to hot mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture is thick and bubbly.
Break toasted bread in small pieces and add to hot tomato mixture.
Serves 4.

title: low sodium bread and butter pickles
directions: In a 4-quart enamel or stainless steel saucepan heat sugar, vinegar and spices to boiling over high heat.
Stir frequently. When to a boil, add cucumber and onion slices.
Bring to boil again, then reduce heat to low and simmer, covered, for ten minutes, stirring occasionally.
Store in covered glass containers in refrigerator.
Use within one month.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan until toothpick comes out clean at 300°.
Remove cake from oven.
While still hot, punch holes in cake with fork.
Pour milk over top.

title: crabmeat salad
directions: Separate crabmeat, removing membrane.
Add remaining ingredients except salad greens, mixing gently.
Refrigerate covered for at least 1 hour.
Serve on salad greens.

title: vanilla pudding
directions: Cook rice and milk together.
Keep stirring on low heat until rice is cooked, about 20 or 30 minutes.

title: broccoli and noodles parmesan
directions: Cut broccoli into bite sized pieces.
In covered 4-quart saucepan over medium heat in 1-inch of boiling water, cook broccoli for 6 minutes or until tender.
Drain in colander.
In same saucepan over medium heat in hot butter, cook onion and garlic until tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in soup and seasoning; mix well.
Add cheese and Parmesan, stirring until melted.
Stir in sour cream, broccoli and cooked noodles.

title: shrimp and linguini
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients and set aside.
Combine cumin, pepper and paprika and toss with shrimp.
Add broccoli to shrimp mixture and steam until shrimp are done, stirring once.
(Shrimp will become translucent.)
Drain pasta and transfer to serving plates. Spoon broccoli and shrimp mixture on top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Serves 2.

title: hungryman casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add remaining ingredients except biscuits.
Put in casserole dish.
Top with biscuits.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Mix together very well the flour, sugar, salt and cocoa.
Then add milk and eggs to flour mixture slowly.
Mix well.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and margarine.
Delicious over biscuits or buttered toast.
Keeps well for several days.

title: beef log
directions: Mix all ingredients; season to taste.
Roll in plastic wrap or wax paper to form a log.
Chill before serving.
Serve with crackers.

title: eggplant appetizer
directions: Place tomatoes in a large saucepan with boiling water to cover for 60 seconds to loosen skins.
Immediately drain tomatoes and rinse under cold running water.
Peel, seed and chop tomatoes; reserve.
Mince garlic; reserve.
Rinse eggplant, cut lengthwise into 1/2-inch slices, then cut slices crosswise into 1/2-inch (1.5 cm) wide sticks.

title: grilled baked potatoes
directions: Wash well and dry thoroughly.
Brush with melted margarine. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Wrap well in foil.
Bake 1 hour turning every 15 minutes.
Delicious!

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients; form into 40 bite size meatballs, using a full tablespoon for each.
Brown lightly in oil.
Cover. Simmer 10 minutes.
Drain excess fat.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
In bowl, sift flour with other dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening; add buttermilk, then yeast.
Stir until flour is dampened.
Knead on floured board 1/2 minute.
Roll out 1/2-inch thickness; cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
No rising necessary.
This dough can be refrigerated and used as needed up to a week.

title: banana split pie
directions: Whip egg whites until peaks form (set aside).
Mix margarine and powdered sugar until soft.
Add whipped egg whites and vanilla.
Whip for 15 minutes.
Fill pie crust with mixture. Cover with bananas and a layer of crushed pineapple.
Cover entire top with Cool Whip.
Drizzle with chocolate syrup and chopped pecans.
Freeze until firm and serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat sugar and oil well until blended.
Add eggs and vanilla and beat.
Add dry ingredients alternately with zucchini.
Stir well.
Add raisins and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: macaroni mousse
directions: Cook macaroni in water that has been salted.
Pour milk over bread crumbs.
Add butter, pimento and remaining ingredients.
Mix all together.
Put macaroni in well-greased baking dish.
Pour mixture over bread crumbs.
Pour egg-milk mixture over the macaroni.
Bake 50 minutes in 300° oven.
Serves 6.

title: potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes until tender; drain.
Mix together with all other ingredients.
Sprinkle paprika on top if desired.

title: arroz con mantequilla
directions: Mash the garlic cloves and finely chop the peppers.
Melt butter in the pot where you wish to cook rice.
Briefly saute the garlic and green pepper in melted butter.
Add the rice and saute a bit longer on medium heat.
Add the boiling water to the rice little by little.
Stir and add salt to taste.
When the water evaporates lower the heat and cover.
When rice is cooked, add peas and fluff with a fork.
Serve hot.

title: salmon casserole
directions: Drain salmon, saving liquid.
Place salmon in center of greased casserole.
Sprinkle with black pepper.
Top with onion, green pepper and 1/3 cup of salmon liquid.
Arrange the potatoes around the salmon.
Dot with margarine and season.
Pour the sour cream over the salmon; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: dump cake
directions: Place in layers in 9 x 13-inch ungreased pan:
pineapple with juice and pie filling.
Then sprinkle cake mix and nuts.
Cut in butter pieces over the top.
Sprinkle with more nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool and top with Cool Whip.

title: cheesy potato wedges
directions: In a plastic food storage bag, combine Parmesan cheese, onion salt and paprika.
Add potatoes. Close bag.
Shake until coated. Arrange potatoes in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch microwave-safe dish. Set aside 1/2 teaspoon Parmesan.
Microwave potatoes, uncovered, on 100% power for 4 minutes.
Give the dish a half turn. Cook for 2 to 4 minutes more or until tender and hot.

title: potato soup
directions: Boil water; add vegetables, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Don't drain.

title: buttermilk fried chicken
directions: Soak chicken in buttermilk and Tabasco sauce for 15 to 30 minutes.
In a bowl, combine flour, spices and herbs.
Lift the chicken pieces from the buttermilk and drain only briefly.
Roll pieces in flour mixture.

title: cloverleaf rolls
directions: Combine shortening, boiling water, salt and sugar.
Stir well until dissolved.
When lukewarm, add well beaten eggs and yeast, softened in 1/2 cup of lukewarm water.
Add remainder of water and stir in flour.
Beat well and place in a covered bowl in refrigerator.
When ready to use, shape into balls.
Place 3 together in a muffin tin.
Let rise for 3 hours.
Bake in a hot oven for 15 minutes.
Knead down dough every day.
I use half of recipe.
They are delicious!

title: old-fashioned butter and egg pound cake
directions: Melt butter in saucepan with milk; set aside until lukewarm. Beat eggs.
Add sugar and beat.
Add flour, baking powder, vanilla and salt.
Add butter and milk mixture and beat well.
Bake in ungreased tube pan at 350° for 45 minutes.
Turn pan upside down until cool (1 hour).

title: corn fritters
directions: Beat eggs; stir in milk.
Add corn and beat in flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and oil.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil (375°). Turn to brown; drain.
Serve hot with maple syrup or sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: old fashioned jam cake
directions: Soak raisins in pineapple for several hours or overnight. Sift together dry ingredients; set aside.
In large bowl, cream butter.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Add jam and buttermilk; blend well.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix until all ingredients are combined.
Stir in raisins and pineapple mixture; add nuts.
Spread into 2 greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until cakes test done.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pans.
Cool and frost.

title: ham supper
directions: Brown ham in margarine.
Add rice with seasonings.
Drain syrup from pineapple and add water to make 2 1/2 cups liquid. Stir into skillet.
Cover and cook until liquid is absorbed.
Add pineapple.

title: spinach orange salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, toss and top with favorite Italian oil-free dressing.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Empty two cans of corn in baking dish.
Beat egg into milk in small bowl.
Mix egg and milk mixture in with corn and mix in 3/4 pack of crumbled crackers.
Press crackers down in corn with a fork.
Break rest of crackers up fine and put on top of mixture; press them down just to moisten.
Dab top with butter and salt and pepper.
Bake for about 1 hour at 350°.

title: cherry angel cake
directions: Place half of the cake pieces in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour cherry pie filling over cake.
Add other half of cake pieces. Combine pudding mix, milk and sour cream; beat smooth.
Spoon over cake and chill for 5 hours.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Arrange bacon in single layer in a 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
Microwave 6 to 9 minutes on High, or until crisp; cool. Crumble into bottom of baked crust.
Sprinkle mushrooms, cheese and onions on top.
Measure cream in 4-cup glass measure and microwave 2 to 3 1/2 minutes on High or until hot but not boiling.
Beat in remaining ingredients.
Pour over bacon cheese mixture.
Microwave 20 to 27 minutes on Medium or until almost set in center.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt together butter, peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Let cool and pour over Crispix.
Mix well.
When cooled, put powdered sugar in a paper bag.
Pour in cereal and shake well.

title: berry pie(one crust)
directions: Fill baked pie shell with berries.
In 1-quart pan, put sugar, water, cornstarch and 1 cup berries.
Cook until thick.
Add jello.
Pour over berries and chill.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Divide pastry into 2 parts and roll thin to fit on an 8 or 9-inch plate.
Set aside.
Mix apples, apple juice concentrate, thickener and spice and stir until apples are well coated.
Add lemon juice if desired to keep apples lighter color.
Taste 1 piece of apple to check spice.
Pour into pastry lined pie pan and top with second crust or pastry strips.
Seal the edges and cut slits in the top crust to allow steam to escape.
Bake at 450° for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm or cold.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cherry chiffon dessert
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Chill and serve.

title: orange punch
directions: Combine orange juice and soda.
Mix in sherbet and ice cream. Garnish with orange slices.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Cut carrots in half crosswise, then lengthwise.
Simmer, covered, in a small amount of salted water 10 minutes or to desired crispness.
Drain.
Melt butter.
Stir in brown sugar until dissolved.
Add carrots.
Cook over medium heat approximately 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: melissa's crock-pot meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in crock-pot.
Make a small well in the top of the mixture; drizzle with ketchup.
Cook on low for 7 to 8 hours.

title: hot brown
directions: Make cheese sauce by melting butter and adding flour, stirring to avoid lumps.
Add cream, stirring until blended.
Add milk; use wire whisk until thick.
Add red pepper to your taste.
Some like it hotter than others.
Place ham and turkey (heated) on bread slices; top with hot cheese sauce.
Place bacon strips and tomato slices to top and enjoy.
Very good.

title: bubble bread
directions: Place frozen rolls in greased Bundt pan.
Mix together brown sugar and pudding mix.
Pour over rolls.
Sprinkle nuts over pudding.
Spread sugar and cinnamon over nuts.
Melt butter or margarine and pour over top.
Let stand overnight.
Do not cover. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand in pan 10 to 15 minutes. Turn out on plate and serve.

title: brianne's cheese bread
directions: Slice loaf into halves.
Spread garlic spread and garlic powder to taste over entire surface of loaf halves.
Sprinkle generous amounts of shredded Mozzarella and then top with grated Parmesan and finally oregano.
Put bread halves back together and bake in tightly sealed aluminum foil in 350° oven about 15 to 20 minutes.
Do not overbake!
Unwrap foil carefully and enjoy!

title: clam dip
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together well.
Add onion and clams. Add clam juice as needed to get desired consistency.

title: shrimp and macaroni salad
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together.
Refrigerate.
Add celery and mayonnaise just before serving.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Mix Jell-O mousse as directed on package.
Bake brownies in 9 x 13-inch pan; cool.
Punch holes in top of brownies with a fork. Pour liqueur over and allow to soak in brownies (leave overnight).

title: potato pudding(kugelis - lithuania dish)
directions: Peel and grate potatoes.
Saute the onions in the butter until soft.
To the potatoes, add flour, baking powder, salt and pepper. Mix well.
Beat the eggs; add the sour cream.
Mix it and add to the mixture.
Add the onions.
Mix it well.
Bake in 400° oven for one hour.

title: bacon and cheese mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until tender and drain. Mash them, then add rest of ingredients and stir well.

title: doves for a crowd
directions: Salt and pepper each bird. Coat with flour. Brown each bird in about 1 inch Crisco. Set aside until all birds are browned. Place all in pot. Pour in enough water to let them steam. Cover and steam 1 to 2 hours on simmer. Do not let all the water steam out. Add more water if needed. When ready to serve, remove all birds and thicken pan juices for gravy.

title: mom's dill pickles
directions: Boil water, vinegar and canning and pickling salt together. Put garlic in each sterilized quart jar and dill seed or fresh dill weed with it.
Put cucumber slices in jar.
Put in a pinch of alum or teaspoon and pour boiling solution over cucumbers and seal.
Keep jars hot while filling with cucumbers by placing them in hot water.

title: pork and bean cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add eggs and oil to mixture.
Mash beans and mix with pineapple.
Add this to first mixture.
Bake in Bundt pan 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: millionaire's pie
directions: Mix pineapple with whipped topping, condensed milk and lemon juice. Add chopped pecans, if desired.

title: old-fashioned oatmeal cookies
directions: Wash raisins. Cover with water in tightly covered saucepan. Bring to a boil. Simmer until raisins are well rounded. Add more water, if necessary.
Pour 3/4 cup plus 1 tablespoon raisin liquid in measuring cup. Set aside to cool. Keep raisins covered while cooling.

title: swedish meatballs with sweet sour sauce
directions: Soak bread crumbs in cream about 5 minutes.
Mix meats together until well combined.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Shape into small balls, about 1-inch size.
Brown meatballs in skillet until well done.
Remove meatballs; drain grease from skillet and add 1 can beef broth and 1 can water. Return meatballs to broth mixture and simmer 15 minutes.
Makes approximately 40 to 45 meatballs.

title: clay(kids stuff)
directions: Cook over medium heat until it is thick and rubbery.
Let cool.

title: casa fiesta dip
directions: Layer beans in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan. Combine sour cream and taco seasoning and spread on top of beans. Next spread Cheddar cheese then top with salsa.

title: *coconut balls
directions: Cook margarine, sugar, egg and dates together until thick; stir constantly.
Cool slightly.
Add remaining ingredients; cool thoroughly.
Roll into balls or tiny rolls, then roll in Angel Flake coconut.
Store in the refrigerator.
Will keep indefinitely.

title: snack cake
directions: Mix cake mix and margarine. Spread in a 9 x 13 dish. Sprinkle chocolate chips, butterscotch chips, coconut and pecans over.
Pour Eagle Brand milk over the top. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Cool and cut into squares.

title: bagna cauda
directions: Heat oil in saucepan; add garlic and 1/4 cup cream.
Reduce heat to low; cook 1/2 hour.
Add anchovies.
Cook 3 minutes.
Add the butter and the rest of the cream and cook 5 to 8 more minutes or until slightly thickened.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve with sliced raw veggies or French bread.
Serves 8.

title: jalapeno sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook slow until onions and peppers are tender. Tomatoes can be mashed with a potato masher if you want. Pack in jars. Add salt. Seal. Place in hot water bath or pressure cooker 10 to 15 minutes.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Fill an 8-inch pie plate 3/4 full with peeled, sliced apples. Sprinkle 1/2 nutmeg and 1/2 cinnamon.
In a small bowl combine butter, sugar, flour, egg, chopped nuts and salt.
Spread over peeled apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until crust is golden brown.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Sprinkle in rice.
Add chicken, onion and salt.
Spoon soup over chicken.
Cook, covered, on High in microwave for 20 to 30 minutes, until chicken is done. Rotate dish every 5 minutes.

title: glass cleaner
directions: Mix.
