A well rinsed plastic gallon milk jug is perfect for mixing and storing this solution but be sure to mark cleaning solution with magic marker on the container and keep out of reach of small children.

title: cassoulet
directions: Brown beef cubes in small amount of vegetable oil.
At same time, cook sausage for 5 minutes, to remove some fat.
Cut sausage into small pieces and add to beef.
Add can of tomatoes until bubbly.
Pour in wine, cooking to boil off alcohol (about 5 minutes).
Sprinkle soup mix; stir well and cook slowly until meat is tender.
(If using pressure cooker, cook on high for 15 minutes and let cool down.)
Add green beans and let cook for 7 to 8 minutes.
Add cooked shells; mix well.
Cover and let stand before serving; leftovers gain flavor.

title: italian crescent casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion in skillet.
Add sauce mix and tomato sauce; heat until bubbly.
Pour into 8 x 12-inch baking dish. Sprinkle Monterey Jack cheese and sour cream on top.
Place rolls on top.
Spread melted butter and Parmesan cheese over top of rolls.
Bake in 375° oven 18 to 25 minutes.

title: cherry balls
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
Take a small amount and form around a cherry in the shape of a ball.
Roll the cherry-filled ball in graham cracker crumbs.

title: bacon cheese ball
directions: Mix together and form in shape of a ball.
Chipped beef or ham can be substituted for bacon.

title: ann's coconut candy
directions: Remove crust from bread and cut into cubes.
Place in an oblong baking dish. Pour milk over bread cubes and gently mix. Add coconut and mix gently.
Spread some coconut on top.
Put in 350° oven until coconut is lightly toasted.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: monkey bread
directions: Put cut biscuits into a plastic bag and add white sugar and cinnamon.
Shake until thoroughly coated.
Put into a greased Bundt pan.
Mix butter and brown sugar together.
Dribble over biscuits.
Sprinkle nuts over the top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: creamy italian pasta salad(makes 3 cups)
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover and chill.

title: hot cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese carefully atop range (don't scorch).
Pour in Ro-Tel; stir until well blended.
Can eat hot or cold.
Keeps well in refrigerator for days.

title: sauteed celery
directions: Wash and separate celery.
Cut crosswise at a slant, about 2 inches long and 1/4 inch thick.

title: quiche lorraine with ham
directions: Saute onion in margarine until soft.
Sprinkle drained onion and bacon over bottom of pie crust.
Add half the ham and 4 slices of cheese.
Repeat layer, using ham and cheese.

title: summer sandwich
directions: Combine all ingredients which have either been grated or finely chopped. Cucumbers should be grated on a paper towel to absorb moisture.

title: summer salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Combine mayonnaise and cider vinegar.
Toss with vegetables and macaroni.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in greased 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: michigans
directions: Mix all ingredients together before cooking.
Simmer until hamburg is done, about 1 hour.

title: susan andracke's cranberry sauce
directions: Pick over and wash berries.
Add water and cook until berries are soft.
Press through fine sieve.
Add sugar and boil another 10 to 15 minutes.
Skim off white foam.
Put in jelly glasses and cover with paraffin.

title: microwave divinity
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and water in a 2-quart glass measure or microproof bowl.

Cook on High for 12 to 15 minutes or until microwave candy thermometer registers 260° (a small amount of mixture will form a ball hard enough to hold its shape, but will remain pliable when dropped into bowl of cold water).

title: roast pork loin with shiitake and leek compote
directions: Cut leek crosswise into 1/2-inch slices and in a bowl, soak in water to cover, agitating occasionally to dislodge any sand, 5 minutes.
Lift leek out of water and drain in a colander.

title: corn chowder
directions: In large heavy saucepan, cook bacon over medium heat until it is crisp.
Transfer to paper towel to drain.
Discard all but 4 tablespoons of fat.
Add onions and celery; cook until tender. Add bay leaf and stir in flour.
Cook and stir for 3 minutes. Stir in potatoes and 5 cups water.
Bring to a boil and simmer for 20 minutes until potatoes are cooked.

title: irene's famous frozen cranberry salad
directions: Fold together and freeze.

title: quick and easy pepper steak and gravy
directions: Cook steak in oil until lightly brown.
Add enough water to cover the meat.
Cook until meat falls apart.
You may have to add a little more water.
Only add enough to cover the meat, you don't want too much water at this point. When meat is done, add Lipton mix (both pkgs), peppers, onions, and mushrooms.
Add 4 cups water. When all is done, add a few tablespoons of water to the cornstarch and mix well.
Pour into the meat.
Stir well.
If you want it thinner add more water.
If you want it thicker add more cornstarch (make sure to mix the cornstarch with a little water first).
Serve this over rice.

title: deer bologna
directions: Mix this in bowl; pour over meat and mix well.
Put in nonmetal container; use plastic.
Place in refrigerator for 3 to 4 days.
Grind again and stuff in bags.
Bake at 200° for 3 hours or a little longer; stir every 1/2 hour.

title: carlyle goffinet's raisin cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well and then add dry ingredients and beat well.
Cook the raisins and use 1 cup raisin water in the recipe.
You need to put the soda in the raisin water and dissolve.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes or until done.

title: apple butter
directions: Mix all together and add spices to suit taste.
Cook 1 to 2 hours at 350°.
Makes 6 or 7 pints.

title: recipe for a "happy day"
directions: Blend together with prayer.
Keep cool and serve generously.

title: pasties
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Add shortening, water, lemon juice and egg yolk.
Mix into each other.
Roll out 6 pasties and fill with hamburger, carrots, onions and a few potatoes.
Salt and pepper.
Add a little cream of mushroom soup. Fold over and bake at 400° for 3/4 hour.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Melt butter in heavy skillet.
Saute onions until soft.
Remove onion.
Combine flour and seasonings.
Coat meat with flour and brown on all sides.
Drain mushrooms and measure liquid.
Add liquid, Worcestershire sauce and onion to meat.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours.
Stir in sour cream and heat.
Do not boil.
Serve over hot cooked rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: low fat eggnog
directions: In large bowl, combine milk and vanilla.
In another bowl, combine pudding mix, sweetener and nutmeg.
Whisk into the milk mixture till smooth.

title: rigatoni
directions: Brown ground beef with the onion, green pepper, garlic powder, oregano, salt and pepper.
Drain well.
Add tomato juice, tomato paste and tomatoes; cook until thick.

title: amaretto cake
directions: Spray Bundt pan with Pam.
Into each crevice, place 2 maraschino cherries.
Sprinkle pecan pieces over bottom of pan.

title: chocolate cherry bars
directions: Combine cake mix, eggs and almond extract in bowl; mix well. Stir in pie filling gradually.
Pour into lightly greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake tests done.
Combine sugar, butter and milk in saucepan; mix well. Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Spread icing over hot cake.
Yield:
30 servings.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Soften cream cheese, then beat in eggs, sugar and vanilla until creamy.
In square cake pan, lay down one roll of cookie dough.
Place cream cheese batter on top, then place second roll of cookie dough on very top.
Hint:
Use flour on hands so dough doesn't stick.
For the second roll of dough, flatten on counter top and place on top like puzzle pieces.

title: boiled custard
directions: Mix together the egg yolk, milk, salt and sugar and cook in top of double boiler over simmering water until mixture will coat a silver spoon.
Gradually pour hot milk mixture over egg white and stir to mix.
Add vanilla to taste.
Serve cold.

title: zebra stripe cookies
directions: Mix flour, sugars, vanilla, margarine, salt and eggs until dough forms.
Divide dough into halves.
Mix cocoa in 1/2.
Pat or roll each half into a 9-inch square.
Cut each square into 3-inch strips.
Cut strips crosswise into halves.
Lift one brown strip half with a large metal spatula.
Place onto plastic wrap.
Top with one white strip half.
Press firmly.
Top with remaining 10 brown and white strip halves, alternating colors and pressing firmly to form into a bar about 4 1/2 inches long, 3 inches wide and 3 inches high.
Wrap in plastic wrap.
Refrigerate until chilled, 1 to 2 hours.

title: spinach roll-ups
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Spread on flour tortillas and roll up.
Put each one in plastic wrap and chill overnight. Take out 30 minutes before serving and cut into fourths.

title: cherries jubilee(microwave)
directions: Combine cherry pie filling, jelly, orange rind and rum in medium glass bowl.
Stir to blend.
Microwave on reheat for 5 to 6 minutes or until heated in center; stir.
Measure brandy into 1 cup glass measure.
Microwave on High for 15 to 20 seconds or until warm.
Pour brandy over cherry sauce and ignite.
Immediately spoon over ice cream.
Makes about 4 cups sauce.

title: frosting
directions: Mix together, then whip.
Add a few drops of flavoring (lemon is good).

title: whipping cream corn
directions: Mix all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Bake at 325 degrees until mixture thickens and is lightly brown on top.

title: linguine with garlic, oil, anchovies and mushrooms
directions: In an 8-inch frying pan, add all ingredients, except linguine. Heat until oil is very hot, then simmer slowly, stirring occasionally to break up anchovies.
Cook until mushrooms are tender (about 15 minutes).
Pour over cooked and drained linguine. Add grated Italian cheese to taste.
Great with other seafood dishes for Christmas Eve dinner.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger; let stand until cool.
Add 1/4 cup dressing, tomatoes, green pepper and onion.
When ready to serve, add crushed chips and rest of dressing.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream together butter and sugar; beat in one egg at a time. Add syrup, canned milk, flour, vanilla and chopped pecans.

title: reuben soup
directions: Combine all
ingredients,
except croutons, and heat to boiling point.
Cook
until cheese is melted, using care so as not to burn.
May garnish with croutons.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add sugar, 2 spoonfuls at a time.
Beat until stiff.
Add vanilla.
Fold in nuts and chocolate chips.

title: grandpa's popcorn balls
directions: Pick over popped corn, discarding all hard kernels.
Combine corn syrup, vinegar and salt, cooking slowly over medium heat until a candy thermometer reaches 270° or until a small quantity of the mixture dropped in cold water forms a hard ball.
Remove from heat; add vanilla extract.
Pour over popped corn, stirring constantly. Grease hands and shape lightly and quickly into balls.
Wrap in waxed paper.

title: galley hot dogs
directions: Saute onions and peppers until almost tender.
Add tomatoes. Cook until done.
Add hot dogs and tomato sauce.
Simmer about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: brown sugar upside-down bread pudding
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Sprinkle sugar over bottom of 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Butter both sides of bread.

title: carrot cake
directions: Grease and flour a 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Beat eggs and oil in small bowl. Combine flour, sugar, baking soda and powder, cinnamon and salt in a large bowl.
Add egg mixture and mix well. Stir in carrots. Pour into pan and bake 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick inserted into center comes out clean. Top with icing when cool.

title: spanish chicken noodle bake
directions: Boil chicken until tender; remove from heat.
Cool and debone. Boil noodles in chicken stock.
Saute celery and peppers in butter. Add cheese; stir until melted.
Add soup, mushrooms, olives, tomatoes and chicken.
Drain noodles and add to the chicken mixture.
Pour into a large casserole dish and heat at 350° until bubbly and heated thoroughly.

title: easy cool whip frosting
directions: Pour milk into medium bowl. Add pudding mix. Beat with wire whisk for 2 min. Gently stir in whipped topping. Spread over 13x9 cake at once.

title: chinese beef
directions: Brown meat in small amount of oil. Add all ingredients except noodles.
Place in greased casserole.
Bake, covered, for 1/2 hour, then bake, uncovered, 1/2 hour in a 350° oven.
Sprinkle with noodles and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: flank steak
directions: Place flank steak in shallow baking dish (laying flat).
Mix all ingredients together, pour over steak and refrigerate; letting it marinate all day, turning occasionally.
Barbecue or broil each side until desired doneness.
Carve diagonally into thin slices and serve with your favorite salad, crusty bread and baked potatoes. Yields 3 servings per steak.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook mixed vegetables according to package; drain.
Place in the bottom of a dish.
Mix together the onions, celery, cheese and mayonnaise.
Spread over the top of the vegetables.

title: meat loaf
directions: Beat thoroughly eggs and mix all ingredients.
Put in loaf pan with 3 strips bacon to cover top.
Pour over all 1 (8 ounce) can Hunt's tomato sauce.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together.
Combine all ingredients together and mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 1/2 package chocolate chips on top of batter.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: kuchen
directions: Cream together the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk and extract and beat well.
Spread in greased pan and cover with fruit (blueberries, apples, prunes, plums, etc.).
Fresh cranberries can be used, mixed with 1/2 cup of water and 1/2 cup of sugar, cooked until cranberries pop open, then cooled. Sprinkle with sugar and then put on crumb topping.
Bake in 375° oven for 40 minutes.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Soak bread crumbs in melted margarine.	Season hamburger with salt.
Fry	meat
and drain fat.
Layer in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with soaked bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix soup and water together.
Heat until warm.
Make a layer of potatoes and onion.
Pour half of soup over potatoes.
Repeat with the rest of the potatoes and soup.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1/2 hour.
Remove from oven, add the cheese.
Return to oven for 10 minutes or until cheese browns.

title: day pickles
directions: Put salt over pickles in the jar. Let stand for 3 or 4 hours. Shake and pour off water the salt makes. Add saccharin. Heat water and vinegar. Pour over pickles in the jar. Allow to sit in the refrigerator for 3 or 4 days. (Very good.)

title: zucchini lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut
off
stem and blossom ends, wash and slice
zucchini
into
thin slices lengthwise.	Saute beef until it loses its color;
drain fat.
Add onion, tomato, tomato sauce and water
along
with seasonings.
Simmer for 10 to 12 minutes.
In
oblong
baking
dish, layer zucchini, meat mixture and cheeses, ending with meat and cheese on top.
Bake 30 minutes or until cheese is bubbly and golden brown.

title: trudy's pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, combine yellow cake mix, apricot nectar and eggs. Blend well. Add vanilla pudding, Crisco and almond extract. Mix well. Pour in a loaf pan sprayed with Pam. Cook until done. Take out of oven and sprinkle with powdered sugar immediately. Wrap with plastic wrap.

title: nanaimo bars
directions: Mix butter, sugar, cocoa, vanilla and slightly beaten egg in bowl over hot water until smooth.
Add graham cracker crumbs, coconut and pecans to mixture and mix well.
Pat firmly into 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: super orange cake(harvey wallbanger)
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixing bowl; beat for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased pan. Cover pan with foil (you can use crock-pot.) Bake in crock-pot for 2 to 3 hours on high.
Have some water in a pan under cake if you use oven. Remove cake from oven and dust with powdered sugar or orange glaze.

title: chicken, sausage and wild rice casserole
directions: In large skillet or Dutch oven, saute sausage over medium-high heat about 5 to 10 minutes or until cooked through; drain and set aside.

title: fettuccine with chicken and sun dried tomato sauce
directions: Mix tomatoes and broth; let stand 30 minutes.
Cook mushrooms, onions and garlic in wine in a nonstick skillet over medium heat about 3 minutes, stirring occasionally until mushrooms are tender. Remove mixture from skillet; reserve.
Cook fettuccine as directed on package; drain.
Heat oil in same skillet over medium heat until hot.
Cook chicken in oil until brown on both sides.
Add tomato mixture.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 10 minutes, until juice of chicken is no longer pink when centers of thickest pieces are cut.
Remove chicken from tomato mixture; keep warm.
Mix milk, cornstarch and basil; stir in tomato mixture in skillet.
Heat to boiling; stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Stir in mushroom mixture; heat thoroughly.
Serve over chicken and fettuccine.
Yields 4 servings.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Using a pie crust cutter, combine ingredients until a dough forms.
Cover bowl and refrigerate.
After 1 hour roll dough into balls and dip into melted chocolate.
Place on wax paper to cool.

title: lemon cheese cake dessert
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick and light.
Add sugar, lemon juice and
rind.	Cook in double boiler until thick.
Dissolve gelatine in a
little
cold	water
and
put into hot mixture. Cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into yolk mixture. Grease 10-inch tube
pan
with
oil.
Cut	cake
into thirds. Alternate
filling and
cake,	starting with filling.	Chill. Turn out
on
cake plate and frost with whipped cream.
Chill until ready
to	serve. (Can
frost
with	whipped
cream and garnish with cherries or lemon wedges or slices.)

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Melt butter or margarine in large saucepan over low heat. Add marshmallows and stir until completely melted.
Remove from heat.
Add Kellogg's Rice Krispies cereal.
Stir until well coated.
Flatten out.
Press into 13 x 4 x 2-inch pan coated with cooking spray.
Cut into 2-inch squares.

title: stuffed summer squash
directions: Stem and hollow out center of squash.
Reserve pulp.
Be careful not to cut through the sides or bottom of squash.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Drain and crumble.
Saute squash pulp and onion in bacon drippings.
Remove skillet from heat.
Allow onion mixture to cool in the skillet for 10 minutes.
Add sour cream, grated cheese and crumbled bacon to the skillet.
Stir.
Stuff this combination into hollowed squash.
Pour the Chablis into a 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Place the stuffed squash carefully into the dish.
Cover with a top or foil and bake in preheated 325° oven for 45 minutes.

title: supper in a pot
directions: Brown and drain sausage, beef, onion and bell pepper.
In a boiler, mix black-eyed peas, corn, Ro-Tel and meat.
Cook until hot.
Serve with cornbread.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix and toss.
Make a day ahead.

title: creamed hamburg-cabbage skillet
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in hot fat.
Add cabbage.
Fry lightly with onion and hamburger.
Add flour and seasonings.
Blend into mixture.
Pour milk over all.
Cover.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until cabbage is tender.

title: chicken mozzarella
directions: Boil 3 whole chicken breasts until tender (approximately 15 minutes).
Remove bones and skin and cut into bite size pieces. Place in casserole dish.
Mix 1 can
cream of chicken soup with 1 cup of stock from chicken plus 1/4 cup mayonnaise.
Mix well and pour over chicken.
Add 1/2 box cheese croutons.
Mix in and top with grated Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° until light brown (approximately 25 minutes).

title: banana split cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed for 2-layer cake.

title: chili
directions: Cook onions and green pepper in small amount of oil; set aside.
Brown meat in same skillet.
In large pot, put kidney beans, water, tomato puree, salt, garlic, Tabasco and chili powder.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and add meat, onions and pepper.
Simmer until ready to serve.

title: kool-aid
directions: In a 10 ounce glass, pour liquor.
Add ice; add juice.
Shake and enjoy.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all of the ingredients together.
Pour in greased baking dish.
Brown until golden brown, about 45 minutes at 350°.

title: salsa shrimp dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and salsa with electric mixer on medium speed until well blended.
Stir in shrimp.
Serve with tortilla chips or vegetable dippers.
Makes 2 cups.

title: no bake fudge
directions: Melt butter with cocoa in saucepan.
Add peanut butter and mix well.
Add vanilla.
Add 10x sugar last.
Mix well.
Press in pan, 8 x 8-inch or 9 x 12-inch.
Refrigerate.
Cut into squares.

title: fried peppers
directions: Rinse the peppers; dry them well.
Cut the top off peppers and pull out the middle.
Clean and cut peppers into slices.
Fry them in a little oil.
When they are a little soft, cut the onion in small pieces; put them in with the peppers.
Let them cook a little, then add your can of tomato sauce, salt, pepper, oregano and basil leaves.
Stir it all together as the peppers are cooking. If pepper mixture gets a little dry, add a little water.
Cook Fried Peppers 20 to 30 minutes or until tender.

title: apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to
425°.	In a large bowl, combine apples and all dry
ingredients.
Toss
lightly
to
mix.
Turn
into pastry lined pan.	Dot with butter.
Cover with top crust; cut slits in crust.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Lay in order in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: chunky applesauce
directions: Combine apples in medium bowl.
Transfer 1/3 of apples to heavy medium sauce pan.
Add 1/2 cup water, sugar, lemon juice, cinnamon, ginger and lemon peel.
Stir mixture over medium heat until sugar dissolves.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add half of remaining apples and 1/2 cup water. Cover and simmer 10 minutes, stirring mixture occasionally.
Add all remaining apples and remaining 1/2 cup water.

Cover and simmer until all apples are tender, stirring occasionally and adding more water by 1/4 cupfuls if applesauce seems too dry, about 10 minutes longer. Can be prepared up to one day ahead. Cover and refrigerate.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: chicken ala king
directions: Brown mushrooms in butter.
Combine mushrooms, white sauce, chicken, pimiento and green pepper.
Season highly.
Cook over hot water until flavors are blended.
Add egg yolks.
Heat thoroughly. Serve in timbale cases, patty shells or on toast.
Serve at once. Yields 12 servings.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Line the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch cake pan with chopped pecans. Spread shredded coconut on top of nuts.

title: mini cheesecake tortes
directions: Place 18 vanilla waters in bottom of baking cup paper in cupcake pan.

title: butterfinger cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
In a large mixing bowl beat sugar and margarine until creamy.
Beat in egg until light and fluffy.
Blend in flour, baking soda and salt.
Stir in chopped Butterfingers.
Drop dough by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 11-13 minutes or until cookies are lightly browned.
Let stand on cookie sheet 2 minutes.
Makes about 30 cookies.

title: potato cakes
directions: Mix together potatoes, beaten egg, onion and flour.
With floured hands, make into patties.
Fry in hot oil, turning to brown on both sides about 5 minutes per side.
Makes about 10 to 12 cakes according to size.

title: rice pudding
directions: Boil the first 4 ingredients for 1/2 hour, stirring occasionally.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook 2 or 3 minutes more, stirring constantly.

title: skillet potato breakfast
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, cook bacon until crisp; drain.
Reserve 2 tablespoons drippings in skillet; set bacon aside.
Cook frozen hash browns with the onion and green peppers until golden brown. Crumble 2 slices of bacon; stir into potatoes.
Sprinkle shredded cheese on top of potatoes.
Place remaining 4 slices of bacon in a crisscross atop cheese.
Carefully bread 1 egg into each triangle formed by bacon.
Cover.
Cook over medium heat about 6 minutes or until eggs are set.
Yields 4 servings.

title: beef stew
directions: In Dutch oven, thoroughly brown meat in 2 tablespoons shortening.
Add 3 cups hot water and next 9 ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours, stirring to keep from sticking. Remove bay leaf and garlic.
Add vegetables; cover and cook 30 to 45 minutes until vegetables are tender.
Skim most of fat from liquid.
Combine 1/4 cup water and 2 tablespoons flour until smooth.
Stir slowly into hot liquid.
Cook and stir until bubbly for 2 to 3 minutes.
I like to make dumplings with this.

title: cereal peanut butter cookies
directions: Bring syrup and sugar to a boil in a large container.
Remove from heat and add 1 pint of peanut butter.
Mix well. Add corn flakes and stir well. Spoon on wax paper and let cool.

title: easy elegant hamburgers man-style
directions: Dissolve bouillion in water.
Combine with beef and add all remaining ingredients.
Mix well. Form patties.
Broil or fry.

title: baked beans
directions: Saute apple, onion and Brown 'N Serve sausage.
Add cinnamon. Add to casserole of beans.
Bake in a 350° oven until bubbly, 1/2 to 3/4 hour.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Mix sugar and butter together until smooth.
Add eggs one at a time beating after each one.
Add salt and baking soda to flour in a separate bowl.
Add vanilla to sugar and egg batter.
Add dry ingredients and sour cream alternately to batter.
Pour into a greased bundt pan and bake for 1 hour or until done.

title: lemon batter fish
directions: In
medium
bowl, mix flour, water, 1/3 cup lemon juice, egg, baking powder, salt and sugar to make batter.
Dip fish in extra lemon juice; coat with flour then the batter.
Fry in hot oil until golden brown; drain.
Serve immediately.

title: baked peaches
directions: Put drained peaches in baking dish, hole side up.
Fill holes with small dab of margarine, sprinkle of cinnamon and sugar, then a small dab of preserves.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 minutes. Good with pork or chicken and makes a pretty dish.

title: no egg gingerbread
directions: Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, vanilla and oil.
Add zucchini.
Mix and add flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add the rest.
Put into lightly greased and floured two loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: granny's date pudding
directions: Pour
cup boiling water over
dates	and
soda.
Let cool. Mix together all the remaining
ingredients
and add to dates and soda mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: sugar-free rice pudding
directions: Over a very low heat and stirring constantly, whisk together the milk and the pudding.
When blended, add rice and stir.
Bring to a soft boil.
Be sure to keep stirring or it will stick to the bottom of the pan.
Cook for the length of time specified on the pudding box.

title: canned green tomatoes for frying
directions: Slice green
tomatoes
as
thick
as
you want them for frying.
Put
them
in
a
pot
of
boiling
water. Cook until tomatoes turn
white
(only
a few seconds). Then layer tomato slices in sterilized canning jars.
Add 1 teaspoon of salt and 1 tablespoon
of vinegar to each jar.
Fill to within 1/2-inch of top
with
the
boiling water from the tomatoes.
Seal. For extra safety, process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.

title: chicken and broccoli with rice
directions: Bring water to a boil.
Stir in rice.
Cover and remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes or until all water is absorbed.
tags: Campbell's condensed cream of chicken soup

title: quick and easy chocolate mousse
directions: Combine chocolate, vanilla and salt in blender or food processor, fitted with steel knife and mix 30 seconds.
Add boiling cream and continue mixing 30 seconds more, or until chocolate is completely melted.
Add yolks and mix about 5 seconds.
Transfer to bowls and allow to cool.

title: gazpacho
directions: Heat tomato juice until boiling; add bouillon and stir until dissolved.
Cool; add other ingredients and chill several hours. Makes 4 servings.

title: asparagus sandwiches
directions: Trim crusts from bread.
An electric knife works very good for this.
Flatten bread with rolling pin.
Spread soft butter on bread.
Lay 1 spear of well drained asparagus on bread; sprinkle with cheese.
Roll, jelly roll fashion.
Place on baking sheet; drizzle with melted butter and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese. Bake in preheated oven for 15 minutes, or until just golden brown. Better if served warm.

title: steak and mushroom gravy
directions: In frying pan, cut steak into pieces.
Put flour into mixing bowl and add the salt.
Cover steak pieces in the flour.
Put into pan and only brown both sides (do not cook).
(When browning, use a little bit of oil.)

title: broiled teriyaki chops
directions: Combine teriyaki sauce, brown sugar, minced green onions and lemon juice together.

Marinate pork chops in mixture, then place in the refrigerator for 1 to 2 hours. Remove; keep marinade. Place pork chops on broiler rack. Broil 5 to 6-inches from heat for 12 to 15 minutes. Brush with marinade.
Turn once.
You'll know they are perfectly cooked when a meat thermometer inserted registers 160°.

title: spam spread(serve warm on open faced buns)
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on open faced buns.
Heat in oven.
Serve warm.

title: dustin maiden cake
directions: In mixing bowl, add flour, soda, chocolate, sugar, cinnamon, cloves, nutmeg, vanilla and salt in order given.
Add nuts, pineapple and oil.
Beat a little and bake for 30 minutes at 350°. An old family recipe everyone loves.

title: crispy-sweet pickles
directions: Slice cucumbers 1/8-inch thick.
Dissolve lime in water and cover cucumber slices.
Let stand 24 hours in refrigerator.
Rinse well and let stand 3 hours in clear water in refrigerator.
Mix well vinegar, sugar, cloves and salt.
Drain cucumbers and pour mixture over them and let stand overnight.
Bring to a boil and boil 35 to 40 minutes.
Fill jars 1/2-inch from top.
Seal and process in boiling water bath for 5 minutes.
Makes 10 pints.

title: chip dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill.

title: no cook candy
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in bowl, mixing well.
Shape as desired on wax paper.
Coat with nuts or coconut.
Store in refrigerator.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: lentil soup
directions: Add all ingredients at same time.
Cook 2 hours or until lentils are tender.
Makes 4 cups.
If desired, chopped ham may be added toward end of cooking time.

title: shrimp fettuccine
directions: Saute onions, bell peppers and green onions in butter until soft. Add flour and parsley flakes, shrimp, Velveeta cheese, half and half and garlic; mix well. Cook about 15 minutes. Boil noodles and drain. Fold noodles into the sauce. Pour into a casserole dish and bake for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°. Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: cheese-filled manicotti
directions: Cook pasta in boiling water for 10 minutes.
Drain and rinse in cool water.
Mix together Ricotta cheese, garlic, salt, bread crumbs and parsley.
Fill pasta with cheese mixture (adequately fills 8 pieces, but used sparingly can fill 12 to 14).
Arrange in baking dish and pour 1 (30 ounce) jar spaghetti sauce over. Sprinkle top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: italian sauced chicken
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Place chicken in pan and pour Ragu over top.
Cook for 1 hour at 400°.
Then top with cheese and cook for 3 minutes or until melted.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit in quarters.
Mix together cinnamon and granulated sugar.
Roll each biscuit in mixture.
Toss into greased Bundt pan.
Melt butter and brown sugar in saucepan.
Pour over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
After it is cool, everyone "picks" their pieces out like a monkey.

title: yogurt marinade(for chicken or lamb)
directions: Chicken parts or cubed meat may be marinated for 2 or 3 hours before cooking.
Mix yogurt and seasonings well.
Put meat into bowl and add yogurt dressing, coating meat on all sides.
Marinate in refrigerator.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, eggs and vanilla.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Add prunes last. Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix and pour salad oil and eggs into chopped apples.
Mix dry ingredients with apple mixture.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan or Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven or until done.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Sift dry ingredients together; cut in shortening with pastry blender.
Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup warm water.
Add alternately with buttermilk to dry ingredients; mix well.
Roll out 1/4-inch thick on floured board; cut with biscuit cutter.
Dip on one side in melted butter.
Fold in half and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake immediately, or keep covered in refrigerator and bake as needed.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Yields 4 dozen.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Beat together Butter and Cream Cheese.
Beat in Sugar, Egg, and Vanilla.
Combine Flour, Baking Soda, and Salt.
Add to butter and cream cheese mixture.
Chill 1 hour.
Shape into 1 inch balls. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Make an indention with thumb. Fill with Preserves.
Bake in 350 oven for 10 - 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool on rack.
Yields:
approximately 48 cookies.

title: butternut cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter until it is fluffy or like ice cream. Add eggs one at a time.
Add with flour, beating good after each egg, then flour addition.
Add vanilla and nut meats.
Cook in well-greased and floured tube pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed.
Bake in greased Bundt pan or 2 waxed paper lined round cake pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ruby preserves
directions: Weigh together the strawberries, raspberries and cherries. Add equal weight of sugar to fruit; boil for 25 minutes.
Add the lemon juice; boil for 2 minutes.
Add the red food color.
Pour into sterile pint jars.
Seal and process for 5 minutes in boiling water bath.
Makes 6 1/2 pints.

title: crab dip
directions: Put butter and cheese in double boiler over boiling water. When melted, add crab and horseradish.
Mix well.
Serve in chafing dish with mild crackers.

title: rumaki
directions: Marinate
and chill chicken livers in mixture of listed ingredients
for
at least 4 hours.
Roll chicken liver with a slice
of
water chestnuts in half a bacon slice.
Secure with toothpick. Roll in brown sugar.
Broil until browned.

title: homemade seasoned croutons
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut bread into medium-sized cubes, dry in the oven on a cookie sheet for 5 minutes.
Melt margarine and saute garlic until soft.
Place bread cubes in a large bowl.
Pour melted margarine over cubes and add remaining ingredients.
Toss well.
Return to the oven on cookie sheet and bake for about 3 minutes, until lightly browned.
Serve cooled croutons on salads or soups.
Store in a covered container in the refrigerator.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute in frying pan margarine and onion.
Mix together in large bowl eggs, whole corn plus juice and creamed corn.
Add muffin mix.
Add margarine and onion; mix well.
Pour into 2-quart buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti in boiling water until tender and drain.
Cook onion and pepper in oil until tender.
Add tomato, salt, pepper and sugar.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and mix with spaghetti.
Add 1/2 of cheese.
Sprinkle top with remaining cheese. Bake at 375° until cheese has melted or turns brown.

title: watergate salad(pistachio salad)
directions: Mix jello into pineapple with juice; whip in Cool Whip, nuts and marshmallows.
Chill.
Yields approximately 12 servings.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops; drain.
Layer pork chops and uncooked rice in baking dish.
Sprinkle with seasoning.
Pour over tomato sauce and water.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Melt butter in small pan with garlic, salt and pepper.

Place shrimp in shallow baking pan tightly, touching one another. Pour butter sauce over and bake in preheated 375° oven about 15 minutes or until water has evaporated. Brush butter sauce over shrimp occasionally.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt butter and cocoa together.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar and eggs; mix well.
Add flour, salt, nuts and vanilla; mix well.
Spoon batter into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Sprinkle marshmallows on top of warm cake.
Cover with Chocolate Frosting.

title: horseradish cheese spread
directions: Melt cheese in the top of a double boiler. Remove from heat. Stir in mayonnaise and horseradish. Pour into a small crock-pot or ceramic bowl. Chill. Serve with crackers. Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: south-of-the-border vegetable mix
directions: Saute onion and green pepper in oil in a Dutch oven 2 to 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 8 to 10 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Makes 8 servings.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Mix ingredients with spoon.
Bake in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottoms only of 12 medium muffin cups, 2 1/2 x 1 1/4-inches or line with paper baking cups.
Beat milk, oil and egg.
Stir in flour, sugar, baking powder and salt, all at once, just until flour is moistened (batter will be lumpy). Fold in blueberries.
Divide batter among muffin cups.
Sprinkle with sugar if desired.
Bake until golden brown, 18 to 20 minutes. Immediately remove from pan.
Makes 1 dozen muffins, 195 calories per muffin.

title: press 'n bake cream cheese crust
directions: Combine cream cheese and butter.
Blend well.
Stir in flour. Refrigerate about 1 hour.
Remove from refrigerator and press into bottom and sides of 9-inch pie pan.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Combine pineapple, sugar and flour.
Sprinkle Cheddar cheese over top.
Cover with cracker crumbs, mixed with melted butter. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken and rice dressing
directions: Place chicken breasts in bottom of baking dish.
Mix the first 4 ingredients together and pour over chicken.
Cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: crustless egg custard
directions: Melt butter in iron skillet.
Mix together in a bowl the sugar, flour, milk, vanilla and eggs.
Pour in skillet and bake in oven for 45 minutes at 325°.
Turn out of skillet on a plate.

title: apple dip
directions: Combine cream cheese, brown sugar and vanilla until smooth. Slice apples and dip into dip.

title: korean braised short ribs
directions: Trim fat from ribs; place in shallow dish.
Mix remaining ingredients; pour over beef.
Cover and refrigerate for 24 hours, turning occasionally.
Drain beef, reserving marinade.
Cook in 4-quart Dutch oven over medium heat until brown; drain.
Pour marinade over beef.
Cover and cook in 350° oven until tender, about 1 hour.
Serve with rice.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: oyster crackers
directions: Combine Hidden Valley mix and oil; add remaining ingredients. Place crackers in large bowl; pour mixture over crackers, stirring to coat.
Place on cookie sheet in warm oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pink fruit freeze
directions: Mix ice cream and cream cheese.
Add 2 cans of fruit cocktail, Miracle Whip and fresh strawberries.
Mix well.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch dish.
Put in freezer overnight.
Cut in squares.
In a bowl, enough strawberries for each sugar.
Add a little powdered sugar; mix well before putting on squares.

title: meatball-vegetable skillet dinner
directions: Soak bread crumbs in evaporated milk.
Put meat in bowl; add 1 teaspoon salt, pepper, nutmeg, onion and milk mixture.
Mix well and make into small meatballs.
Roll meatballs in flour.
Melt shortening in electric frying pan; brown meatballs.
Add vegetables and water.
Sprinkle 1/2 teaspoon salt and pepper to taste.
Cover and cook until vegetables are tender, about 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: ugly duckling pudding cake
directions: Blend all ingredients except brown sugar and nuts in a large mixing bowl. Beat 4 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan. Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until cake pulls away from sides of pan.
Do not underbake.
Cool 15 minutes. Spoon hot butter glaze over warm cake.

title: microwave shrimp cream cheese dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in 1-quart microwave casserole dish. Cook on High for 2 to 3 minutes or until warm, stirring once during cooking time.
Stir; serve with crackers or chips.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Mix thoroughly the shortening, sugars, egg and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet. Bake 10 minutes.
Immediately remove from baking sheet.
Yields 3 dozen cookies.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Cream sugar and butter together. Add flour, vanilla and egg. Put drained fruit in bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan. Pour topping over fruit. Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill about 2 hours before serving.

title: ricotta-red pepper pasta
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain well. Meanwhile, combine red peppers and 1/2 cup Ricotta into blender; puree until smooth.
Transfer to large serving bowl.
Stir in remaining Ricotta, parsley, oregano, salt, pepper, garlic and lemon peel.
Add hot pasta and toss well.
Makes 4 servings.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Grease casserole with margarine.
Cook potatoes with skins on in salt water; cool and peel.
Shred coarsely on grater.
In saucepan over low heat, combine cheese and 1/4 cup margarine, stirring occasionally until almost melted.
Remove from heat; blend in sour cream, onions, salt and pepper.
Fold into potatoes and turn into 2-quart greased casserole.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: french toast sticks
directions: Cut each slice of bread into 5 sticks.
Beat flour, sugar, salt, milk and eggs until smooth.
Dip bread into mixture and drop in hot oil until brown.

title: chocolate butter frosting
directions: Melt margarine, cocoa and milk together.
Beat in sugar and vanilla.

title: festive holiday meatballs
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, onion, garlic, parsley, eggs, salt and pepper in large bowl until well mixed.
Shape into 1-inch balls and brown in butter or margarine over medium heat.
Remove from skillet and set aside.

title: cream cheese tarts
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Pour this mixture over upside-down wafers in muffin pan to 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool!
Top with cherry pie filling!!

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place half of bread in bottom of casserole.
Combine diced chicken, onions, celery, pimentos and salt and spread over the bread.
Place remaining bread over chicken mixture.
Mix mayonnaise, milk and eggs together and pour over casserole.
Chill overnight.

title: taco pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Brown meat, onion and green pepper in large skillet; drain grease.
Add tomato paste, water and taco seasoning mix.
Stir; let simmer for 10 minutes.
Spray a 9-inch pie pan with Pam.
Flatten biscuits to cover bottom and sides of pan.
Layer 1/2 the meat mixture and 4 ounces of cheese.
Repeat. Bake for 15 minutes, or until crust is done.
Let stand about 5 minutes before serving.

title: swedish rye bread
directions: Pour boiling water over 1st 7 ingredients.
Stir well and cool to lukewarm.
Crumble yeast into mixture.
Stir until yeast is dissolved.
Add 6 cups of flour.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Mix in rye flour with hand.
Add enough white flour to make soft dough.
Mix well.
Let dough rest for 10 minutes.
Knead until smooth and elastic.
Place in a greased bowl.
Punch down and let rise again. Punch down and divide into 5 or 6 loaves.
Cover and let rise again until almost double.
Bake in 350° to 360° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chicken with oranges and snow peas
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Slice chicken into 1-inch slices.
Heat 3 tablespoons orange juice in frying pan, add chicken.
Saute for 5 minutes.
Combine soup mix, water and remaining orange juice in a large casserole.
Add chicken, water chestnuts and oranges; bake, uncovered, 20 minutes.
Add snow peas and bake for 5 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Boil 4 cups of water.
Place tea bags in boiling water; remove from heat and set aside for 10 minutes.
Remove tea bags.
Add 1 cup water, sugar and cloves.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; add all juices.
Mix well.
Serve warm.
Makes 1 1/4 gallons.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix together sugar, shortening and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, to mixture.
Beat together well.
Sift together flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Add to shortening mixture and mix well.
Drop cookies onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake for approximately 10 minutes.

title: coffee cake
directions: Blend these ingredients together well before mixing batter.

title: philippine chicken(low calorie)
directions: Place chicken in shallow baking pan.
Mix all other ingredients; pour over chicken.
Bake at 325° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: crock-pot smothered steak
directions: Put steak strips, flour, salt and pepper into crock-pot.
Stir well to coat the meat.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook on high for 1 hour, then turn down to low and cook for 8 hours.
Can be cooked in 5 hours on high.
Serve on rice or noodles.

title: jacobsburg brew
directions: Bring to boil in enameled pot.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Layer asparagus and peas in casserole.
Pour mushroom soup; flavor with onion and condiments over vegetables.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: bell pepper casserole
directions: In a casserole, place the mixture of bell peppers, cracker crumbs and Zippy Cheddar cheese.
Over this mixture, pour the milk and dot with butter.
Place in a 400° oven and bake for 35 minutes.

title: easy lasagna(do not cook lasagna noodles)
directions: Brown ground beef; drain fat.
Add sauce; cook until hot.
Add 1/2 to 1 cup of water to sauce until sauce is runny.
In a large mixing bowl, combine cheeses, egg, garlic salt, pepper and parsley.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease two 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pans.
In a large bowl with fork, mix flour, sugar, walnuts, marshmallows, chocolate chips, raisins, baking powder and salt. In medium bowl with fork, beat eggs slightly.
Stir in salad oil, zucchini and lemon peel. Stir liquid mixture into flour mixture just until flour is moistened. Spread evenly in pans.
Bake bread 1 hour.
Cool in pans on wire racks for 10 minutes. Remove from pans.

title: three-minute fudge
directions: Mix milk, sugar, salt and cocoa in a pan.
Heat to boiling over low heat.
Boil and stir 3 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add marshmallows, vanilla and nuts. Stir until marshmallows are melted.
Pour into pan.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: breaded pork chops
directions: Shake ingredients in a medium plastic or paper bag.
Dip 4 pork rib or loin chops (1/2 to 3/4 inch thick) into 1/4 cup of milk. Shake each in pork coating mix, coating both sides.
Cook on rack in shallow roasting pan in 425° oven until done and brown, 30 to 35 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except crackers and margarine together. Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix crackers with melted margarine.
Spread this on top of vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: eggs-tremely good dip
directions: In a food processor, combine juices, mustard, mayonnaise and Tabasco.
Add eggs and blend until smooth and fluffy.
Add seasonings and cheese.
Blend until smooth.
Spoon into a bowl and top with parsley.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: creamy coleslaw
directions: Chill cabbage thoroughly.
Shred fine.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over cabbage.
Mix lightly.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Makes 6 servings.
(I usually double the recipe as people go for seconds.)

title: "old timey" caramel frosting
directions: Mix sugar and milk.
Cook until it forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat. Add butter and vanilla. Cool slightly.
Beat until spreading consistency.
Requires much beating.

title: marinated vegetables
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate.

title: hot cabbage soup
directions: Cut up cabbage.
Put water in cabbage.
Add diced and pureed tomatoes and bacon bits.
Add red pepper seeds as desired.
Cook on high until it starts to boil.
Turn down heat and cook 1 hour.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Wash and clean 8 big yams.
Boil yams until soft. Drain water from yams and add butter, sugar and milk.
Mash everything together.
Put in casserole dish and add marshmallows. Put in oven until marshmallows are melted.
Take out and serve.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Refrigerate for several hours before serving.

title: brown glazed chicken wings
directions: Wash and pat dry chicken wings.
Cut into 2 parts at the joint.
Place wings in large, shallow baking pan.
In a small saucepan, put soy sauce, vinegar, honey, sugar, garlic and ginger. Stir until blended.
Heat until sugar and honey dissolve.
Pour this on the wings.
Marinate for 2 hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Turn and baste occasionally.

title: white christmas pie
directions: In saucepan, combine 1/2 cup sugar, flour and salt. Gradually stir in milk. Cook over low heat until boils 1 minute. Remove from heat and stir in gelatine. Beat until smooth. Cool. Blend in flavors. Fold in whipped cream (already whipped) and carefully fold in meringue, then coconut. Put in baked pastry shell and sprinkle top with coconut. Garnish with maraschino cherries, if desired.

title: hot fruit bake
directions: Layer fruit in a 2-quart casserole dish and set aside.
Melt butter in a small saucepan.
Combine sugar and cornstarch; stir into butter.
Gradually stir in sherry.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and smooth.
Pour over fruit, cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Place the margarine in saucepan.
Add hamburger; cook until browned.
Add all other ingredients; simmer for 25 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients into bowl.
Make well in center; add remaining ingredients at once.
Mix until smooth.
Grease and flour 3 loaf pans (fill 1/3 full).
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until done.

title: blueberry gems
directions: Combine flour and sugar and set aside. Combine eggs, vanilla, oil and milk. Pour over dry ingredients and mix well. Fold in blueberries; stir just until mixed. Spoon batter into greased muffin pans or cupcake holders. Fill half full. Bake at 375° for approximately 25 minutes. Makes about 2 dozen muffins.

title: spaghetti and meatball
directions: Meatball:
Thoroughly mix the first 7 ingredients; form into 1 large ball.
Bake in a greased pie tin in a 350° oven for approximately 1/2 hour, until lightly browned and firmly set.

title: mom's stuffed mushrooms
directions: Wash mushrooms and remove stems.
Melt 3/4 stick butter; add onion and chopped mushroom stems.
Cook until onion is clear. Remove from heat and cool.
Add beaten egg and bread crumbs to make stuffing.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Stuff caps and put on foil lined cookie sheet.
Melt 1/4 stick butter and pour over top. Cover tightly with foil and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: hamburger bean soup
directions: Place beans in large soup pot.
Heat to boiling and boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and let stand for 1 hour.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix sugar and flour.
Pour butter over the mixture.
Add egg yolks and peaches.
Pour in pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix ingredients together in a bowl and chill.
After chilled, roll into a ball and roll in chopped nuts.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Brown onion in butter.
Add soup, milk, broccoli and Velveeta cheese.
Add cooked rice.
Bake casserole 20 minutes at 350°.

title: lions club catfish
directions: Cut catfish into strips (2 to 3 to a fillet).
Sprinkle Louisiana hot sauce on fish until it becomes a pale pink. Sprinkle celery seed over mixture.
Sprinkle all-purpose flour very lightly; work into mixture.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Mix eggs, cheese, noodles, margarine and milk (keep a little cheese for topping).
You can add a little more milk so it won't be dry.
Top with margarine.
Bake 1 hour or until brown at 350°.

title: cream of mushroom soup
directions: Saute mushrooms in 2 tablespoon butter; set aside.
Saute scallions; set aside.

title: terrebone jambalaya
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in casserole. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Stir occasionally. Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Fry bacon till crispy.
Cut broccoli and cauliflower to bite size pieces and mix in bowl.
Mince onion and mix cheese and onion and chopped bacon into vegetables.
Mix mayo, sugar and vinegar into creamy sauce, pour over vegetables and coat.
Yummy!!

title: brownies
directions: Put egg whites in large bowl.
Beat with spoon until slightly frothy.
Add oil and vanilla, then mix and stir in sugar and cocoa.
Mix again.
Stir in flour and salt.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken rice-a-roni casserole
directions: Prepare Rice-A-Roni according to instructions on box.
In very large baking dish or bowl, mix rice, chicken, sausage, soups and onion.
Put mixture into 1 or 2 baking dishes.
Prepare stuffing according to instructions on box; spread on top of chicken mixture.
Sprinkle cheese on top of stuffing.
Bake at 350° in preheated oven until heated through.
This recipe makes enough to freeze 1 casserole, if desired.

title: seafood newburg
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour and seasonings.
Add cream gradually and cook until creamy and thick.
Stir constantly.
Stir in egg yolks and seafood.
Cook over low heat until hot.
Serve on toast.

title: tijunana hot dish
directions: Brown beef and onion; add stewed tomatoes, tomato sauce, green chili peppers, taco seasonings and olives.
Simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Place 1/4 cup of meat mixture in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Place the tortillas side by side on meat mixture; top with more meat mixture and then grated cheese.
Repeat layers until all gone.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: oreo fudge pie
directions: Spread ice cream in crust; top with fudge sauce.
Freeze until firm, about 6 hours.
Put Cool Whip topping and bite size cookies on top.

title: miniature reubens
directions: Arrange bread slices on large cookie sheet.
Bake 5 minutes at 350°.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Spread each with mixture of mayonnaise, chili sauce, horseradish and green pepper.
Top each slice with some corned beef, sauerkraut, then cheese, cutting corned beef and cheese slices to fit.
Bake about 10 minutes more or until cheese is melted.
Serve immediately.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: chicken and spaghetti
directions: Heat oil.
Add chicken, onion and carrots.
Stir-fry until vegetables are tender.
Stir in next six ingredients.
Simmer, covered, for 5 minutes.
Serve sauce over hot spaghetti.

title: foolproof dark chocolate fudge
directions: In heavy pan, over low heat, melt chips with the Eagle Brand condensed milk.
Remove from heat; stir in nuts and vanilla. Spread evenly into waxed paper lined 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Chill 2 hours or until firm.
Turn fudge onto cutting board; peel paper off.
Cut into squares.
May store loosely in covered container in refrigerator or room temperature.

title: sugar cookie
directions: Cream first 4 ingredients; add eggs and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda and tartar together.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Roll in balls, flatten with glass dipped in sugar. Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Makes 10 dozen.

title: pecan pie
directions: Blend together with mixer.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 70 minutes until set.

title: ten bean soup
directions: Hash beans.
Place beans in large kettle and cover with water to 2 inches deep.
Add salt.
Soak overnight.
Drain next day and add 2 quarts of fresh water.
Add ham hocks or ham.
Bring to a boil and simmer slowly for 3 hours.
Add onion and tomatoes. Season with chili powder, lemon, salt and pepper.
Remove ham meat from bone and return to soup.
Simmer slowly for 1 hour or more. Serve with salad and crackers.

title: apple meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Pack into a greased loaf pan, 9 x 5 x 3-inches.
Bake in a moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: buckeye balls
directions: Combine first four ingredients.
Form balls and chill.
Melt bark.
Dip balls in bark and place on wax paper to harden.
You may freeze.

title: oatmeal zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine yogurt, brown sugar and applesauce.
Beat in eggs.
Combine dry ingredients and fold into egg mixture.
Stir in shredded zucchini.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Brown bacon in a skillet; then pour off most of grease. Remove bacon and cook onions in grease.
Then add green beans, bacon, onions and sweet and sour sauce.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: georgia barbecue sauce
directions: Combine oil, onion and garlic in saucepan.
Cook until the onion turns yellow and transparent, but not brown.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer for 45 minutes.
Use to baste either chicken or pork.
Makes enough for 2 chickens or one pork loin.

title: cookies
directions: Melt butter, peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Pour over cereal.
Shake in bag with powdered sugar.

title: lentil soup
directions: In a Dutch oven add all ingredients except mustard and simmer covered 1 hour or until lentils and vegetables are tender.
Stir in mustard.
Remove and discard bay leaf before serving.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: molly hogan's
directions: Separate eggs; beat whites stiff.
Combine egg yellows, sugar, vanilla, lemon concentrate and orange juice.
Add one fifth gin and beat.
Add egg whites last.
Combine 1/3 cup of mix, ice and 7-Up.

title: cranberry salad 2
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water.
Add other ingredients and chill.

title: company mashed potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients together.
Place in a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 250° for 15 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Put in sliced apples.
Cover with brown sugar and lemon juice.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt; add beaten egg and mix until crumbly.
Cover apples with this mixture.
Drizzle melted oleo over all.
Sprinkle cinnamon on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: children's play dough
directions: Put
the dry ingredients into an electric skillet.
Set the skillet at 400°.
Add the liquid ingredients and stir with a wooden spoon.
Cook the mixture 7 to 8 minutes or until the dough pulls
away
from the pan.	Turn dough onto counter and knead
as it cools.
Add food coloring.
Store in an airtight container until ready for use.
This is great fun!!

title: lemon dessert
directions: Make or buy a graham cracker crust.
Mix together pie filling, Eagle Brand milk, drained fruit cocktail and pudding.

title: oat bran muffins
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Spray muffin pans and bake at 400° for 14 minutes.

title: corn flake bars
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Cook until smooth and starts to boil. Remove from heat and add corn flakes.
Put in buttered 13 x 9-inch cake pan.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: easy lasagna bake
directions: Brown ground
beef;
drain.
Add sauce, water, salt and sugar; cook
together
several
minutes.
Using
a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer 1/3 sauce, 1/2 spaghetti, 1 cup cottage cheese and 1/3 Mozzarella.
Repeat,
ending with sauce and cheese.
Cover with foil;
bake
at
350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Remove foil; let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: zucchini dish
directions: Cook, peel, slice Zucchini.
Cover bottom baking dish with croutons.
Layer of Zucchini, 2nd croutons, cover with undiluted celery soup.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350.

title: nacho cheese dip
directions: In a large skillet, fry sausage and ground beef together. Melt cheeses, on low heat, in slow cooker.
Add sausage/beef mixture to melted cheeses.
Add Ro-Tel tomatoes and cream of mushroom soup to mixture, stirring often.
(Do not get cooker too hot, cheese will scorch.) When dip is completely mixed, serve with nacho chips. (Keep slow cooker set on low while serving to keep dip warm.)

title: chicken nachos
directions: In saucepan, combine cheese and 1/2 cup sour cream.
Stir until cheese melts.
Add cooked chicken and chiles to cheese mixture until heated.

title: basic sourdough starter
directions: Feed me (sourdough) every Wednesday and Saturday or I will die. Do not use me the same day you feed me.
Take out what is needed before feeding.
Never let the dough get down to less than one cup.

title: fluffy banana cake
directions: Beat on No. 8 speed on your mixer until fluffy and mixture will hold its shape, about 3 minutes.

title: fried cabbage noodle dish
directions: Cut bacon slices crosswise into small pieces and brown in skillet.
Do not drain bacon grease.
Cut up onion and cabbage and add to bacon and drippings.
Cook, covered, until cabbage is cooked thoroughly; add pepper, stir or turn frequently with spatula.
Cook noodles until tender.
Drain and mix with cabbage mixture.
Serves 6. Can freeze.

title: skinny soup
directions: Bring all to a boil except the cabbage, then simmer until vegetables are almost done.
Then add cabbage and simmer until it's done.
You can add any other fresh vegetables that you want. Can be frozen.
Contains 0 fat and is low sodium.

title: fruit bowl
directions: Mix all ingredients together and chill. Serve cold.

title: date and nut cookies(icebox cookies)
directions: Sift flour.
Measure and sift with baking soda and cream of tartar.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and milk.
Add dry ingredients, dates, nuts and flavoring.
Mix thoroughly and form into loaf.
Chill overnight.
Slice thin and place on well greased baking sheet.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 10 minutes or until delicate brown.
Makes 100 cookies.

title: fantastic chicken
directions: Cut up dried beef.
Lay in bottom of ungreased baking dish. Wrap one piece of bacon around each chicken breast half. Place in baking dish on top of dried beef.
Mix soup and sour cream together.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 300° for 2 hours.
Serve with rice.

title: mona's mexican dish
directions: Brown ground beef.
Drain fat and set beef aside.
In saucepan, over medium heat, combine Ro-Tel and chili.
Butter or spray Pam cooking oil in bottom and sides of a 9 x 13-inch cooking dish.

title: breading pudding
directions: Cut top crust of bread slices and arrange in a 9 inch baking dish and set aside.
Whip together eggs and sugar.
Then add in milk and vanilla.
Pour over bread and then sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken in water until done, about 1 hour.
Remove from liquid and cut in chunks.
Mix chicken and soups; put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Make Stove Top according to directions.
(I use broth from chicken instead of water.) Spread on top of mixture and bake at 375° for 40 minutes.

title: shrimp jambalaya
directions: In large skillet, saut chopped onion, bell pepper and parsley in butter. Add Ro-Tel tomatoes, onion and cream of mushroom soup to the mixture. Stir in uncooked rice and season to taste (salt and pepper). Add shrimp and crabmeat to the mixture and mix well. Pour all into a greased 9 x 13 baking dish. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Stir after 30 minutes and finish baking.

title: candied pecans
directions: Place pecans in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Heat in 250° oven for 5 minutes.
In a 2-quart saucepan, melt margarine over medium heat.
Stir in corn syrup, 1/4 cup of the sugar and cinnamon. Stirring constantly, bring to boil over medium heat.
Boil, without stirring, 5 minutes.
Pour syrup over pecans, stirring constantly to coat evenly.
Bake in 250° oven, stirring several times; immediately spread out on greased cookie sheets.
Cool slightly. With 2 forks, separate pecans.
Cool completely.
Store in tightly covered container.
Makes 3 cups.

title: jerry duncan's meat loaf
directions: Mix together and shape into a loaf.
Put in loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 2 hour.

title: party salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 2 cups water.
Add the marshmallows.
After Jell-O starts to set, add sliced bananas and crushed pineapple (drained); allow to set.
Cook together until thickened the sugar, flour, egg and combined pineapple juice and water to equal 1 cup. After mixture cools, add 1 package whipped topping and spread over set Jell-O.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top.

title: lemon pie bars
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Add sugar, flour, lemon juice and lemon rind.
Pour over crust.
Bake 20 more minutes at 325°.
Cool and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut into squares.

title: venison in mushroom gravy
directions: Combine flour, salt, pepper, onion and thyme; coat venison. Melt butter; brown the venison.
Place in baking pan.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together and cover chicken or beef for a great barbecue flavor.
Makes 1 cup.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed on box. Brown sausage. Mix all ingredients together. Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: baked artichoke and cheese dip
directions: Heat oven to 375°. In a 10-inch skillet, melt 1 tablespoon butter until sizzling; stir in onion, red pepper and garlic. Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are crisply tender, 1 to 2 minutes. In a 2-quart saucepan, melt remaining 3 tablespoons butter; stir in flour. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and bubbly, 30 seconds. Stir in milk. Continue cooking, stirring occasionally, until mixture comes to a full boil, 2 to 3 minutes. Boil 1 minute. Remove from heat. Stir in cream cheese, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese until melted. Stir in 1/4 cup parsley, mayonnaise, lemon juice, artichoke hearts, pepper and lemon peel. Stir cheese mixture into sauted vegetables. Pour into shallow 1 1/2-quart ovenproof casserole. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly. Sprinkle with remaining 1/4 cup parsley. Serve with French bread or crackers.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Combine egg white, cornstarch and soy sauce.
Stir in pork cubes to coat.
Combine Bisquick and water and stir into pork mixture.
Fry each cube in deep oil. Drain and set aside.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: pecan honey graham cookies
directions: Place graham crackers on a cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Boil butter, oleo and sugar 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour butter sauce over graham crackers and bake at 350° for 6 minutes.
Let cool.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and pour into graham cracker crust.
Freeze until firm; keep in freezer until ready to serve.

title: breakfast burrito
directions: Melt margarine in large nonstick skillet over medium heat. Add potatoes and chili powder. Cook potatoes until tender, stirring occasionally.

title: homemade chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, salt, cocoa, sugar, milk and egg yolks.
Heat in double boiler on medium heat until thick.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and butter.
Pour into browned pie crust; top with meringue or Cool Whip.

title: ginnie's scintillating soup
directions: Brown ground beef and drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Let simmer until all vegetables are cooked.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Thoroughly mix the ingredients, then add 1 1/2 cups of hot applesauce (unsweetened) in which you have dropped 2 teaspoons of soda.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a tube pan.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Combine thawed potatoes, 1/2 cup melted margarine, onion, soup, sour cream and cheese.
Place in buttered 2 1/2-quart casserole.
Drizzle melted 1/4 cup margarine over corn flakes. Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: virgie's crumb cake
directions: Blend
margarine,
brown sugar, white sugar and flour to crumbs and
reserve
cup for the top.
To the remainder, add sour milk, soda, cinnamon, eggs and salt.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Sprinkle 1
cup
of
chopped
pecans in pan. Pour in cake batter,
sprinkle
reserved
crumb
mix
over top. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: italian delight
directions: Boil and blanch spaghetti.
Fry meat until brown.
Remove from pan; fry onion and green pepper slowly in grease until tender. Mix all ingredients; add to spaghetti.
Salt to taste.
Mix well. Put into greased baking dish.
Sprinkle top with grated cheese. Bake at 350° for approximately 1 hour.

title: never fail dumplings
directions: Mix flour, salt, shortening, egg and broth (or water).
Stir well. Roll out thin on well floured surface. Let dry 15 minutes. Cut into strips and drop in slow boiling broth.

title: quick and easy salad
directions: Mix cottage cheese, dry Jell-O and pineapple well.
Add Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix vanilla wafers, orange juice and sugar together and roll in small balls.
Then roll in coconut or can be rolled in pecans or powdered sugar.

title: granola
directions: Mix.
Add oil mixture to oatmeal; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Stir after 15 minutes.

title: gracious oatmeal patties
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Add enough water to work up and form into patties.
Flatten patties to about 3/4-inch thick; fry in skillet with about 1/2 inch vegetable oil, until golden brown.

title: hot biscuits and pancake mix
directions: Mix together flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Using a pastry blender, cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Store in a well-sealed container in the pantry or fridge. When making biscuits, use 1/3 cup milk for every cup of mix.
For pancakes, add enough liquid for the batter consistency desired.

title: frozen strawberry pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in graham cracker crust and freeze.
Enjoy!

title: whipping cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add flour to creamed mixture alternately with whipping cream, beginning and ending with flour.
Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: homemade tortillas
directions: Combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Work in shortening, then add water, working into a large ball.
Break into small balls (about 24) and roll flat on floured surface.
Heat on both sides, then they are ready to eat.

title: marinated chicken
directions: Mix first five ingredients; add chicken and toss.
Refrigerate 30 minutes.
Broil or grill chicken on rack 6 inches from heat for 30 minutes or until done.
Turn and brush often with sauce.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook noodles or macaroni.
Drain.
Warm peas, soup, tuna, milk and bouillon cubes.
Add drained macaroni or noodles.
May garnish with bacon bits and/or minced onions.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Break up 3 slices of bread in greased casserole. Saute lightly, mushrooms, celery and onion. Mix with mayonnaise and spread over bread. Cover with the next 3 slices of bread and beat eggs and milk together and pour over top. Let stand overnight. Cover with mushroom soup, grated cheese and bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: meat and potato pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie plate with one crust.
Mix ingredients together except hash browns.
Lightly pat into pastry-lined pie plate.
Top with hash browns.
Place top crust on; seal and flute edge.
Prick with fork.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes until browned.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fajitas
directions: Warm tortillas.
Cook beef, pepper and onion until tender. Drain and add dressing mix.
Place meat mixture in center of tortilla roll.
Serve on lettuce topped with all trimmings.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix peanut butter, sugar and margarine.
Form into 1 inch balls.
Place on a cookie sheet and chill for a few minutes. Melt chocolate chips and paraffin in double boiler.
Dip each ball into chocolate. Keep chocolate at low temperature while dipping them.

title: onion soup
directions: In heavy pan, melt butter.
Add onions and cook slowly, stirring occasionally, until golden.
Sprinkle on flour and stir a few minutes to cook the flour.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add in broth, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and let simmer, partially covered, for 30 minutes.

title: pimiento cheese spread
directions: Melt cheese and milk in double boiler.
Add remainder of ingredients; mix well.
Refrigerate.
May be used as a dip or spread for sandwiches.

title: mildred's eclair cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, water, vegetable oil and eggs. Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes (test with toothpick until done).

title: mushroom quick chicken*
directions: In a bowl, combine eggs and milk; whip until light and frothy. Put flour in a shallow dish.
Melt the butter in a frying pan on medium heat; do not let butter burn.
Dip chicken in egg/milk mixture, then lightly coat with flour and brown both sides in buttered skillet (fry approximately 5 minutes on each side).
Place chicken on paper towel to drain.

title: pig pickin' cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well with electric mixer.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes; cool.
Frost with Filling.

title: hamburger delight
directions: Generously grease 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or baking dish.
Brown beef and drain well.
To beef, add mixed veggies and mushroom soup (no water!).
Stir well.
Add water to Bisquick to a spreadable consistency.
Place in pan banking higher on outside edges next to pan to form small roll higher than middle.
Add meat mixture on top of Bisquick layer, then bake approximately 400° for 20 minutes.
Add cheese on top of meat mixture.
Return to oven and cook until cheese melts.

title: holly wreaths
directions: Melt marshmallows and margarine, add vanilla and green food coloring. Remove from stove, add corn flakes and stir until coated. Drop by spoonful on wax paper and put 3 red hots on each wreath.

title: apple salad
directions: Cook beaten egg, sugar, pineapple juice and cornstarch until thickened.
Let cool, then pour over apples, pineapple and marshmallows.
Mix and refrigerate.

title: corn bread
directions: Melt stick of butter in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine all other ingredients together and pour into pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Chop nuts.
Melt butter, let cool.
Add fruit, 1/2 cup at a time.
Beat eggs and mix all together.
Pour into a 9-inch pie crust.
Set on a cookie sheet and bake 40 minutes in 300° oven. Let cool before cutting.

title: tuna apple raisin salad
directions: Drain tuna.
Dice apples.
Add apples and raisins to tuna. Add mayonnaise, salt and pepper to taste.

title: microwave southern pralines
directions: Combine sugar, half and half and salt in a deep glass bowl, mixing well.
Blend in oleo.
Microwave on High, 10 minutes, stirring once.
Stir in pecans.
Cool 1 minute.
Beat by hand until creamy and thickened, about 4 to 4 1/2 minutes.
The mixture will lose some of its gloss.
Drop by the tablespoonful onto waxed paper.
Makes 2 to 2 1/2 dozen.

title: chocolate swirl cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In the top of double boiler over hot (not boiling) water, combine chocolate and 1/2 cup of sugar.
Heat until chocolate melts and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat; set aside.
In a small bowl, combine graham cracker crumbs, 2 tablespoons of sugar and butter.
Mix well.
Pat firmly into a 9-inch spring-form pan, covering bottom and 1 inch up sides.

title: potato and meat balls
directions: Mix hamburger meat, salt, pepper, sage and eggs thoroughly. Roll into meat balls and fry in deep fat until golden brown. Remove from grease and place in large pan.
Peel potatoes and cut into quarters.
Boil in salt water until about half done.
Remove from heat and place potatoes between meat balls.
Take water in which potatoes were cooked and part of fat in which meat balls were fried.
Pour over meat balls and potatoes.
Place in oven and bake at 450° for about 30 minutes or until potatoes are brown. Remove from oven and serve.

title: pepperoni ritz
directions: Place crackers on a cookie sheet.
Then add pizza sauce, one pepperoni and a little Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: rice-broccoli casserole
directions: Fry onion in the oil.
Add the chopped broccoli, milk, Cheese Whiz and soup.
Salt to taste.
Cook for 3 minutes, add the cooked rice and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix crushed (finely) vanilla wafers and butter.
Line bottom of large spring pan.
In mixer combine cream cheese and sugar #8. Continue by adding eggs slowly one at a time.
Add sour cream and vanilla and continue mixing until mixture is smooth.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
(Do not open oven.)
Shut oven off and leave in oven 1 more hour.
(Do not open oven during 2 hour period.)
Best if chilled overnight.

title: orange balls
directions: Mix all ingredients except coconut.
Roll into balls.
Roll in coconut.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Mix together and let stand in refrigerator 2 hours.
Add more or less milk for desired consistency.
Enjoy.
Makes 3 (1 cup) servings.

title: chicken and rice bake
directions: Grease bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Spread cooked rice as a bottom layer. Mix soups and milk; heat and pour over rice. Place chicken pieces on top of soup mixture. Sprinkle dry onion soup over chicken pieces. Cover with foil. Bake at 325° for 2 hours.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix yolks and milk.
Combine flour, sugar and cocoa.
Pour all into top of double boiler.
Cook, stirring constantly,
to keep from lumping.
Cook until very thick.
Pour into baked shell.
Use whites from eggs to make meringue.

title: banana cake
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar until fluffy. Add eggs.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add bananas.
Beat 2 minutes.
Set aside.
Sift flour, soda and salt.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk and vanilla.
