Beat well.
Stir in nuts.
Turn into two lightly greased 9-inch round cake pans. Sprinkle batter with half the coconut.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove cakes from pan and cool, coconut side up on wire racks.

title: beef stew(servings:  8)
directions: Sear meat in fat; add all except carrots and potatoes.
Cook 1 1/4 hours.
Add carrots and potatoes and cook 30 minutes.
Serve with hot cornbread.
Excellent warmed up.

title: funnel cake
directions: Beat together the eggs, sugar and milk.
Sift dry ingredients and then add to egg batter.
(Batter needs to be mixed until smooth.)
Heat skillet to 375° and pour batter into funnel.
Swirl batter from funnel into skillet.
Fry on one side until golden brown, then turn over and fry on the other side.
Remove from skillet and sprinkle powdered sugar on both sides of cakes.
Makes about 30 cakes.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Preparation 20 minutes.
Let stand 1 hour and 10 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Cool and put in refrigerator overnight.
Sprinkle cheese over top. Cover with cracker crumbs.
Melt margarine; pour over top of cracker crumbs.
Heat on 450° until brown.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form a ball or log and roll in pecans.
Chill until ready to serve with your favorite crackers.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix together, oil and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a tube cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: my mother's gingerbread
directions: Sift flour with soda, salt and spices.
Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add beaten egg and molasses.
Add sifted dry ingredients and hot water alternately.
Beat until smooth.
Pour into well-greased, floured pan.
This gingerbread may be reheated to serve hot for dinner.
Bake in a 10 x 14-inch pan in a preheated 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions; drain.
Beat eggs and soup together.
Stir in mayonnaise and onion.
Add broccoli.
Pour into a greased casserole dish; top with buttered crumbs and grated cheese.
Cover with foil and bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
When prepared in advance, sprinkle on crumbs just before heating to avoid a soggy topping.

title: spanish rice
directions: Combine in a large saucepan and bring to a boil.
Add 1 cup rice; cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes.

title: millionaire fudge
directions: Mix sugar, margarine and milk in a large heavy saucepan. Bring to a boil and cook for 10 minutes, stirring constantly, until soft ball stage is reached.
Remove from heat and add chocolate chips.
Stir until chocolate melts; add marshmallow cream and pecans.
Stir well.
Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.

title: lemon bars deluxe
directions: Sift together the first 2 ingredients; cut in butter until mixture clings together.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned (approximately 20 to 25 minutes).
Put eggs, 2 cups of granulated sugar and lemon juice in blender; blend until thick and smooth.
Sift 1/4 cup flour and baking powder. Add to blender; blend to combine.
Pour over crust.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Cool; cut into bars.
Makes 30 bars.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Blend shortening and sugar in bowl.
Add eggs, one at a time, blending well after each addition.
Stir in combined dry ingredients.
Add sour cream and flavoring, mixing well.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes or until cake tests done.
Do not open door during.

title: chicken croquettes
directions: Melt butter.
Blend in flour, salt and milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until smooth and thick.
Add chicken, onion and parsley.
Spread in an oiled, shallow pan.
Chill thoroughly.
Divide into 8 portions.
Shape into logs.
With a fork, lightly beat the eggs.
Dip the croquettes in egg mixture and then in crumbs.
Fry until golden brown, 3 to 5 minutes, in cooking oil heated to 365°.
Drain on absorbent paper.

title: spiced tea
directions: Combine both concoctions and simmer a few minutes.
Serve hot or iced.
Lasts more than a week in the refrigerator.

title: baked parmesan chicken
directions: Combine cheese, flour and seasonings.
Dip chicken in combined egg and milk.
Coat with cheese mixture.
Place in baking dish. Pour butter over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Drain corn; save liquid.
Add milk to liquid to measure 1 cup. Melt butter.
Add flour, salt and pepper.
Blend.
Add liquid; cook until
thickened.
Remove
from
heat.
Add corn. Slowly add beaten
eggs.
Put
in
greased
baking
dish.
Put crumbs and paprika on
top.
Put baking dish in shallow pan of water.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: hello dolly cookies
directions: In a 9-inch pan, melt margarine.
Spread graham cracker crumbs, coconut and nuts.
Pour on top Eagle Brand milk.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: marinated mushrooms
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, lemon juice, honey, onion, mustard, paprika, celery seed and salt in bowl.
Mix well.
Whisk in oil and add mushrooms.
Marinate in refrigerator overnight.

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat eggs well and add milk.
Mix flour and sugar; add to milk and eggs.
Stir thoroughly.
Cook and stir until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour over wafers and bananas.
If desired, cover with meringue and brown in oven.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender. Stir in flour, salt and pepper (to taste). Add milk and cheese. Cook until thick and bubbly. Cook and stir 1-2 minutes more.

title: shrimp-cucumber appetizer spread
directions: In a mixing bowl, stir together the cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Stir in the catsup, mustard and garlic powder.
Stir in the chopped shrimp, cucumber and onion.
Spread over melba toast.
Garnish with additional shrimp and cucumber if desired.

title: crockpot roast beef
directions: Brown meat and put it in a large crockpot.
Add the rest with enough water to make thin gravy.
Cook on high for several hours or all day.

title: 24 hour cole slaw
directions: Cut cabbage and carrot on grater, chop onion and pepper small. Place in covered container.

title: plum pound cake
directions: Grease tube pan, cut paper for bottom and grease again.
Dump all ingredients together and mix.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool in pan 10 minutes.
Turn cake out and immediately glaze with 1 cup powdered sugar, mixed with lemon juice.
May be served plain, cold or hot.
Freezes well.

title: poached apple rings
directions: Put first 4 ingredients in skillet or shallow saucepan.
Stir thoroughly.
Place over heat and simmer 5 minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Allow cheeses to soften at room temperature.
Combine with remaining ingredients; blend until smooth.
Refrigerate about 30 minutes.
Shape into ball.
Roll in chopped nuts, if desired. Serve as spread for crackers.
Yield:
about 3 cups spread.

title: ranch yeast biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar and oil.
Mix flour, baking soda and salt together and add alternately with buttermilk to mixture.
Roll out on floured surface and cut into biscuits or drop by spoonful.
Does not have to rise, but they are better if left to rise 15 to 20 minutes.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream Crisco with white and brown sugar.
Add beaten eggs; mix well.
Add 1 cup peanut butter.
Add salt, baking soda and flour. Roll in your hands in little balls and place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Pat each cookie on top (flatten) with a fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: chocolate spiders
directions: Mix peanuts and noodles together.
Melt chocolate and pour over noodles and peanuts.
Add marshmallows and stir.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on waxed paper until chocolate sets.

title: cabbage dinner
directions: Brown the onion and ground beef. Steam the cabbage until limp. Place cabbage in buttered baking dish. Layer with onion and meat. Alternate cabbage and onion. Top with tomato soup.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: adobo
directions: Put ingredients in a pan and bring to a boil.
Lower heat to medium until chicken is tender and cooked (approximately 15 to 20 minutes).

title: 8 layer salad
directions: In a large glass bowl, layer ingredients in order; cut or tear lettuce.
Layer celery, eggs, peas, green pepper, green onion, mayo and sprinkle with sugar.
Be sure all edges are sealed.
Top with layer of fried crumbled bacon.
Cover salad with plastic wrap or foil and refrigerate at least 12 hours before serving.

title: pineapple macadamia cake
directions: Cook over medium heat. Spoon over cooled cake.

title: rolled round steak
directions: Sprinkle tenderizer and seasonings on the meat.
Lay bacon and onions on the steak.
Roll steak jelly roll style and place skewers in several places to hold all together.
Brown steak. Cover and bake at 325° until fork-tender.
Thicken juices over meat, not all juice or as thick as gravy.
Served best with baked potato.

title: baked chicken chimis'
directions: Combine chicken, picante sauce, green onions, cumin, oregano, chilies and tomato sauce.
Brush one side of tortilla with melted butter.
Spoon 1/3 to 1/2 cup chicken mixture on unbuttered side of tortilla.
Top with cheese.
Fold sides over, ends down.
Place seam down in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 450° for 13 minutes or until crisp and golden brown.
Serve with sliced lettuce, tomatoes and olives along with guacamole or sour cream.

title: rice and shrimp casserole
directions: Mix rice, celery, meat, eggs and lemon juice. Fold in mayonnaise and soup.
Place in greased casserole dish. Top with onion rings or bread crumbs or add last 10 minutes as they tend to get too brown on top. Bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes until bubbling hot. Serves 6.

title: sausage and pinto beans
directions: Cut sausage into 1-inch lengths and brown in an iron skillet. When completely brown, drain off excess fat.
Add beans, onions, bell pepper, Mrs. Dash and chives.
Rinse bean cans with a little water and add to beans.
Bring to a boil, then lower heat and simmer about 1 hour.
Stir often.
If mixture begins to stick, add a little more water.

title: french onion soup
directions: Slice onions.
Melt butter in a 4-quart Dutch oven.
Slowly cook onions in butter until lightly browned, about 20 minutes. Add bouillon cubes, water and wine to onions.
Cover and simmer 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add Worcestershire sauce, salt and white and black peppers to soup, stirring until blended.
To serve soup, place a thin slice of French bread into the bottom of each individual ovenware serving bowl.
Ladle soup into bowls.
Top with layer of shredded cheese.
Place under broiler until cheese melts.
Serve at once.

title: belgian mayonnaise
directions: Place the egg yolks in a bowl with a pinch of salt and prepared mustard. Beat with a wire whisk until well mixed and slightly thickened.
It will take just a second or two.

Pour on a couple of drops of oil. Beat until mixed before adding more, drop by drop at first, increasing gradually until you are pouring a thin stream of oil. Beat hard and fast; the mayonnaise will get quite thick. When you have added about half the oil, add a little vinegar, just a few drops, which will thin down mayonnaise. Add more oil, a little more vinegar, and finish with oil always beating hard. When are are sure mayonnaise is getting fluffy and creamy, you can switch to an electric beater. Taste and season the mayonnaise well with salt and pepper and more vinegar, if necessary. The mayonnaise should be creamy.
Makes approximately 1 1/2 cups.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Press meat into pan. Spread onions over that. Spread undiluted soup over that. Place Tater Tots to cover the whole top and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until well done.

title: hamburger hot dish for 100
directions: In a large frying pan, brown hamburger and onion in small batches.
Drain off fat.
Put batches in large roaster.
Cook spaghetti in 10-quart kettle or do in batches according to directions on package.
Drain and rinse in cold water. Add to hamburger. Add all other ingredients, mixing well.
Stir occasionally until heated through.

title: mamma's happy birthday, anniversary and wedding cake(by dom deluise)
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Slowly add egg yolks to egg whites, one at a time.
Then add sugar and vanilla.
Add baking powder to flour and gradually add to the other ingredients and mix well.
Pour half the batter into each 9-inch square or round baking pan, both of which have been lined with wax paper.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes .
Remove from pan, cool on rack. Remove wax paper (it peels off easily).

title: all-american apple pie
directions: Combine sugar, flour, spices, salt and lemon juice. Add apples.
Toss to mix.
Put half the apple mixture into 2 (9-inch) unbaked pie crusts; pack well.
Dot with butter.
Add remaining apples.
Bake at 400° for 50 to 60 minutes until apples taste done.

title: icing
directions: Get a medium size bowl.
Put the powdered sugar and the butter in it; mix them up with a spoon, then put in the milk and mix.
If you want, put food coloring in your icing.

title: florida pecan pie
directions: Combine the first 7 ingredients in a large bowl. Beat at medium speed until well blended. Stir in chopped pecans. Pour filling into the pie crust. Top with pecan halves. Bake at 350° for 55 minutes to 1 hour. Serve with whipped cream. Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: shrimp fettucini
directions: In food processor combine first 5 ingredients.
Transfer to saucepan and stir over medium heat until smooth and warm.
Add shrimp, salt and pepper; stir and simmer 1 to 2 minutes.
Serve over fettucini.
Makes 4 servings., 474 calories, 3.4 g fat.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Add salt.
Beating constantly, add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time. Beat until stiff peaks form and sugar is dissolved.
Gently stir in vanilla and chocolate chips.

title: lemon fluff
directions: Place cottage cheese in a large bowl.
Sprinkle dry gelatin over the top; stir until mixed.
Stir in whipped topping and marshmallows.
Gently stir oranges into the cottage cheese mixture.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: sweet pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers and
onions.
Mix
with other ingredients and cook (uncovered) for 30 minutes on medium heat.
Pour into hot jars and seal.

title: gourmet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skins; cool.
Peel and shred coarsely.
In saucepan over low heat, combine cheese and 1/4 cup butter, stirring occasionally, until almost melted.
Remove from heat and blend in sour cream, onions, salt and pepper.
Fold in potatoes and put into greased 2-quart casserole.
Dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake 25 minutes at 350° or until heated through.
Serves about 8 people.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Stir up and bake in greased and floured pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: the thing
directions: Mix butter, yellow cake mix,
pecans and 1 egg together real well.
Put and pat in 9
x	12-inch
pan real well.
(Put hand in warm water and pat).
Mix
eggs, powdered sugar and cream cheese together with mixer and
pour over cake.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add soup, water, Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Heat through, stirring often.
Serve on buns.

title: katherine hepburn's brownies(these are the best!)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Melt unsweetened chocolate and butter or oleo over very low heat in a heavy saucepan.
Remove from heat and stir in granulated sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Quickly stir in chopped walnuts, 1/2 cup all-purpose flour and salt. Spread batter in a well-greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.
Cut when cool.

title: stir-fried asparagus
directions: Cut asparagus in 3-inch diagonal pieces.
Fry in hot oil, stirring frequently until well coated.
Add salt.
Continue frying for 3 minutes or until tender-crisp.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Cut tomatoes into 1/4-inch slices.
Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge tomato slices with this mixture.
Place in heavy skillet, containing hot bacon drippings.
Fry slowly until brown, turning once.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: sailor's slop
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in skillet.
Boil water and cook noodles.
Heat chili beans, corn and spaghetti sauce.
Mix all ingredients together and simmer for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 6; to make for large groups, just increase quantity.

title: muffins
directions: Mix ingredients.
Pour into greased muffin pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
You may add fruit, about 1/2 to 1 cup.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt margarine and pour over confectioners sugar.
Add peanut butter, coconut and crumbled graham crackers. Cream.
Roll into balls.
Melt chocolate or peanut butter chips and paraffin wax in double boiler.
Remove from stove.
Dip balls into mixture.
Lay on wax paper.

title: cheese dip
directions: Combine butter, chilies, tomatoes and onion.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add Velveeta cheese.

title: swiss green beans
directions: Boil beans until tender and set aside.
Blend remaining ingredients.
Cook until tan in color.
Add 1 cup sour cream, stirring all the while.
Add 1/2 pound Swiss cheese, grated, to the sauce.
Put beans, drained, into a baking dish.
Cover with cheese sauce and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli au gratin
directions: Cook broccoli in boiling water until crisp-tender; drain well. Spoon broccoli, pimiento and celery into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine soup, sour cream and salt.
Pour over broccoli mixture.
Bake in a preheated 325° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Top with combined cheese and bread crumbs.
Return to oven until cheese begins to melt.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: egg and spinach dinner
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Melt 3 tablespoons margarine in large skillet.
Add first four ingredients and mix well.
Cover and simmer 3 minutes.
Remove cover and raise heat.
Cook, stirring, until all moisture has evaporated.

title: orange slice candy cake
directions: Roll dates, nuts and candy in 1/2 cup flour.
Mix all the other ingredients and then add dates, nuts and candy.
Pour in Bundt pan and bake at 250° for 2 hours.

title: gooey german chocolate cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Spread in a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix next 3 ingredients together and spread over top.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes.

title: ghivetch
directions: Preset oven to 350°.
Place all veggies in shallow greased baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Mix up.
Put bouillon in small pan. Add olive oil, garlic and rest of the spices.
Pour over veggies.
Cover tightly with foil and bake 1 hour and 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Parmesan Chicken and Ghivetch make a very elegant company dinner for 8 or 10.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine sour cream, cream cheese and seasonings.
Mix well. Stir in Cheddar cheese and crabmeat.
Cover and chill 2 hours. Sprinkle with paprika.
Serve with crackers.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach as directed on box; reserve 1/2 cup liquid.
Melt butter, add flour and stir until smooth.
Add onion; cook until tender.
Add liquids and stir until smooth.
Slice the cheese (use 1/2 of the roll if you don't want it too hot).
Add seasonings, stir until cheese is melted.
Add the spinach and stir until mixed thoroughly.
Pour into a casserole dish; top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Best if made the night before.

title: green rice
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter. Add Cheez Whiz and soup. Add cooked rice and slightly cooked broccoli (chopped fine).
Put in casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pizza meatballs
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; mix well. Cover each cheese cube with about 1 tablespoon meat mixture, carefully sealing all around.
Place meatballs in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Place pizza sauce in a large pot. Cook over medium just until boiling.
Add meatballs. Stir gently and cook until heated through.
If desired, serve on a bed of lettuce and garnish with mushrooms.
Makes 6 servings.

title: 20 minute cake
directions: Heat water, oleo and cocoa to boiling.
Combine flour and sugar and add to boiled mixture, then add remaining ingredients. Bake in sheet pan at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: stir-fry chicken and vegetables
directions: In wok or large frying pan, heat 1 tablespoon oil.
Add frozen vegetables with 1 tablespoon garlic salt and stir frequently until cooked.
Remove from wok or pan.
Add remaining oil, boneless chicken, garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Stir frequently until cooked.
Add cream of mushroom soup with half can of water.
Stir well, then add into cooked chicken.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Serve over white rice.
tags: cream of mushroom soup or cream of chicken soup

title: pasta al pesto
directions: Drop pasta into salted boiling water and cook until al dente, just tender.
Drain pasta in colander.
Toss with pesto, cheese and pepper to taste.
Serve hot with extra Parmesan cheese on the side.

title: skillet beans
directions: In skillet cook onion and green pepper in oil until tender but not browned.
Stir in remaining ingredients, cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: pepper relish
directions: Grind peppers, apples and onions all together.
Mix vinegar, sugar, salt and spices.
Let come to boil.
Add ground mixture and boil 10 minutes.
Put into sterilized jars and seal.

title: mild cheddar cheese ball
directions: Soften cheese to room temperature.
Blend all ingredients except pecans.
Shape into round ball and roll in pecans.
Serve with your favorite wheat crackers.
It may be made in advance of a party several days.
It keeps well in the refrigerator wrapped in wax paper.

title: watermelon rind pickles
directions: Peel and remove all green and pink portions from melon.
Cut into 1-inch cubes and soak overnight in salt water.
Drain, cover with fresh water and cook until almost tender.
Drain.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Place all ingredients, except nuts, in a bowl.
Microwave at High dial until chocolate chips, etc. are melted together, 3 to 5 minutes, stirring once or twice during cooking.

title: applesauce bread or muffins
directions: Bake in 325° convection oven for 25 minutes for muffins and 1 hour for loaves.
Yield: 250 muffins; use #14 or #16 scoop or 10 loaves of bread.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Sift next 5 ingredients and add to mixture.
Stir, then add walnuts and raisins.
Bake 1 hour at 275° if you have a colored Bundt pan; if not, 300° in a greased and floured pan.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Place green beans in a baking dish.
Combine all remaining ingredients in a saucepan, except for cheese.
Heat over medium heat for about 15 minutes and pour over green beans.
Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 can Parmesan cheese and dust with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, until bubbly.

title: rum broiled bananas
directions: Preheat broiler.
Place bananas in a single layer in an ovenproof baking dish.
Sprinkle bananas with lemon juice.
Pour rum over bananas.
Sprinkle bananas with brown sugar and dot with butter.
Broil 4 inches from heat until bananas are lightly browned and very tender, about 6 minutes.
Serve hot from baking dish.

title: potato burgers
directions: Mix onion and potato. Add salt and hamburger.
Mix well. Shape into patties.
Brown on one side in skillet.
Turn.
Pour tomato juice over patties. Cover and cook 35 to 40 minutes on low heat.
Can be fixed on grill, leaving tomato juice off.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: flaky pie crust
directions: Stir oil and mix all at once into flour.
Make into ball and divide in two.
Roll each ball between 2 sheets of wax paper. Remove top sheet of paper and turn crust into pan.
Remove other paper.
Fill pie.
Roll other ball in same manner and cover pie. Press edges together.

title: chili tortillas
directions: Make milk gravy, but do not brown.
Add tomato sauce, chili beans and peppers.
Saute hamburger meat.
Salt and pepper to taste; drain.
Warm flour tortillas in microwave.
Lay tortillas flat on serving plate.
On half of it, put a layer of meat, onion and grated cheese.
Fold; cover with sauce and top with lettuce and tomato.

title: oven baked bass fish
directions: Season fish with lemon pepper and Mrs. Dash.
Dredge in corn meal.
Spray aluminum foil with Pam.
Place in oven at 350°.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Take out and sprinkle with paprika, lemon juice and sweet basil.
Use a little squeeze oleo.
Cook until brown and tender, about 25 minutes.

title: oslo kringle
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients like pie crust.
Pat into cookie sheet (ungreased) in 2 strips, 3 inches wide and as long as the sheet.
Put water in saucepan with butter.
Heat to boiling point. Remove from heat and add flour, all at once; immediately stir until smooth (using wooden spoon).
Stir in 1 egg at a time and beat well after each addition; add flavoring and spread on top of first mixture.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: poppy seed bread(cake)
directions: Mix
together all the ingredients.
Pour in greased and floured loaf pans (2) and bake 50 minutes in a 350° oven.
For smaller
loaves,
reduce the oven temperature.
Cool 5 minutes and glaze.

title: chocolate fudge pudding
directions: Combine granulated sugar, flour, 2 tablespoons cocoa, baking powder and salt in mixing bowl.
Add nuts.
Stir in milk, oil and vanilla; spread into an 8-inch square pan.
Mix brown sugar, 1/4 cup cocoa, salt and hot water.
Pour over unbaked batter.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: melt-in-your-mouth chicken pie
directions: Mix soup and broth in casserole dish.
Add chicken, eggs and vegetables with salt and pepper; set aside.
Mix milk, butter and flour well.
Do not beat.
(Batter will be lumpy.)
Pour batter over chicken mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: hamburger helper zesty italian
directions: Brown ground beef in 10-inch skillet; drain.
Stir in uncooked macaroni, sauce mix and hot water.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Uncover and cook until desired consistency.
Makes 5 servings (1 cup each).

title: lorna doone cake
directions: Melt margarine. Crush cookies and mix together. Press into 9 x 13 pan. Mix pudding, milk and ice cream together and pour over cookies. Cover this with 1 container of Cool Whip. Top with crushed candy bars. Put in refrigerator for 2 or 3 hours before serving.

title: fillet roll-ups
directions: Saute scallops (which have been chopped fine) in oil with onion, parsley and seasonings for 1 minute.
Mix in cracker crumbs. Spread evenly on each fillet, then sprinkle grated cheese; add a few drops of lemon juice over dressing.
Roll each fillet, jelly roll fashion.
Skew with toothpicks.
(These may be cut after being rolled, making two roll-ups out of each.)
Dot each with butter. Place on a cookie sheet lined with foil.
Cover lightly with foil and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 10 minutes.
Remove foil and cook another 10 minutes or until fish flakes easily when touched with a fork.
Serves 6.

title: sesame christmas cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Blend in almond extract and salt. Add flour.
Mix well.
Shape dough in balls.
Roll in sesame seed. Place on cookie sheet and flatten slightly.
Fill with jam.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and press in bottom of a medium pizza pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Mix mayonnaise, cream cheese, garlic powder, dill weed and onion.
Spread over cooled crust.
Top with thinly sliced vegetables; cucumbers, radishes, green peppers, tomatoes, etc.

title: easy beef stew
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, in a baking dish with lid.
Mix tomato soup and water.
Pour over ingredients and cover.
Put in a 325° oven and bake
for 3 hours or until done.

title: spring macaroni salad
directions: Cook spring macaroni according to package directions.
Rinse and cool.
Place in large mixing bowl.
Add diced onion, celery and green pepper to cooled macaroni.
In a saucepan, combine sugar, hot water and vinegar.
Stir until the sugar dissolves. Place mayo and turmeric in a medium sized mixing bowl.
Stir until smooth.
Add the sugar, hot water and vinegar mixture to the mayo mixture.
Mix well.
Pour over the macaroni mixture in the large mixing bowl.
Stir well.
Refrigerate 24 hours.
Stir once or twice before serving.

title: mexican chocolate coffee
directions: In 1-quart measure, combine 1/2 cup water with all ingredients except milk.
Microwave on High for 2 to 3 minutes until chocolate melts and mixture is smooth, stirring once.
Add milk to measure; stir to combine.
With vented cover, microwave on High for 3 minutes until heated through.
Stir before serving. Makes 4 servings.
May use whole milk if preferred.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Pour water off canned beans.
Put in oblong pan.
Sprinkle some onion rings over beans and mushrooms.
Mix a little water with soup and pour over beans.
Put rest of onion rings on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: avo-taco pie
directions: In a large fry pan, brown beef and onion; drain fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, taco mix and olives.
Separate crescent dough in 8 triangles.
Place triangles in ungreased 9 or 10-inch pan.
Press to form crust.
Sprinkle 1 can corn chips over crust.
Spoon meat mixture over crust and chips.
Spread sour cream over meat mixture; cover with cheese.
Sprinkle remaining chips.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes until crust is brown.
Serve in wedges topped with lettuce, tomato and avocado slices.

title: 6 weeks bran muffins
directions: Add soda to boiling water and cool.
Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and soda mixture.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Spoon into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Keep remaining batter in an airtight container in refrigerator; do not stir.
Will keep 6 weeks.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in 3 cups boiling water.
Stir in pineapple and juice along with the relish.
Pour into two 13 x 9-inch pans and refrigerate.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: In 9 x 13-inch cake pan, put in rhubarb and sprinkle with sugar and package of strawberry Jell-O.
Mix cake mix according to directions and pour over rhubarb.
Bake at 350°, approximately 55 minutes.
Serve with whipped topping or ice cream.
Serves 12 to 16 people.

title: sauerkraut with pork(kapusta z zeberkami)
directions: Cover spareribs with cold water and bring to a boiling point. Skim. Add onion, sauerkraut and caraway seed.
Simmer, uncovered, for 2 hours or until meat is tender. Add no salt.
The brine in the sauerkraut is salty.

title: patti's biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients, shortening and milk.
Knead through with hands.
Roll out and cut with round cookie cutter or another shape of your choice.
Bake at 450 degrees for 12 - 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter and oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat first 3 ingredients until fluffy. Add 1/4 cup corn syrup, egg, water and vanilla.
Mix until smooth. Stir in combined dry ingredients.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press into 2 1/2-inch circles. Bake 9 to 11 minutes or until golden brown. Cool 1 minute. Remove to wire rack. Cool completely.

title: garden chicken salad
directions: Pour boiling water over rice and onion in 2-quart bowl.
Cover with foil and let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in dressing and remaining ingredients and mix lightly.
Serve on lettuce if desired.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cobbler
directions: Melt butter; set aside.
Mix remaining ingredients except for fruit.
Pour into butter.
Put fruit on top of batter mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: no-bake cheese cake
directions: Roll vanilla wafers into crumbs.
Stir in melted margarine. Press into pan.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Preheat broiler.
Place potatoes in a large saucepan.
Add milk and water to cover.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes until soft.
Drain potatoes, reserving cooking liquid.
Place potatoes in food processor or blender.
Add butter, brown sugar, granulated sugar and cinnamon.
Process until well blended.
Thin with reserved cooking liquid, if necessary. Pour mixture into 9-inch square glass baking dish.
Sprinkle marshmallows over potatoes mixture.
Broil 8 inches from heat source for 1 minute until marshmallows are lightly browned.

title: microwave pickle chips
directions: Mix sugar, vinegar, mustard seed, celery seed and turmeric. Pour over cucumbers and onion.
Do not cover.
Microwave 4 minutes on High.
Stir and repeat 4 minutes on High.

title: hasty pudding
directions: Place in cake pan 1 cup brown sugar, boiling water and butter. Make a batter of remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonfuls into mixture in pan.
Bake about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: flaky pie crust
directions: In medium bowl, mix flour and salt.
Add shortening with pastry blender or two knives.
Mix until like coarse oatmeal. Quickly sprinkle ice water, one tablespoon at a time, tossing lightly with fork after each addition and pushing dampened portion to side.
Sprinkle only dry portion remaining in center of bowl. Pastry should be just moist enough to hold together, not sticky. Flour board.
Roll out for one 9-inch pie shell.

title: ambrosia shake
directions: Mash bananas until smooth and creamy; beat in orange juice, honey, salt and vanilla.
Add milk; beat well and chill.
Makes 6 servings.

title: german chocolate cake mix cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients. Blend well.
Drop dough by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes or until set.
Cool 1 minute and remove from sheet.
Makes 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: pizza burgers
directions: Brown ground chuck.
Drain off grease.
Add pizza sauce and bring to a slow boil.
Break American cheese into pieces; add to meat mixture.
When cheese melts, stir and set aside to cool.
Put meat mixture on a bun.
Sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top of meat mixture.
Wrap each sandwich in foil; reheat at 350° for 15 minutes or until hot.

title: broccoli quiche
directions: Layer into 10-inch deep pie dish (sprayed with nonstick spray) the broccoli, small onion (diced fine) and Swiss cheese.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry bacon and drain.
Break up in pieces.
Mix everything together and bake 2 hours at 325°.
Stir occasionally.
(Can slice bacon after freezing, then fry and drain.)
Serves 6 to 8.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch dish for this recipe.
For the first layer, dissolve 1 package jello in 1 cup boiling water.
Add 1 small package strawberries, 2 sliced bananas and 1/2 can crushed pineapple; mix well.
Chill until firm.
Spread sour cream over congealed layer.
For the second layer, repeat the directions for the first layer.

title: marinated beans
directions: Drain all beans; mix together with other ingredients and chill.

title: chocolate oat bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass).
Combine flour, oats, brown sugar and butter.
Set 1/2 cup aside and press the rest firmly down and bake 10 minutes.
Pour milk evenly over crust. Sprinkle nuts and chocolate morsels on and press down and bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: bundt bread
directions: Melt margarine in Bundt pan.
Sprinkle cheese and oregano over margarine.
Place biscuits in pan without separating them.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Invert onto plate or into basket. Pull apart and serve while still hot.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cream cheese and contents of pear can.
Blend in blender until smooth.
Pour in molds and chill.
Serves 8.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash spinach.
Dry; remove stems and tear up.
Slice onion thin and separate into rings.
Trim mushroom stems; rinse and slice.
Drain oranges and hull berries.
In large bowl, toss ingredients.
Turn into large salad bowl (5 to 6-quart) and add dressing lightly.
Sprinkle with bacon and serve.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, salt, soda and cinnamon. Add oil, vanilla, eggs and pineapple. Mix by hand (no mixer).
Fold in bananas and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: low-fat minestrone soup
directions: In 3-quart casserole (for microwave) or large soup pot (for top of stove).
Combine all ingredients, cover and microwave on High (about 45 minutes, stirring once), or simmer on the top of the stove, until all vegetables are tender.

title: spinach mashed potatoes
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Add sour cream, sugar, butter, salt and pepper.
Beat with mixer until light and fluffy.
Add chives, dill and drained spinach.
Place in casserole and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Delicious!

title: green bean bundles
directions: Drain green beans and separate into groups of about 7 beans. Wrap each bundle with one slice of bacon and secure with a toothpick.
Arrange in a well greased 9 by 13-inch baking dish. Pour Italian dressing evenly over bundles.
Sprinkle on enough brown sugar to suit your taste.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes.
Drain and and remove toothpicks.
Serve hot.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Blend the first 5 ingredients well.
Mix together the remaining ingredients; add to first mixture.
Mix well.
Bake in 2 loaf pans at 325° for 1 hour, or until done.
(I usually double the recipe, then make 3 loaves.
Increase time.)

title: nut pepper biscotti
directions: Combine the dry ingredients and set aside.
Cream the butter until light. Gradually add sugar.

Mix in eggs, one at a time. Add orange peel, vanilla and nuts. Add dry ingredients and mix until blended. Chill in refrigerator at least 1 hour. Grease and flour baking sheet. Divide and shape dough into 1 1/2-inch wide logs. Bake in preheated 350° oven until light brown, about 20 minutes. Cool slightly and cut on diagonal into 1/2-inch wide slices.
Turn cut side down and bake until golden, about 15 minutes.
Cool. These freeze well.

title: shortcut biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Cut shortening into flour with pastry blender until mixture resembles fine crumbs.
Stir in just enough milk so dough leaves side of bowl and rounds up into a ball (too much milk makes dough sticky, not enough makes biscuits dry).

title: tomato-less meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well and shape into a loaf.
Bake at 375° for 60 to 90 minutes.

title: orange treat salad
directions: Boil 3 cups water and stir in Jell-O and pudding mixes.
Cook until thickened and set aside to cool.

title: cornbread stuffing
directions: Crumble sausage into a 3-quart microwave-safe casserole dish. Stir in onions and celery.
Cover with lid and microwave on High for 5 minutes or until sausage is no longer pink.
Stir once during cooking to separate meat.
Stir in butter, apples and broth.
Cover and microwave on High for 5 minutes or until apples are tender and broth is boiling, stirring once during cooking. Stir in stuffing mix, pecans and parsley.
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes.
Makes about 6 1/2 cups or 10 servings.
